(30, '', 'warning labels on social media', 'Warning Labels Needed for Social Media&#039;s Hidden Dangers', 'brand management digital marketing and business', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">US Surgeon General Vivek Murthy has issued a bold call to action, urging the addition of warning labels on social media apps to alert young people of the potential harm they can cause. The warning label, similar to those on tobacco products, aims to increase awareness and change behavior, according to Murthy. The surgeon general\'s warning comes as social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, and Snapchat have been accused of having a profoundly negative impact on children, including promoting negative body images, shortened attention spans, and vulnerability to online bullies and predators.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The concern is not unfounded. Young people are spending an average of four hours a day on social media, exposing them to a constant stream of curated content that can be detrimental to their mental health. The platforms\' algorithms are designed to be addictive, keeping users engaged for as long as possible by serving up increasingly provocative content. This can lead to a range of negative outcomes, including depression, anxiety, and even suicidal thoughts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Some US states have already taken steps to address the issue, passing legislation aimed at protecting children from the harmful effects of social media. For example, New York state has banned social media companies from serving addictive algorithmic content to users under the age of 18 without parental consent. Florida has gone further, banning children under 14 from using social media altogether and requiring 14- and 15-year-olds to get parental consent.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Murthy\'s call for warning labels on social media apps is a critical step in addressing this public health crisis. By placing clear warnings on these platforms, we can empower young people and their parents to make informed decisions about their use of social media. It is time for Congress to take action and pass legislation requiring these warning labels, ensuring that young people are protected from the harms of social media.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-06-08', '21:32:23', 'warning-labels-on-social-media', 'article/visionariesnetwork-warning-labels-needed.jpg', 'social media warning', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-warning-labels-needed.jpg', 6, 2024, 'social media, social media news, latest news, visonaries network', 'Warning Labels Needed for Social Media&#039;s Hidden Dangers', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(31, '', 'Inside Out 2 Conquers Box Office Records', 'Inside Out 2 Conquers Box Office Records', 'Entertainment and Recreation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The highly anticipated Pixar film, Inside Out 2, has been a massive hit, breaking records and raking in a whopping $724 million worldwide. The animated movie has taken the top spot as the highest-grossing film of 2024, surpassing other blockbusters. Its success is a testament to the enduring popularity of the beloved franchise, which has captivated audiences of all ages.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In its second week of release, Inside Out 2 saw a slight decline in ticket sales, with a 35% drop in bookings. However, it still managed to pull in $100 million, a feat achieved by only a handful of movies. This impressive performance is a testament to the film\'s enduring appeal and the loyalty of its fan base.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Only a select group of movies have been able to achieve this level of success in their second week of release. These include some of the biggest blockbusters of all time, such as Star Wars: The Force Awakens, Avengers: Endgame, Infinity War, and Black Panther. The fact that Inside Out 2 has joined this exclusive club is a testament to its widespread appeal and the quality of its storytelling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">According to AP, the film is expected to easily cross the $1 billion mark within a week, making it the first movie to do so since Barbie\'s release last year. This milestone is a significant achievement for any film, and it cements Inside Out 2\'s status as one of the most successful movies of the year.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The film\'s success can be attributed to its engaging storyline, lovable characters, and stunning animation. The movie follows the adventures of Riley and her emotions as they navigate new challenges and learn valuable lessons about friendship and growing up. With its combination of humor, heart, and adventure, Inside Out 2 has become a must-see movie for fans of all ages.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-07-08', '23:28:24', 'inside-out-2-box-office', 'article/visionariesnetwork-conquers-box-office-records.jpg', 'Box Office Records', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-conquers-box-office-records.jpg', 7, 2024, 'Box Office Records, Box office, entertainment news, visionaries network', 'Inside Out 2 Conquers Box Office Records', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(32, NULL, 'openai launched chatgpt edu', 'OpenAI unveiled ChatGPT Edu: Game Changer for AI Adoption in Universities', 'Healthcare and Medical Devices', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">OpenAI has launched ChatGPT Edu, an AI technology tailored for universities to meaningfully integrate AI into campus and academic processes. With its GPT-4o engine, this new platform provides advanced text and vision reasoning capabilities, data analysis functionality, web browsing capability, and document summarization among many other features. Enterprise-class security paired with the affordable pricing makes ChatGPT Edu an instant favorite within the education sector.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Building on the success of ChatGPT Enterprise at the likes of the University of Oxford, the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania, amongst many others, ChatGPT Edu is about to change educational experiences as well as various operational efficiencies in education through AI.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Innovative Campus Applications</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Universities, otherwise have embraced ChatGPT quite diversely to beef up their operations. At Columbia University, for instance, Professor Nabila El-Bassel leads a project that uses Artificial intelligence to address overdose fatalities. Through the use of GPT- rapid analysis of data, its researchers conduct research much faster and, hence allow for timely interventions.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Wharton School equally has students of Professor Ethan Mollick use ChatGPT in coming up with questions for final reflection assignments. That deepens learning on course materials.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Also at Arizona State University, Assistant Professor Christiane Reves is developing a language-specific Language Buddies GPT to assist students in practicing German-giving them personalized conversations and feedback along the way.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">ChatGPT Edu Features</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">ChatGPT Edu comes with a range of features that cater to learning and operational processes at campuses. The following are some of such features:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull;Scan GPT-4o: Do text understanding, coding, and math as best as can be done.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull;Capabilities Adv: This lists data analytics, web browsing, and document summarization.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; One\'s own GPTS: Campus may develop and distribute its custom versions of ChatGPT in its space.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; High Message Limits: Its facility drives substantially extended usage compared with the free version of ChatGPT.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; Several language options: Apart from English it supports over 50 languages. Delivering is at high speed while the quality is also improved</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; Strong Security and Privacy: It has group permissions Single Sign-On, GPT management, SCIM 1-and. So, all your conversations between you and AI data are secret.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">However, Kyle Bowen, Arizona State University\'s Deputy CIO added that Open AI\'s tool may fundamentally change educational models and make it easier to collaborate and scale in consequence.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">ChatGPT Edu: Empowering Educational Institutions</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Designed for institutions interested in leveraging AI to better serve students and the community at large, ChatGPT Edu gives an easy way to scale the institutional implementation of AI. Interested educational stakeholders should reach out to Open AI\'s team to learn more about how it can be used.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2024-06-08', '23:36:34', 'openai-launched-chatgpt-edu', 'article/visionariesnetwork-openai-chatgptedu.jpg', 'OpenAI unveiled ChatGPT Edu', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-openai-chatgptedu.jpg', 6, 2024, 'OpenAI, ChatGPT Edu, ChatGPT,  AI Adoption in Universities, visonaries network', 'OpenAI unveiled ChatGPT Edu: Game Changer for AI Adoption in Universities', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(33, '', 'Pretoria Surgeons Open Zululand Spinal Center with Endoscopic Spinal Surgeries', 'Pretoria Surgeons Open Zululand Spinal Center with Endoscopic Spinal Surgeries', 'Healthcare and Medical Devices', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Three Pretoria-based spine surgeons have opened an advanced spinal care unit at the Empangeni Mediclinic. Spinal surgeons Dr. Sailesh Ragoo, Dr. Kritish Timakia, and Dr. Neil van der Berg have opened the Zululand Spinal Centre of Excellence.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The trio pools their expertise to ensure an interdisciplinary approach is taken for very complex procedures not before available locally. Dr. Ragoo has a long background in Orthopaedic Spinal Surgery; Dr. Timakia is in Neurosurgery; and Dr. Van der Berg is in Orthopaedic Surgery. Together, they promise superior care to patients presenting for advanced spinal treatment.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Of particular interest is the introduction of endoscopic spinal surgeries, a minimally invasive technique bound to change spinal interventions for good. This technology comes with reduced trauma, faster recovery, and lessening complications when placing it against the conventional methods, and therefore is very inviting for patients across all ages and health conditions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Endoscopic spinal surgeries have already brought some astonishing outcomes in terms of the improved mobility and quality of life of patients. Patients had to be drawn in from as far afield as Cape Town, while the team found itself called upon to revise those previously unsuccessful cases that might have been performed across the primary treatment spectrum.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Within this dream of changing lives to better spinal health and re-claiming mobility, the vision of founding the Zululand Spinal Centre of Excellence was conceived.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-06-08', '23:41:50', 'endoscopic-spinal-surgeries-in-zululand', 'article/visionariesnetwork-pretoria-surgeons-zululand-spinal-center.jpg', 'Pretoria Surgeons Open Zululand Spinal Center', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-pretoria-surgeons-zululand-spinal-center.jpg', 6, 2024, 'Pretoria Surgeon, Zululand Spinal Center, Endoscopic Spinal Surgeries, visionaries netwrok', 'Pretoria Surgeons Open Zululand Spinal Center with Endoscopic Spinal Surgeries', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(34, NULL, 'TCS IoT engineering lab in Cincinnati', 'TCS Opens New IoT Engineering Lab in Cincinnati to Boost Innovation', 'IoT and Robotics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Tata Consultancy Services has opened a new engineering lab for the Internet of Things in Cincinnati, Ohio. The new 3,000-square-foot lab has been specifically designed to run rapid prototyping, experimentation, and large-scale implementation for artificial intelligence, general AI, and IoT engineering solutions for its customers.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">The lab, as developed, will also strengthen the TCS suite of IoT solutions, including that of TCS Clever Energy, TCS Digital Manufacturing Platform (DMP), and that of TCS Digifleet. The given solutions will be brought in to serve different industries, such as healthcare, manufacturing, energy, consumer packaged goods, among several others.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">This will help the clients of TCS in developing innovative solutions using new facilities that enable increased collaboration and co-innovation between business entities. It is aimed at bringing together physical assets, partner technologies, and customer challenges to result in new offerings.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><strong><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Key projects at the IoT Engineering Lab include the following:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; <strong>Digital Twin of the Heart:</strong> TCS has come up with the first digital heart of a professional runner to showcase the potential for AI-empowered digital twin technology in changing how athletes train and receive health care.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; <strong>Building Software-Defined Vehicles:</strong> TCS empowers car manufacturers to build software-defined vehicles that are armed with GenAI, enabled for object detection, and able to monitor locales, people, vehicles, and other hazards on the road.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">&bull; <strong>Smart Gardening Technology:</strong> Engaging the community, TCS Grow+ has harvested over 3,500 pounds of fresh produce that is distributed to more than 500 families via food banks and other charities.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">The lab will be based in Cincinnati, home to TCS\'s largest delivery center in the Americas. The IoT engineering lab for TCS-connected transformations hosts a local talent reef of tech-savvy people that can support this real-time product connectivity model with TCS clients across North America. This investment looks into bridging operational and digital technology gaps with TCS clients.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2024-07-08', '23:48:12', 'tcs-iot-engineering-lab-in-cincinnati', 'article/visionariesnetwork-tcs-iot-engineering-lab-cincinnati.jpg', 'TCS Opens New IoT Engineering Lab', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-tcs-iot-engineering-lab-cincinnati.jpg', 7, 2024, 'TCS, IoT news, Cincinnati, IoT Engineering Lab, visionaries network', 'TCS Opens New IoT Engineering Lab in Cincinnati to Boost Innovation', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(35, '', 'Finisterre First Retail Store in Portland', 'Finisterre Makes Waves in North America with First Retail Store in Portland, Maine', 'retail and ecommerce', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Finisterre, a UK-based sustainable surf and outdoor apparel brand, has launched its first-ever North American retail store in partnership with Maine Surfers Union in Portland, Maine. The 1,100-square-foot storefront, located in the heart of the Old Port shopping district, reflects the brand\'s UK stores and serves as a \"launching pad and community hub\" for Finisterre\'s global retail expansion into North America.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">The store offers a range of men\'s and women\'s collections, including wetsuits, swimwear, and accessories such as the popular fluorocarbon-free Stormbird waterproof jacket and technical women\'s Anella swimsuit. Chris Evans, president and general manager of Finisterre North America, expressed his excitement about the partnership, stating that the brand is \"beyond stoked\" to launch with the Maine Surfers Union and the Portland community.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">The store will also host events with the Maine Surfers Union, including film screenings, beach clean-ups, roundtable discussions, and garment repair workshops. Finisterre founder Tom Kay praised the partnership, saying it\'s a significant milestone in the brand\'s journey and thanking Charlie and the crew at Maine Surfers Union for making it happen.</span></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-07-30', '21:50:21', 'finisterre-first-retail-store-in-portland', 'article/visionariesnetwork-finisterre-north-america-firs-retai--rtore.jpg', 'finisterre north america first retail store', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-finisterre-north-america-firs-retai--rtore.jpg', 7, 2024, 'Finisterre,,First Retail Store, Portland', 'Finisterre First Retail Store in Portland', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(36, '', 'abb robotics introduced omnicore', 'ABB Robotics Unveils OmniCore, a Next-Generation Automation Solution', 'iot-and-robotics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">ABB Robotics has introduced OmniCore&trade;, a cutting-edge automation platform designed to revolutionize business productivity and flexibility. This innovative platform, backed by a strategic investment exceeding $170 million, heralds a new era of faster, more precise, and sustainable automation solutions.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">The OmniCore platform represents a significant leap forward in robotics control architecture, seamlessly integrating AI, sensor technology, cloud computing, and edge computing systems. This integration enables the development of highly advanced and autonomous robotic applications, addressing the evolving needs of industries worldwide.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Sami Atiya, President of ABB&rsquo;s Robotics &amp; Discrete Automation Business Area, emphasized the strategic importance of automation for businesses navigating challenges such as labor shortages, uncertainty, and sustainability imperatives. He highlighted how OmniCore\'s intelligent features empower businesses to achieve greater flexibility, simplicity, and efficiency in response to these global megatrends.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">With its class-leading motion performance, OmniCore ensures unparalleled robot path accuracy, enabling applications in precision-critical sectors such as arc welding, mobile phone assembly, and laser cutting. The platform enables robots to operate up to 25 percent faster while consuming up to 20 percent less energy compared to previous ABB controllers, resulting in significant productivity gains and cost savings.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Built on a scalable and modular control architecture, OmniCore offers a diverse range of functions to suit various industries, including biotechnology and construction. With over 1,000 hardware and software features, customers can easily design, operate, maintain, and optimize their operations, supported by software solutions like ABB\'s Absolute Accuracy and PickMaster&reg; Twin.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">Marc Segura, Division President of ABB Robotics, underscored OmniCore\'s transformative impact on industries, emphasizing its ability to manage motion, sensors, and application equipment within a unified system. This unified approach unlocks endless possibilities and avenues for value creation, empowering businesses to achieve new levels of efficiency and competitiveness.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-language: EN-IN;\">OmniCore represents the latest milestone in ABB Robotics\' 50-year history of innovation, building on past achievements such as the world\'s first microprocessor-controlled robot in 1974 and the introduction of RobotStudio&reg; software in 1998. With OmniCore, ABB Robotics aims to empower customers across all sectors to overcome future challenges and drive industry breakthroughs.</span></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-12-30', '00:44:40', 'abb-robotics-introduced-omnicore', 'article/visionariesnetwork-abb-robotics.jpg', 'abb robotics introduced omnicore', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-abb-robotics.jpg', 12, 2024, 'ABB Robotics, OmniCore,  Next-Generation, Automation Solution, latest news', 'abb robotics introduced omnicore', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(37, '', 'perforation type anchors humanoid robotics', 'Revolutionizing Humanoid Robotics: The Breakthrough of Perforation-Type Anchors', 'iot-and-robotics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a groundbreaking innovation, a team of researchers from the University of Tokyo has successfully developed perforation-type anchors that enable the attachment of living skin to robotic surfaces, a crucial step in creating humanoid robots that mimic human-like expressions. Building on their initial success with 2D robots, the team applied their innovative approach to a 3D facial mold, paving the way for more lifelike and functional robots.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>The Challenge of Adhesion</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While human skin-like tissue has been developed for humanoid robots, the challenge of attaching this skin to robotic parts has been a major hurdle. Traditional methods have struggled to provide a secure and natural attachment, making it difficult to achieve realistic expressions and interactions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Inspiration from Human Skin Ligaments</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Inspired by the way human skin ligaments attach the skin to muscles, the researchers proposed perforation-type anchors to overcome the adhesion challenge. These innovative anchors mimic the structure and function of human skin ligaments, allowing the living skin to integrate with the robotic surface. This secure attachment enables natural movements and expressions, making humanoid robots more lifelike and engaging.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Optimizing Anchor Density</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The study also explored the relationship between anchor size, arrangement, and anchoring strength. By tailoring anchor density to specific areas, researchers can optimize adhesion based on the function and interaction with the environment. For example, areas with frequent external contact would require a higher anchor density, while regions needing flexibility would have fewer anchors.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Implications and Future Directions</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This breakthrough has significant implications for humanoid robotics, enabling the creation of more lifelike and functional robots that can seamlessly interact with humans. The integration of human-like skin with robots not only improves their aesthetic appeal but also enhances their interaction capabilities, bringing us closer to a future where robots blend seamlessly into our daily lives.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With this innovative technology, researchers have overcome a major hurdle in humanoid development, paving the way for further advancements in robotics and artificial intelligence. As we move forward, we can expect to see humanoid robots that are more lifelike, expressive, and engaging, revolutionizing the way we interact with machines and each other.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-08-21', '00:42:31', 'perforation-type-anchors-humanoid-robotics', 'article/visionariesnetwork-revolutionizing-humanoid-robotics.jpg', 'revolutionizing-humanoid-robotics', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-revolutionizing-humanoid-robotics.jpg', 8, 2024, 'perforation, anchors, humanoid robotics, latest news, visionaries network', 'perforation type anchors humanoid robotics', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(38, '', 'Costco Travel Can Make Your Travel Dreams a Reality', 'Costco Travel Can Make Your Travel Dreams a Reality', 'tourism and hospitality', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Costco, the retail giant known for its buying-in-bulk deals and affordable hot dogs, has a travel section dedicated to helping consumers find savings on their next adventure. Costco Travel is a one-stop shop for booking travel arrangements, offering discounted rates on hotel and flight combinations. According to travel expert Mark Ellwood, Costco Travel could be the new go-to destination for travel planning.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Ellwood notes that one of the key benefits of using Costco Travel is the discounted rates on hotel and flight bookings. <em>\"They sell travel at discounted rates, especially if you\'re looking for hotels and flights together,\" </em>he explains. \"It\'s great at peak times, even last-minute because the pricing works out cheaper.\" This means that customers can score better deals on their travel arrangements without sacrificing quality or service.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With Costco Travel, customers can book flights, hotels, and car rentals all in one place, making it easy to plan and book their entire trip. Ellwood highlights the convenience of using Costco Travel, saying, \"It\'s a one-stop shop for all your travel needs.\" By leveraging its massive buying power and partnerships with major airlines, hotels, and other travel providers, Costco Travel is poised to revolutionize the way they book travel. Whether you\'re planning a quick weekend getaway or a luxurious vacation, Costco Travel could be the key to unlocking incredible savings and making your next trip truly unforgettable.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2024-08-29', '22:07:42', 'costco-travel-deals', 'article/visionariesnetwork-costco-travel.jpg', 'costco travel', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-costco-travel.jpg', 8, 2024, 'Costco Travel, Travel Dreams, travel, tourism, latest news', 'Costco Travel Can Make Your Travel Dreams a Reality', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(39, '', 'Amazon Retail Chief Stresses Balance Between Cost-Cutting and Innovation', 'Amazon Retail Chief Stresses Balance Between Cost-Cutting and Innovation', 'retail and ecommerce', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">During a recent meeting at the company, Amazon Retail Chief Doug Herrington discussed making the balance of cost-cutting versus innovation. If a team aims solely to be efficient, then they may forfeit creativity and expansion, Herrington cautioned. Herrington declared, \"My suggestion would be for all the teams that if you find yourself only doing cost reduction with no invention and innovation, or if you find yourself only working on innovation and not thinking at all about how to become more efficient, then you probably don\'t have the right balance.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This counsel comes as Amazon Retail is also endeavoring to reduce its costs. The company has already shed over 27,000 employees since late 2022, including 200 jobs eliminated from its fashion and fitness department last month. Despite these layoffs, Amazon Retail will be investing a record $105 billion in new ventures for 2025, all aimed at expansion. Herrington noted that such investments are critical, stating, <em>\"We have to keep cutting costs so that we can pay for the big investments in big new businesses.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Amazon\'s retail Chief Financial Officer Gail Carpenter illustrated how the savings initiatives of the company contribute towards enhancing the experiences of the customers. According to her, <em>\"When we eliminate waste and inefficiency, we can provide faster delivery, lower prices, and more selection profitably.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Amazon is concentrating on accelerating its shipping and reducing its expenses. The business is said to have lowered its cost to ship per unit within the last two years. Moving forward, Herrington disclosed that it will keep investing in quick delivery alternatives like same-day delivery and drone delivery, and AI-motivated ideas like the shopping bot Rufus.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br>Amazon Retail aims to remain competitive by being efficient yet innovative, and at the same time enhancing the customer experience.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-03-06', '21:50:03', 'amazon-retail-chief-stresses-balance-between-cost-cutting-and-innovation', 'article/visionariesnetwork-amazon-retail.jpg', 'Amazon Retail Chief Stresses Balance Between Cost-Cutting and Innovation', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-amazon-retail.jpg', 3, 2025, 'Amazon Retail, Chief Stresses Balance, Cost-Cutting, Innovation, latest news, updated news', 'Amazon Retail Chief Stresses Balance Between Cost-Cutting and Innovation', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(40, '', 'Biocon Biologics, Civica Team Up to Expand Insulin Aspart Access in U.S.', 'Biocon Biologics, Civica Team Up to Expand Insulin Aspart Access in U.S.', 'healthcare and medical devices', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-IN; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Biocon Biologics and Civica, Inc. issued a major announcement on Thursday to make it easier for people in the United States to get affordable diabetes treatment, Insulin Aspart.<br><br>The official announcement states that Biocon Biologics will supply the drug substance of Insulin Aspart to Civica. Civica will utilize the drug substance of Insulin Aspart to manufacture the drug product of Insulin Aspart in its Petersburg, Virginia, facility. The companies assured that the deal doesn\'t involve technology transfer.<br><br>Civica will market the drug in the United States after completing extensive development work and clinical trials. The alliance is aimed at making the drug more accessible and affordable for diabetes patients in the nation.<br><br><em>\"As a global biologics player, Biocon Biologics is positioned to succeed through smart marketing practices that work for everyone. Our collaboration with Civica is a testament to this intention, enabling us to make Insulin Aspart accessible to more patients in the United States and demonstrating our commitment to treating individuals with diabetes. Together, we are making high-quality, affordable insulin accessible to more patients,\"</em> said Shreehas Tambe, CEO &amp; Managing Director, Biocon Biologics Ltd.<br><br>This deal is to be added to Biocon Biologics\' own Insulin Aspart drug product, which is under review by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA). The firm has been making a concerted effort to introduce high-quality biosimilars to the market, responding to the increasing need for low-cost insulin.<br><br>Most Americans must be able to afford insulin. There are approximately 38.4 million people with diabetes, which makes up around 11.6% of Americans. Additionally, approximately 97.6 million Americans are prediabetic. It is frightening to know that for every five individuals with diabetes, one person has reported rationing, delaying, or avoiding taking less insulin than prescribed since it is unaffordable.<br><br><em>\"Civica\'s mission is to provide affordable generic and biosimilar drugs to those who need them. This holds true for patients with diabetes, one in five of whom have postponed, cut out, or reduced insulin doses to save on costs. Our partnership with Biocon Biologics for the supply of Aspart drug substance will allow us to fulfill our meaningful mission and assist patients who need access to Insulin Aspart. Civica will manufacture prefilled vials and pens of insulin through our Petersburg, Virginia, manufacturing facilities,\"</em> said Ned McCoy, President and Chief Executive Officer, Civica, Inc.<br><br>This collaboration is in the right direction towards addressing the issue of insulin prices. It indicates that both firms are committed to ensuring health for the population through provision of required diabetes care.<br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></span></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-03-03', '21:42:06', 'biocon-biologics-civica-team-up-to-expand-insulin-aspart-access-in-us', 'article/visionariesnetwork-biocon.jpg', 'biocon', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-biocon.jpg', 3, 2025, 'Biocon Biologics Civica Team, Insulin, Biocon news, Biotechnology, latest news', 'Biocon Biologics, Civica Team Up to Expand Insulin Aspart Access in U.S.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(41, '', 'DHL eCommerce Opens &pound;482M Parcel Hub Near Coventry Airport', 'DHL eCommerce Opens &pound;482M Parcel Hub Near Coventry Airport', 'retail and ecommerce', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-IN; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">DHL eCommerce has&nbsp;opened&nbsp;a massive 25,000 m&sup2; parcel&nbsp;hub&nbsp;to the&nbsp;south of Coventry Airport.&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a significant&nbsp;investment&nbsp;as&nbsp;part of&nbsp;the company\'s &pound;482 million&nbsp;plan&nbsp;to&nbsp;advance&nbsp;logistics&nbsp;in the UK.&nbsp;The&nbsp;new center has the capacity&nbsp;to&nbsp;process&nbsp;over one million parcels per day.&nbsp;It&nbsp;is expected to&nbsp;create&nbsp;a&nbsp;potential&nbsp;of&nbsp;600 jobs&nbsp;and&nbsp;enhance&nbsp;both domestic and international&nbsp;online&nbsp;buying services.<br><br>The UK&nbsp;online&nbsp;retail&nbsp;market&nbsp;is&nbsp;growing&nbsp;very&nbsp;quickly&nbsp;and&nbsp;is&nbsp;estimated&nbsp;to&nbsp;be&nbsp;&pound;176 billion by 2029. To&nbsp;be&nbsp;a part of&nbsp;this, DHL&nbsp;has recently opened a&nbsp;new&nbsp;package&nbsp;center&nbsp;with&nbsp;advanced automation, a&nbsp;space of&nbsp;48&nbsp;doors&nbsp;where packages can be moved, and&nbsp;storage for&nbsp;efficient&nbsp;customs services.<br><br>At&nbsp;the grand&nbsp;launch, Business Minister Justin Madders emphasized&nbsp;how&nbsp;the hub&nbsp;will&nbsp;impact&nbsp;the economy, stating:<br><br>\"The West Midlands is a&nbsp;great&nbsp;place&nbsp;to invest, and this&nbsp;new&nbsp;Coventry&nbsp;hub&nbsp;will not only&nbsp;provide&nbsp;plenty&nbsp;of local jobs but&nbsp;also&nbsp;support&nbsp;our logistics&nbsp;business&nbsp;and&nbsp;deliver&nbsp;to&nbsp;our&nbsp;customers&nbsp;quicker.\"<br><br>DHL&nbsp;eCommerce&nbsp;CEO&nbsp;Pablo&nbsp;Ciano&nbsp;noted&nbsp;that&nbsp;the&nbsp;firm&nbsp;is&nbsp;dedicated&nbsp;to meeting&nbsp;increasing&nbsp;demand, saying,<br><br><em>\"With our&nbsp;expansion&nbsp;to our network, we are&nbsp;greatly&nbsp;increasing&nbsp;our&nbsp;ability&nbsp;to sort&nbsp;and&nbsp;process,&nbsp;so&nbsp;we&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;ready&nbsp;to&nbsp;meet&nbsp;our customers\'&nbsp;needs and&nbsp;help&nbsp;their business&nbsp;grow.\"</em><br><br>The new parcel hub&nbsp;is&nbsp;sustainable and&nbsp;has&nbsp;a BREEAM&nbsp;\'Excellent\'&nbsp;rating.&nbsp;It&nbsp;features 7,000m&sup2; of solar panels, LED lighting, and&nbsp;wildlife-friendly landscaping.&nbsp;There&nbsp;are also&nbsp;120 electric vehicle charging points&nbsp;to&nbsp;assist&nbsp;with&nbsp;cleaner&nbsp;logistics.<br><br>This expansion&nbsp;solidifies&nbsp;DHL eCommerce\'s position as a&nbsp;leading&nbsp;firm&nbsp;in the UK&nbsp;delivery&nbsp;sector,&nbsp;resulting&nbsp;in&nbsp;faster deliveries and&nbsp;ongoing&nbsp;industry&nbsp;expansion.<br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></span></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-03-04', '21:49:52', 'dhl-ecommerce-opens-parcel-hub-near-coventry-airport', 'article/visionariesnetwork-dhl-ecommerce.jpg', 'DHL eCommerce Opens', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-dhl-ecommerce.jpg', 3, 2025, 'DHL, eCommerce, Parcel Hub, Coventry Airport, DHL news', 'DHL eCommerce Opens &pound;482M Parcel Hub Near Coventry Airport', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(42, '', 'Retail Demand Remains Inconsistent, Festive Season Drives Temporary Growth', 'Retail Demand Remains Inconsistent, Festive Season Drives Temporary Growth', 'retail and ecommerce', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">Indian retail demand varies. The sales increase primarily when there are festive seasons, observes Kumar Rajagopalan, CEO of Retailers Association of India (RAI). There was some increase in January and February 2025, sure, but retailing is never easy when it is not a peak shopping time.<br><br>RAI figures show retail sales increased by 5% in January, and February will also be the same. \"We don\'t have February\'s figures yet, but from what we have and what we\'ve heard, it seems there won\'t be much change,\" Rajagopalan said. The increase is moderate in comparison to last year, reflecting cautious expenditure by middle-class and poor families.<br><br>Retail demand has performed better in key festive months like October, November, and December, with sales rising by 8%. This was due to rising numbers of people looking to buy clothes, footwear, and jewelry. But in the off-season, retail demand has not actually picked up, which means sustainable growth is still a problem.<br><br>Food and luxury goods sales have remained relatively strong, but consumers have spent very little on discretionary items. Shoppers are being closely monitored by retailers as they prepare ways to propel sales throughout the year, rather than waiting for holiday buying.<br><br>The retail sector is looking to emphasize special offers, improving in-store shopping experiences, and online sales gains to drive long-term sales. But unless the economy as a whole picks up, stores can still experience low levels of spending during the slower periods.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-03-04', '21:49:36', 'retail-demand-remains-inconsistent-festive-season-drives-temporary-growth', 'article/visionariesnetwork-retail-demand.jpg', 'Retail Festive Season Drives Temporary Growth', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-retail-demand.jpg', 3, 2025, 'Retail, Festive Season, Temporary Growth, retail news, latest news', 'Retail Demand Remains Inconsistent, Festive Season Drives Temporary Growth', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(43, '', 'Revolutionizing Antibacterial Coatings with Silver Nanoparticles: Innovation in Surface Protection', 'Revolutionizing Antibacterial Coatings with Silver Nanoparticles', 'biotechnology and pharmaceuticals', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">A new method of combating bacterial infections associated with medical devices has been found in a recent study by Dr. Ashwin Ambi and his team. Such infections are among the leading causes of issues in healthcare. The research explains the limitations of conventional antibiotic coatings, which have enabled drug-resistant bacteria to thrive. Instead, it employs silver nanoparticles (AgNPs) to develop an improved and safer method of preventing infections that may revolutionize the way infections are prevented in hospitals.<br><br><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span><strong>Emergent Plasma Technology to Improve Antibacterial Activity<br></strong><br><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>The study takes into account argon plasma grafting technology, which facilitates easy adherence of silver nanoparticles to the surfaces of biomaterials. The new method increases the efficacy of the nanoparticles in fighting bacteria and remaining stable over the long term. Scientists have created surfaces that are highly efficient in fighting bacteria and safe for human tissue by regulating the quantity of AgNPs utilized and the rate of release.<br><br><strong>Successful History of Fighting Drug-Resistant Bacteria<br><br></strong>To verify the effectiveness of AgNP-coated biomaterials, the scientists conducted a number of tests for antibacterial and anti-biofilm properties. The tests revealed that an adequate number of silver nanoparticles on the surface were able to effectively prevent bacteria from adhering and developing biofilms, even drug-resistant bacteria such as Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) and Escherichia coli. This is a pioneering discovery that indicates AgNP-immobilized biomaterials can be highly effective in preventing infections associated with medical devices.<br><br><strong>Ensuring Biocompatibility and Safety<br><br></strong>In addition to antibacterial activity, the AgNP-coated surfaces were also comprehensively tested for biocompatibility. Interestingly, human fetal osteoblasts, bone growth cells, were shown to be viable on the surfaces, demonstrating that the materials are non-toxic to human tissue. Such a balance between antibacterial activity and cell viability is critical in the creation of safe, long-term medical devices.<br><br><strong>Changing Clinical Uses<br></strong><br>This research has various applications. Silver nanoparticle-coated material can be added to different medical devices, including catheters, implants, and surgical tools. These materials can stop bacteria from developing into a layer, which can possibly reduce infection levels and help in the recovery of patients, without raising healthcare expenditures.<br><br>While scientists are still refining the process and testing long-term stability, silver nanoparticles are leading the way toward a bright future in the battle against medical-device-related infections.<br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-03-05', '21:22:59', 'revolutionizing-antibacterial-coatings-with-silver-nanoparticles', 'article/visionariesnetwork-antibacterial-coatings-silver-nanoparticles.jpg', 'antibacterial coatings silver nanoparticles', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-antibacterial-coatings-silver-nanoparticles.jpg', 3, 2025, 'antibacterial coatings, silver nanoparticles, antimicrobial technology, surface protection, nanotechnology in coatings, silver-based coatings, nanomaterials for bacteria prevention, advanced coating solutions, antibacterial innovation, sustainable surface protection', 'Explore how silver nanoparticles are revolutionizing antibacterial coatings, offering cutting-edge solutions for surface protection. Learn about the benefits of nanotechnology in antimicrobial coatings and how silver-based innovations are shaping industries like healthcare, manufacturing, and consum', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);
