(101, '', 'Bitcoin Dip Below $77K Sparks Market Turmoil', 'Bitcoin Dip Below $77K Sparks Market Turmoil', 'blockchain and cryptocurrency', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a surprise move for the&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/crypto-etfs-approved-wall-streets-biggest-bet-on-blockchain-stocks-yet\">cryptocurrency</a></span> space, Bitcoin (BTC), the world\'s most valuable cryptocurrency dipped below $77,000 on Wednesday morning (April 9), sending shivers down investors\' spines. This Bitcoin dip illustrates the continued rollercoaster effect in the market due to worldwide tensions, particularly the fresh U.S. tariffs on China. <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://coinmarketcap.com/\">CoinMarketCap</a></span> data indicates that the total Market Fear &amp; Greed Index stood at 15 (Extreme Fear), which illustrates the prevailing uncertainty.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">When this was being written, Bitcoin was trading at $76,452.37, down 4.08 percent in the last 24 hours. BTC was traded in India at approximately Rs 65.87 lakh. Ethereum (ETH), the second largest altcoin in terms of market capitalization, also fell sharply, down 8.25 percent to $1,454.86. Other top altcoins, such as Solana (SOL), Ripple (XRP), and Litecoin (LTC), also fell, with the losses ranging from 3% to 5%.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Altcoins are losing value</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Dogecoin (DOGE) fell 4.90% and was trading at $0.1438</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Litecoin (LTC) fell 3.43% to $69.79</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Ripple (XRP) fell by 4.18% to $1.80</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Solana (SOL) declined by 4.59% to $105.49</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The global crypto market capitalization stood at $2.43 trillion, having decreased by 3.62% in the last 24 hours.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Main Movers</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The biggest gainer of the day was JasmyCoin (JASMY), which gained 5.05% to $0.01038. The other notable gainers were Story (IP), UNUS SED LEO (LEO), Four (FORM), and Hyperliquid (HYPE).</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But the largest loser was the AB token, dropping more than 27% over the past 24 hours. Fartcoin (FART), NEAR Protocol (NEAR), and Lido DAO (LDO) also suffered double-digit declines.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What Experts Say Regarding Bitcoin dip</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/edulpatel/?originalSubdomain=in\">Edul Patel, the CEO at Mudrex</a></span>, said the following about the circumstance: \"Bitcoin has recovered to $76,000 after retouching the support level around $74,500. Both the U.S.-China trade war and volatility in the equity market are catalyzing the move. Despite the recent downtrend in Bitcoin dip, whales accumulation is still being observed, indicating long-term confidence.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Unocoin CEO Sathvik Vishwanath clarified, \"Today\'s big 5.7% drop is pricing in growing jitters. Tech signals indicate that Bitcoin is on the verge of hitting oversold levels. If the price does not hold above $74K, it could see a further fall nearer to $70K.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Extended Role</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The U.S.\'s 104% <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/china-manufacturing-sector-faces-challenges-amid-trade-tensions\">tariff on Chinese imports</a></span> is being regarded as the main reason. The S&amp;P 500 dropped 1.57%, having a domino effect on financial markets globally. Cryptocurrency exchanges such as CoinSwitch and BuyUcoin report that investors are split in their sentiment, with some believing this is an opportunity to buy and others believing there will be more falls.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">BuyUcoin CEO Shivam Thakral stated, \"This latest Bitcoin dip shows how sensitive the market is towards big economic movements. While there are investors out there who are purchasing the dip, the future is uncertain.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Outlook for Bitcoin </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are analysts who believe the recent drop won\'t be lasting. Pi42 CEO Avinash Shekhar stated, \"Bitcoin\'s RSI is making a bottom for a bull market. That means there should be a bottom around $70K. Some short-term losses will result in a turnaround in the middle term.\" The CoinDCX Research Team is still bearish: \"The market is in a state of fear. Unless Bitcoin maintains its support levels, a correction to deeper levels is possible. The sentiment for this Bitcoin dip remains bearish for now.\"</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-04-09', '23:29:43', 'bitcoin-dip-below-77k-sparks-market-turmoil', 'article/visionaries-network-bitcoin-dip-below-dollar77k.webp', 'Bitcoin Dip Below $77K Sparks Market Turmoil', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-bitcoin-dip-below-dollar77k.webp', 4, 2025, 'Bitcoin dip, market turmoil, cryptocurrency crash, Bitcoin price drop, crypto market, Bitcoin news, digital currency, visionaries network, Bitcoin fall, cryptocurrency news', 'Bitcoin dips below $77K, causing significant market turmoil. The drop shakes investor confidence and fuels volatility in the cryptocurrency market.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(102, NULL, 'Micron Technology Adds Surcharge to Offset Trump Tariffs', 'Micron Technology Adds Surcharge to Offset Trump Tariffs', 'semiconductors', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.micron.com/\">Micron Technology, a US-based memory chip manufacturer</a></span>, has informed customers that it will implement a surcharge on certain products starting Wednesday, April 9, to offset the impact of the Trump tariffs recently imposed by President Donald Trump. These tariffs are part of a broader trade policy shift that is affecting imports from several Asian countries, where Micron has most of its manufacturing facilities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Micron&rsquo;s Overseas Manufacturing Faces Tariff Pressure</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Micron Technology manufactures a significant portion of its products in Asia, including China, Taiwan, Japan, Malaysia, and Singapore. With the new tariff regime taking effect, memory modules and solid-state drives (SSDs) imported from these countries are now subject to additional import duties, despite semiconductors being spared in the latest announcement.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Memory Modules and SSDs Now Come at a Premium</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a letter to customers, Micron clarified that the surcharge will apply specifically to memory modules and SSDs &mdash; essential components for data storage in devices like laptops, vehicles, and data center servers. These products are integral to modern computing and enterprise <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/amcham-korea-signs-landmark-mou-for-seamless-integration-into-us-infrastructure\">infrastructure</a></span>, and the added cost may trickle down to end-users.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Company Aligns with March Earnings Call Message</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This decision supports what Micron executives stated during a March 21 post-earnings call that the company would pass tariff-related costs to customers rather than absorb them. The announcement follows closely behind a late-March notice to customers regarding price hikes due to unexpectedly strong demand.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Global Reaction to Trump Tariffs</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">President Trump&rsquo;s 10% tariff on imports from several countries went into effect over the weekend. Starting Wednesday, even steeper &ldquo;reciprocal&rdquo; tariffs &mdash; ranging from 11% to 50% will hit specific nations. This move has triggered concerns about a possible global trade conflict and economic downturn. The Trump tariffs are being viewed by many international suppliers as a disruptive force, challenging long-standing trade dynamics and business models.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Asian Suppliers Echo Micron&rsquo;s Stance</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Other companies in the memory chip industry are reacting similarly. A senior executive from an Asian NAND module firm told Reuters that they had also notified U.S. clients they would not bear the cost of the new tariffs. &ldquo;If they&rsquo;re not willing to bear the taxes, we can&rsquo;t ship. No business can afford to swallow tariffs this steep,&rdquo; the executive said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Impact on Customers and the Broader Tech Industry</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The surcharge from Micron Technology is expected to influence procurement strategies for businesses that rely on high-performance memory and storage. Industries ranging from automotive to <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/microsoft-at-50-celebrating-a-legacy-and-embracing-an-ai-driven-future\">cloud computing</a></span> may feel the ripple effect as suppliers adjust to the Trump tariffs and their long-term implications.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Conclusion: Who Will Bear the Cost?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As Trump tariffs continue to reshape international trade routes and cost structures, tech companies like Micron Technology are passing the burden to customers. The coming months will reveal how resilient global supply chains really are&mdash;and who ultimately pays the price.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-09', '23:45:23', 'micron-technology-adds-surcharge-to-offset-trump-tariffs', 'article/visionaries-network-micron-technology-trump-tariffs.webp', 'Micron Technology Adds Surcharge to Offset Trump Tariffs', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-micron-technology-trump-tariffs.webp', 4, 2025, 'Micron Technology, Trump tariffs, surcharge, semiconductor industry, tariffs impact, US-China trade, tech prices, global trade, tariff adjustments, Micron news', 'Micron Technology introduces a surcharge to offset the impact of Trump-era tariffs, aiming to manage costs in the semiconductor industry amid ongoing trade tensions.', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(103, NULL, 'Samsung Price Hike Sparks Concern Amid US Tariff Threats', 'Samsung Electronics Price Hike Sparks Concern Amid US Tariff Threats', 'semiconductors', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.samsung.com/in/\">Samsung Electronics</a></span> hiked the price of its DRAM and NAND flash memory chips by 3% to 5%. They attribute this to uncertainty regarding potential US tariffs on imports of semiconductors. Samsung Electronics price hike comes after the global financial markets reacted to heightened trade tensions as a result of US President Donald Trump\'s recent moves to slap <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/china-manufacturing-sector-faces-challenges-amid-trade-tensions\">tariffs</a></span>. They have the potential to disrupt semiconductor supply chains and dampen world economic growth.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Industry observers note that this move is a proper response to the threat of tariffs that could be imposed on some semiconductor products. If such tariffs are imposed, the extra cost to chipmakers and electronics firms could make memory chips even more expensive over the next few months.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Samsung Electronics price hike to manage future risks</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Analysts attribute Samsung Electronics price hike to coping with potential US trade restrictions. \"Companies are preparing for a tough second half of the year,\" said Kevin Liu, a semiconductor market analyst. \"This price increase is an indication of what the industry anticipates: increased operating expenses and reduced profits if tariffs are enforced.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The NAND flash memory and DRAM markets react strongly to changes in demand and supply. In recent times, companies like Samsung have reduced output to address oversupply. However, with trade risks being such a significant problem, this tight supply&mdash;along with defensive pricing maneuvers&mdash;may lead to even higher costs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Chip prices rise due to supply cuts</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Memory chip manufacturing remains constrained as firms take a wait-and-see stance. Most manufacturers cut production during the 2024 downturn in demand and have not yet regained full capacity. Thus, analysts expect memory prices to rise further in Q3 and Q4 of 2025, particularly if US tariffs are ultimately implemented.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Samsung Electronics price hike will be experienced throughout prices in the technology sector. Smartphone, PC manufacturers, and data center companies that use DRAM and NAND flash chips will likely increase prices to consumers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Market reaction reflects broader concerns</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Investors and market analysts are reading the jump in Samsung Electronics\' price as an indicator of wider trade and supply chain fluctuation. Shares of semiconductors remained more volatile in the aftermath, with most paying close attention to any developments out of US trade officials.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/how-an-ecg-smartwatch-is-revolutionizing-heart-health-among-young-adults\">Samsung&rsquo;s</a></span> move is more than just a pricing decision&mdash;it&rsquo;s a defensive strategy in response to global trade uncertainties,&rdquo; said Julia Cheng, an economist focused on Asia-Pacific markets. &ldquo;It highlights how sensitive the tech industry is to geopolitical developments.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While discussions relating to trade continue between the US and influential countries, memory chip technology stands out prominently right now. Increasing expense, potential tariffs, and contracted availability may transform how producers and users approach technology procurement in the forthcoming future.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-09', '23:53:54', 'samsung-electronics-price-hike-sparks-concern-amid-us-tariff-threats', 'article/visionaries-network-samsung-electronics-price-hike.webp', 'Samsung Price Hike Sparks Concern Amid US Tariff Threats', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-samsung-electronics-price-hike.webp', 4, 2025, 'Samsung Electronics, price hike, US tariffs, trade tensions, visionaries network, tariff threats, Samsung news, global trade, US-China tariffs, tech industry', 'Samsung Electronics raises prices, raising concerns amid ongoing US tariff threats. The hike impacts consumer electronics and adds uncertainty in global tech markets.', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(104, NULL, 'Sports Analytics: Changing How We Watch and Predict Games', 'Sports Analytics Is Changing How We Watch and Predict Games', 'data analytics and visualization', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Amidst the thrilling environment of a packed stadium, thousands of spectators hold their breath as a critical penalty kick unfolds. While the audience hangs in suspense, data scientists are studying these moments carefully through sports analytics. By transforming intricate data into simple-to-understand visuals, these specialists provide insights that assist coaches, players, and even gamblers on platforms such as <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://rajbet.co.in/index.html\">RajBet</a></span> in making more informed choices.<br><br>Sports today are not merely about physical ability; they are highly dependent on data-driven tactics. With the help of line graphs, heatmaps, and dashboards, sports analytics transforms raw data into actionable insights with ease, enabling teams to see trends and make the right choice.<br><br><strong>Identifying Patterns with Time-Series Charts<br></strong><br>Take a football team that has played ten games. Rather than analyzing complicated stats, a line graph can simply show how the team is doing, like dips in performance when a star player is out. This simple-to-grasp graph helps coaches know where to improve and make changes to their game plan if needed.<br><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span><br><strong>Heatmaps: Uncovering Tactical Insights</strong><br><br>Heatmaps can be used to indicate where the players are moving and where they are the busiest on the pitch. In football, they can indicate where a player is extremely busy, and this assists in planning. For instance, a heatmap can indicate that a midfielder would play almost entirely on the left side, which indicates where other teams should be focused.<br><br><strong>Head-to-Head Visuals: Clarifying Rivalries</strong><br><br>Visual comparisons, like bar charts, can settle arguments between rival teams by offering transparent, data-based insights. Through the analysis of statistics like recent wins, goals scored, and defense records, these visuals offer a balanced view of team performance, deflecting arguments away from personal beliefs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Applying sports analytics has transformed how teams prepare and compete. Translating information into easy-to-read pictures has enabled people on the inside to make informed decisions that enhance performance and planning.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Whether you\'re a coach strategizing for the game, an athlete looking to improve, or a punter on RajBet seeking an edge, using <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/how-realtime-monitoring-and-data-visualization-help-prevent-cyber-attacks\">visualizations with data</a></span> is vital for comprehending current sports life.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-09', '00:01:29', 'sports-analytics-is-changing-how-we-watch-and-predict-games', 'article/visionaries-network-sports-analytics.webp', 'Sports Analytics Is Changing How We Watch and Predict Games', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-sports-analytics.webp', 4, 2025, 'sports analytics, game predictions, sports data, analytics in sports, sports technology, predictive modeling, sports performance, sports trends, data-driven predictions, sports insights', 'Sports analytics is revolutionizing how we watch and predict games, providing deeper insights into performance, trends, and data-driven predictions for fans and teams alike.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(105, NULL, 'How to Start a Data Analyst Career: A Beginner&#039;s Guide', 'How to Start Data Analyst Career: A Simple Guide for Beginners', 'data analytics and visualization', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Nowadays, businesses rely on information to make smart choices. In&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/smartbiz-becomes-first-fintech-bank-approved-under-trump\">finance</a></span> and marketing, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/amazon-retail-chief-stresses-balance-between-cost-cutting-and-innovation\">retail</a></span> and <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/u-s--healthcare-system-is-failing-but-personalized-care-offers-hope\">healthcare</a></span>, data analyst professionals are needed in nearly every industry. If you\'re curious about how to start data analyst career, you\'re not alone. Many people, even non-tech individuals, are now choosing this profession because it\'s in demand, flexible, and fulfilling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Understand the Role of a Data Analyst</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Before you begin, it is essential to know what a data analyst does. They mostly gather, tidy up, and analyze data to help companies make informed decisions. They use tools to discover patterns, trends, and insights within data and then present them in clear and easy-to-understand terms. This helps leaders address problems and create better strategies.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To succeed in this role, you need to be comfortable with numbers, be methodical, and have a keen eye for detail. If that is you, you\'re halfway there.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Start with the Right Path</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the best first things you can do is enroll in a <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/courses?query=data%20analysis&amp;productDifficultyLevel=Beginner&amp;msockid=2aad64c6e205683d3ed37785e3f26953\">beginner\'s course in data analysis</a></span>. These will cover the fundamentals, such as the manipulation of spreadsheets, data visualization, and programming in rudimentary tools like SQL or Python. Good choices for beginners are available on platforms like the popular Coursera, Udemy, and LinkedIn Learning.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">These programs do not have any technical prerequisites, so they are ideal for students or career changers. Opt for one that has practical projects so that you can immediately apply what you learn.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Learn the Key Tools</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If you are interested in advancing in this profession, you must know some basic tools. There is Excel or Google Sheets, which are used to sort and analyze small datasets. And there is SQL, a programming language used to manage and query data in databases. This is one of the basic skills required for most data analyst roles.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You must learn Python or R, which are used for advanced analysis and automation. Lastly, learn Tableau or Power BI, which are used to create charts and dashboards that enable data to be easily read. Knowing these tools enables you to work on real-world projects confidently.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Get Some Hands-on Experience Even at a beginner level, you can gain useful experience through small projects. Try working out free data from websites like Kaggle or Data.gov. You can help your friend\'s business, work for non-profit organizations, or do small freelance jobs online. Such projects send the message to future employers that you have learned how to apply your skills.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Another fantastic method is portfolio projects. Build three or four quick case studies where you pose a question, examine data, and share findings. Share them on LinkedIn or <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://github.com/\">GitHub</a></span> to get your online handle in front of others.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Earn a Certificate</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If you wish to enhance your resume, apply for a data analyst certification. Two of the most popular ones are the Google Data Analytics Professional Certification and the IBM Data Analyst Certification. They have the basics in them and will guide you through learning paths.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Certificates show that you\'re dedicated to your career and can make your job search competitive. They\'re also a great way to obtain the most wanted skills from the professionals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Apply for Jobs and Continue Learning</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">After learning the fundamentals and having some portfolio, start applying for junior roles. You can look for roles like Junior Data Analyst or Data Assistant. Although you might not meet all the qualifications of the job, apply anyway. Mention your learning process, showcase your projects, and highlight your eagerness to learn. Remember that the key to success here is learning constantly. Be inquisitive, challenge yourself, and continuously learn to do things better.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If you\'re still thinking about how to start data analyst career, the answer is simple: start now. Sign up for a beginner course, play around with data, get familiar with the essential tools, and build a portfolio. This career is within reach of anyone eager to learn&mdash;and with time and patience, you can build a thriving career in the world of data.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-10', '00:07:28', 'how-to-start-data-analyst-career-a-simple-guide-for-beginners', 'article/visionaries-network-data-analytics-career-a-simple-guide.webp', 'How to Start Data Analyst Career: A Simple Guide for Beginners', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-data-analytics-career-a-simple-guide.webp', 4, 2025, 'data analyst career, start data analytics, beginner guide, data analysis, data science, career tips, data analyst skills, data tools, analytics job, entry-level data analyst', 'Learn how to start a data analyst career with this simple guide. Discover essential skills, tools, and tips to launch your career in data analysis.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(106, NULL, 'Westown Smart City to Transform KwaZulu-Natal', 'Westown Smart City South Africa Set to Transform KwaZulu-Natal', 'smart city and security infrastructure', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">South Africa has begun building a new smart city called Westown in KwaZulu-Natal. The large project will cost R15 billion ($805 million). Westown smart city South Africa initiative is one major transformation for the region. It is one that will transform the way people live, work, and play through the integration of contemporary buildings and digital technology.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The first part of the building started earlier this year. A town center, shopping mall, and public square are done, and they already have over 1,500 workers. Officials believe this project will help improve the economy in the western part of KwaZulu-Natal and bring in long-term private <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../magazine/profile/etumos-is-the-marketing-operations-expert-focused-on-helping-clients-activate-the-full-potential-of-their-marketing-investments\">investment</a></span>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A New City with a Purpose</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Westown is located to the west of Durban. It is being constructed as a place that has homes, businesses, health centers, and parks, all equipped with smart technology. The infrastructure has advanced traffic management systems, water conservation measures, and processes to detect utility problems. It is designed to be future-proof and efficient.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The city will generate more than 23,000 jobs and generate up to R500 million ($26 million) in annual revenue once completed. The project is said to be one of the country\'s most ambitious, particularly after past failures such as the <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.smec.com/project/lanseria-smart-city/\">Lanseria Smart City</a></span>, which could not be sustained despite initial momentum.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Westown\'s Vision Strategy</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Local officials and planners think Westown shows a new way of getting things done. Unlike previous <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://techbehemoths.com/blog/top-smart-cities-in-the-us\">smart city projects</a></span>, this one is playing out in carefully planned phases. The project is designed step by step, starting with building critical infrastructure first&mdash;like traffic management systems, police coordination systems, and energy-efficient utilities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Senior project manager Themba Masimula explained to the media, \"The point is to ensure that with this development, we have jobs and shopping and eating in one location. The vision is to transform the future development of the West.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">That vision appears to be taking shape as the first part is already underway, and many new job opportunities are being created. The aim is to provide a digital way of life that is attractive not just to locals but also to tourists, investors, and tech entrepreneurs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What\'s Next for Westown?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Over the next 15 years, the construction will be done in phases, with the next several months focused on government updates and working with developers. Community engagement and transparency with the process are key components of the project development plan.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Westown smart city South Africa project has already started generating interest from local investors and city planners who are keen to adopt its model. With its combination of smart technology, people-focused planning, and economic potential, Westown can serve as a blueprint for the future cities of the African continent.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As South Africa looks into smart urban spaces, the Westown smart city South Africa project could begin a new path for the nation to construct and maintain its cities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-10', '23:44:47', 'westown-smart-city-south-africa-set-to-transform-kwazulu-natal', 'article/visionaries-network-westown-smart-city-africa.webp', 'Westown Smart City South Africa Set to Transform KwaZulu-Natal', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-westown-smart-city-africa.webp', 4, 2025, 'Westown, smart city, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa, development, urban planning, innovation, infrastructure, economy, real estate, investment, technology, sustainability, future city, growth', 'Westown Smart City in KwaZulu-Natal is set to boost innovation, infrastructure, and economic growth in South Africa.', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(107, NULL, 'Digicomm Expands via EasyStreet Smart Poles Deal', 'Digicomm Expands with EasyStreet&rsquo;s Smart Composite Poles Deal', 'smart city and security infrastructure', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Digicomm International, the leading distributor and manufacturer in the&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/dot-and-nabard-join-hands-for-digital-empowerment-in-rural-india\">telecommunication sector</a></span>, has acquired EasyStreet Systems, a fast-growing firm that produces smart infrastructure. The significant acquisition will enable Digicomm to reign supreme in the future of telecommunication networks and smart cities, using sustainable and scalable technologies like smart composite poles.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Founded in 1993, Digicomm International is a reliable broadband service provider partner globally. Digicomm International has an extensive range of Fixed Wireless, HFC, and FTTx products of top brands such as CommScope, Tarana Wireless, and PPC. It also produces optical passives, EDFAs, and other vital components utilized in network installation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Digicomm is entering the fast-growing infrastructure space with the acquisition of EasyStreet Systems. They are offering solutions targeting the changing needs of cities, telcos, and developers constructing smart cities. EasyStreet was established in 2020 by experienced professionals Pete Chase and Kent Harrison. The company has received quick recognition for its smart composite poles, which are manufactured in the United States and meet Build America, Buy America (BABA) standards.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">These strong, lightweight poles support a variety of applications, including small cell networks, IoT sensors, EV charging, public lighting, and WiFi. Notably, the poles are stronger than steel but significantly lighter, reducing installation costs by up to 70% and reducing carbon emissions by up to 75%. This positions them ideally for fast, efficient deployment of smart city infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;We\'re thrilled to be joining the Digicomm family,\" said EasyStreet Systems CEO Pete Chase. \"With this alliance, we\'ll have the resources to grow faster and bring EasyStreet\'s solutions to new markets and customers around the world.\" Rob Donziger, CEO of Digicomm International, shared the excitement: \"EasyStreet offers something new and of value in the market. This acquisition helps us to respond to the growing need for smart infrastructure. Together, we feel there is much room for growth in the telecom, local government, and business areas.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With more people wanting smart cities, the inclusion of EasyStreet\'s smart composite poles in Digicomm\'s portfolio means that the company is dedicated to providing smart solutions. The acquisition also forms part of Digicomm\'s overall strategy to chase more opportunities that fit its vision of connected, efficient, and sustainable infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With this acquisition, Digicomm International is well positioned to become a market leader in smart infrastructure, offering combined solutions that improve connectivity, creativity, and performance.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>For more information, visit:</strong><br><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.digicomm.com\" target=\"_new\">www.digicomm.com</a></span><br><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.easystreetsystems.com\" target=\"_new\">www.easystreetsystems.com</a></span><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-11', '00:03:07', 'digicomm-expands-with-easystreets-smart-composite-poles-deal', 'article/visionaries-network-smart-street-poles.webp', 'Digicomm Expands with EasyStreet&rsquo;s Smart Composite Poles Deal', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-smart-street-poles.webp', 4, 2025, 'Digicomm, EasyStreet, smart poles, composite poles, telecom, infrastructure, expansion, smart city, technology, connectivity, urban solutions, innovation, network, digital, growth', 'Digicomm partners with EasyStreet to expand smart city infrastructure using advanced smart composite poles technology.', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(108, '', 'UK Fibre Rollout Led by Altnets &amp; CommScope', 'UK Fibre Network Partnership: Altnets and CommScope Lead Rollout', 'telecommunication and electronics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To accelerate the United Kingdom\'s transition to full-fibre broadband,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.altnets.co.uk/\">Altnets</a></span> has entered into a landmark UK fibre network partnership with <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.commscope.com/\">CommScope</a></span>, a world network leader. The deal is more than a typical distribution agreement&mdash;Altnets will offer fibre-specific <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/amcham-korea-signs-landmark-mou-for-seamless-integration-into-us-infrastructure\">infrastructure</a></span> solutions critical to network build-out, upgrading central offices, and enhancing broadband services nationwide.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Altnets\' Role in Project Gigabit</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Altnets, one of the leading fibre suppliers in the UK based in Brighton, has made a significant contribution in bridging the digital divide in the nation. With this new alliance, Altnets will leverage its long-established industry connections and market reputation to sell and distribute CommScope\'s new fibre optic and broadband offerings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><strong><em><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paul-britnell-200a3633/?originalSubdomain=uk\">Paul Britnell, co-founder of Altnets,</a></em></strong></span><strong><em> has stated:</em></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>&ldquo;We are extremely proud to be backing CommScope\'s vision to build a stronger UK telecoms sector. Our fibre connectivity solutions enable fast, scalable FTTX networks, and this transaction reaffirms our mission to enhance the digital infrastructure of the UK.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Facilitating National Connectivity Objectives</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Under the UK Government\'s Project Gigabit, ISPs are competing to bring high-speed broadband to every corner of the country. This UK Fibre Network Partnership is meant to assist in speeding that work along, facilitating quicker rollout of scalable networks. Altnets will assist CommScope as well with technology marketing activity and attendance at key industry events&mdash;informing ISPs and network operators about the advantages of migrating to next-generation broadband infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Advanced Fibre Solutions for Central Offices CommScope provides highly sophisticated solutions for central offices, GPON, XGS-PON, and high-density fibre. These assist providers in addressing the growing demand for very high-speed internet, 5G backhaul, and wireless configurations. Through Altnets\' logistical and industry expertise, these technologies will be readily available to providers across the UK.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><em>Ronald van der Kraan, VP Broadband &ndash; EMEA at CommScope, stated:</em></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"We are pleased to partner with Altnets. They have an established track record and good reputation in full-fibre products and so are a very good partner to have. Together, we wish to enhance the UK\'s digital infrastructure and assist communities in better connecting.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Enabling Scalable Fibre Networks</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The alliance will enable network operators to own their fibre management systems and Optical Distribution Frames (ODFs) in their entirety. They are critical for developing central office capabilities. It is extremely significant since data usage continues to rise at a highly rapid pace within homes and businesses.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Empowering the Future of UK Connections </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By embracing CommScope\'s initiative for innovation and product superiority and marrying it to Altnets\' nationwide reach in the UK, this UK Fibre Network Partnership is a revolutionary move for the UK telecom industry.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It\'s not just an answer to the current connectivity demand but also sets the groundwork for economic and technological expansion going forward. As digital transformation rolls across industries, alliances such as these will be vital to making the UK competitive, connected, and prepared for what\'s next in the broadband revolution.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-11', '17:46:46', 'uk-fibre-network-partnership-altnets-and-commscope-lead-rollout', 'article/visionaries-network-uk-fibre-network-partnership.webp', 'UK Fibre Rollout Led by Altnets &amp; CommScope', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-uk-fibre-network-partnership.webp', 4, 2025, 'UK fibre, Altnets, CommScope, broadband, network, internet, visionaries network, rollout, telecom, connectivity, FTTP, digital UK, fiber optic, ISP, partnership', 'Altnets and CommScope partner to accelerate the UK fibre network rollout, enhancing broadband access and digital connectivity nationwide.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(109, NULL, 'MTN Drives Smart City Future in South Africa with IoT', 'MTN Powers the Future of Smart City South Africa with IoT Tech', 'iot-and-robotics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.mtn.com/\">MTN</a></span> is no longer merely a mobile network operator &ndash; it is now a major contributor to the Internet of Things (IoT) development in South Africa. With close to 6 million telemetry subscribers, MTN plays a critical role in developing smart technology solutions far beyond mere mobile services.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MTN began its <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../magazine/profile/overdrive-iot-is-a-real-time-asset-management-iot-company\">Internet of Things (IoT)</a></span> journey using Machine-to-Machine (M2M) technology and now boasts a robust and agile platform for smart solutions. The bedrock of this growth is the MTN Connected Things (MCT) CMP platform, which has been developed in collaboration with Eseye. The MCT CMP platform supports critical smart city South Africa and is market-ready, with a formal launch set for the second quarter of 2025.<br><br><strong>Leading the Innovation of Smart City</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The MCT CMP platform provides a strong foundation for the deployment of sophisticated smart systems across South Africa. Backed by a strong partner ecosystem, MTN integrates across every level of the IoT technology stack &mdash; hardware, sensors, software, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/smart-learning-and-data-analytics\">data analytics</a></span>, and security &mdash; enabling it to provide full-scale, vertically integrated industry solutions.<br><br>\"Through collaborations with top industry brands, MTN is developing end-to-end IoT solutions that address real-world challenges,\" <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sudipto-moitra-88990a103/?originalSubdomain=za\">said MTN executive Moitra</a></span>. \"We are well-positioned to deliver solutions that address the growing needs of Smart City South Africa development.\"<br><br><strong>Smart Logistics and Intelligent Fleet</strong><br><br>One of the major IoT services offered by MTN is the MTN Connected Fleet (MCF) solution, which is at the application level. MCF gives organizations AI-based insights on vehicle operation, driver behavior, asset tracking, and routing planning. The solution is already serving customers in the public and private sectors.<br><br>&ldquo;Our customers are experiencing dramatic gains in fleet efficiency and productivity. We\'re pleased to provide a solution that provides real, quantifiable value,\" Moitra said.<br><br><strong>Government Partnerships and Intelligent Utilities<br></strong><br>MTN\'s dedication to innovation has positioned it as a strategic partner for government-initiated smart projects. Grateful to the RT-29 transversal contract from the National Treasury, MTN engages directly with municipalities to provide smart water and electricity metering services.<br><br>These initiatives are all building blocks towards the overall aim of the Smart City South Africa vision. This vision is to use data to improve services and infrastructure for all. MTN has a great track record and cutting-edge technology, and therefore, it is a suitable partner for government initiatives that are innovative. &ldquo;We\'re thrilled to help build smarter, more connected cities in South Africa,\" said Moitra. \"We want to continue to help enable digital transformation at all levels &mdash; from hometown towns to national headquarters.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-11', '00:52:15', 'mtn-powers-the-future-of-smart-city-south-africa-with-iot-tech', 'article/visionaries-nework-mtn-powers-the-future-smart-city.webp', 'MTN Powers the Future of Smart City South Africa with IoT Tech', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-nework-mtn-powers-the-future-smart-city.webp', 4, 2025, 'MTN, smart city, South Africa, IoT, technology, innovation, 5G, connectivity, urban development, digital,visionaries network, smart tech, future cities, telecom, network', 'MTN leads smart city innovation in South Africa, using IoT tech to boost connectivity, efficiency, and digital infrastructure.', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0);
