(112, NULL, 'AI Hair Care Tailored for Black Women', 'AI hair care for Black women is getting personal with technology', 'women in leadership', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In an industry that has long overlooked the specific needs of Black women,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.myavana.com/pages/the-company\">Candace Mitchell Harris</a></span> is rewriting the rules&mdash;using <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/agibot-humanoid-robot-founder-peng-zhihui-meets-premier-li-qiang\">artificial intelligence</a></span>, molecular science, and cultural awareness. As the founder and CEO of Myavana, a beauty tech company based in Atlanta, she has built a powerful platform that provides AI hair care for Black women, tailored to each user&rsquo;s unique texture, health, and lifestyle.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">And now, with national media coverage like MSN\'s <em>&ldquo;Myavana&rsquo;s Mission to Map the DNA of Beauty and Identity&rdquo;</em>, the world is beginning to understand just how big her vision truly is.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>From Coding to Curls: The Birth of Myavana</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">A computer science graduate from Georgia Tech, Candace Mitchell Harris was already a rising star in tech when she realized the beauty industry wasn&rsquo;t designed for her hair&mdash;or for the millions of women who shared her experience. Frustrated by the endless trial-and-error of buying hair products, she decided to take a scientific approach.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;I examined my hair under a microscope,&rdquo; she recalled in interviews. &ldquo;I realized no one was applying science to our hair, and that&rsquo;s when the idea for Myavana was born.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Founded in 2012, Myavana&mdash;a blend of &ldquo;my hair&rdquo; and &ldquo;nirvana&rdquo;&mdash;uses AI and hair strand analysis to provide custom hair care recommendations. With over a decade of R&amp;D and customer feedback, it&rsquo;s become a trusted platform for textured hair solutions that are accurate, culturally aware, and grounded in data.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>HairAI&trade;: Personalized Beauty Powered by Science</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At the heart of Myavana is its proprietary technology, HairAI&trade;, which uses machine learning to assess hair texture, type, density, and health from a single photo or strand. Users either upload images of their hair or send in samples using a Hair Analysis Kit. The result? A scientifically backed, fully customized regimen for hair care&mdash;including product recommendations and style suggestions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This AI-driven model doesn&rsquo;t just serve individuals. Myavana also supports salons and stylists, helping professionals better understand the science of hair and provide elevated services to their clients.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Mapping the DNA of Identity</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/technology/myavanas-mission-to-map-the-dna-of-beauty-and-identity/ar-AA1Cw2FA?ocid=BingNewsVerp\"> recent feature by MSN</a></span>, Mitchell Harris shared her deeper mission: to map the DNA of beauty and identity. Her work is more than just innovation&mdash;it&rsquo;s cultural restoration.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;For far too long, textured hair was misunderstood, misrepresented, or simply ignored in science and commerce,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re not just recommending products&mdash;we&rsquo;re validating beauty, celebrating identity, and giving women the power to understand themselves through the lens of science.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The article highlights how Myavana is not just revolutionizing beauty but empowering women through technology that affirms their individuality and cultural legacy. In doing so, Harris is redefining what beauty tech can&mdash;and should&mdash;look like.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Filling a Market Gap with AI Hair Care for Black Women</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although Black women spend nine times more on hair products than other demographics, the market has historically failed to meet their needs with science-based solutions. That&rsquo;s why AI hair care for Black women stands out as such a vital innovation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Myavana fills this gap by using culturally competent, data-driven analysis. From hair density and porosity to strand strength and environmental damage, Myavana&rsquo;s system considers over 20 variables. Users no longer need to guess which products might work&mdash;they now have access to personalized insights backed by real science.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>From Startup to $50 Million Valuation</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Myavana has attracted major investments from Amazon, Ulta Beauty&rsquo;s Prisma Ventures, and H/L Ventures, raising nearly $6 million in funding. Today, the company is valued at over $50 million and continues to grow through its app, Pro Hair Labs for stylists, and enterprise solutions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Candace Mitchell Harris has also received national honors, including Forbes 30 Under 30, the BET Honors STEM Award, and recognition by WWD as one of the Top 50 Beauty Innovators.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Bridging Technology and Culture</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Located in Atlanta&mdash;a historic hub for Black entrepreneurship&mdash;Myavana is continuing the legacy of icons like Madam C.J. Walker. But as the MSN article noted, Candace is blending heritage with hardware, creating a beauty brand that is just as scientific as it is soulful.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The company&rsquo;s headquarters even sit just blocks from where Walker herself once ran her hair empire.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Looking Ahead: The Future of AI Hair Care for Black Women</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Looking ahead, Mitchell Harris envisions a future where Myavana becomes a global standard. Plans are in motion to install hair analysis kiosks in salons and beauty retailers across the U.S. and abroad, including Africa and the Caribbean.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">She also hopes to partner with hair care brands to design new products based on real consumer hair data, leading to formulations tailored not just by type but by individual hair profiles.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By using artificial intelligence to elevate beauty routines and build deeper cultural confidence, AI hair care for Black women is set to become more than just a trend&mdash;it&rsquo;s poised to become the new industry norm.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Candace Mitchell Harris isn&rsquo;t just the Founder of a fast-growing beauty tech company. She&rsquo;s a visionary shaping the future of inclusive innovation. With Myavana, she&rsquo;s giving Black women access to science, self-discovery, and smart, confident hair care&mdash;on their terms.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">And for millions of women who&rsquo;ve long felt left out of the beauty conversation, that&rsquo;s more than innovation&mdash;it&rsquo;s empowerment.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-11', '22:52:37', 'ai-hair-care-for-black-women-is-getting-personal-with-technology', 'article/visionaries-network-ai-hair-care-for-black-women1.webp', 'AI hair care for Black women is getting personal with technology', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-ai-hair-care-for-black-women1.webp', 4, 2025, 'AI hair care, Black women, personalized beauty, textured hair, natural hair, tech in beauty, hair technology, Black hair AI, smart hair tools, beauty innovation, curly hair, AI products, ethnic hair, AI beauty trends, visionaries network', 'Discover how AI is revolutionizing hair care for Black women with personalized solutions for natural and textured hair needs.', 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(113, '', 'Airwallex Singapore Powers SME Growth in 2024', 'Airwallex Singapore&rsquo;s Growth in 2024 Fuels SME Digital Expansion', 'Beyond-Silicon-Valley', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.airwallex.com/\">Airwallex</a></span>, a leading global financial technology platform, has announced record performance in Singapore for fiscal year 2024. It is a significant milestone in its expansion in the region and worldwide. With a 153% revenue growth year on year and a significant rise in transaction volumes, Airwallex Singapore&rsquo;s growth in 2024 indicates that small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in Southeast Asia desire additional digital financial solutions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The firm\'s robust Q4 performance was the main driver of its success, and revenues surged 215% YoY while transaction volume grew 192%. In the full fiscal year, Singapore\'s transaction volume grew 159%, a testament to the city-state\'s strategic value as a fintech hub and digital innovation leader.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2024 was a new era of expansion for us in Singapore and regionally,\" said <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/awxlucy/\">Lucy Liu, Airwallex President and Co-founder</a></span>. \"Our results show the strength of delivering businesses access to next-generation infrastructure that unlocks cross-border potential.\".</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Singapore as Hub of Choice</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Airwallex chose Singapore as its primary headquarters, which has greatly contributed to its rapid expansion. In 2024, locally, the business employed 58% more personnel, with over 250 people in corporate, commercial, and product development staff. The PED team expanded broadly, with an increase of new hires by 98%, while the business reinforced its AI, data, and engineering capabilities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To support this expansion, Airwallex expanded its office footprint in Guoco Tower, a reflection of its long-term strategy of leading innovation in Singapore and beyond.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SMEs are responsible for growth</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Among the most important reasons for Airwallex Singapore\'s growth in 2024 has been its focus on helping SMEs scale and digitalize. Airwallex has partnered with an expanding list of <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../magazine/innovation-excellence-awards-2023-sent\">innovative brands</a></span> like Endowus, Love, Bonito, and Mighty Jaxx, while continuing to maintain relationships with long-standing partners like EU Holidays, Far East Flora, and Huber\'s Butchery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Airwallex realized the issues that small and medium-sized businesses in Singapore are facing, so they sent a survey to 250 Singaporean small and medium-sized business leaders. They found common challenges such as increased costs, inadequate skilled workers, and cash flow issues, yet also revealed a strong appetite to grow despite them.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Key Survey Discoveries:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&bull; 62% of SMEs mention increasing the cost of operations as a key issue</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&bull; 48% attribute difficulties in managing global and local cash flow</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&bull; 43% are impacted by inflation</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&bull; 40% struggle with regulatory complexity</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&bull; 46% view too few workers as a challenge to growth</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In spite of all these challenges, SMEs remain optimistic. 76% intend to raise business expenditure in 2024, with 33% investing huge amounts in expansion. Expansion is still the top priority, with 40% of the survey respondents looking towards Southeast Asia, 37% towards East Asia, and 30% towards Central Asia.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Digital finance is expanding rapidly</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The survey further pointed to an overwhelming shift to FinTech and digital platforms. Nearly 96% of the SMEs that were polled already have or plan to adopt digital finance platforms in order to streamline their operations. These platforms process transactions more efficiently, cost less, are more transparent, and offer more features than banking systems.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Surprisingly, 91% of people surveyed reported that they trust online financial platforms such as Airwallex to handle their finances&mdash;a striking reversal in sentiment that reflects the growing influence of online financial resources.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"SMEs power Singapore\'s economy, constituting 99% of businesses and almost half of the GDP,\" Airwallex\'s Southeast Asia Head, Ershad Ahamed, clarified. \"Our research indicates that SMEs want to scale but are held back by very real constraints. We want to give them scalable, intuitive tools that make their finances easy.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Growing Overseas but Contributing Locally</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beyond Singapore, Airwallex is accelerating its global expansion. In January 2025, the business launched its New Zealand operations and acquired CTIN Pay, a licensed intermediary payment service provider in Vietnam. They are just some of a broader push to expand its Asia-Pacific footprint and help businesses navigate global markets.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Airwallex\'s numbers do the talking: the business now makes more than US$600 million in revenue every year and processes over US$130 billion in annualised transaction value. Its work has not fallen on deaf ears&mdash;Airwallex has just been named one of Fast Company\'s 2025 World\'s Most Innovative Companies, hailed for its reinvention of cross-border financial innovation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Looking Ahead</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As digital transformation accelerates in the majority of industries, Airwallex Singapore&rsquo;s growth in 2024 emerges as a pioneer in new financial services. As more small and medium enterprises adopt digital models and expand into new markets, Airwallex is speeding up investment in AI, data, and user experience to deliver new solutions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By combining local knowledge with global reach, Airwallex continues to close financial gaps for rapidly growing businesses. Its platform not only streamlines cumbersome cross-border payments but also enables businesses to move with more agility, transparency, and confidence.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Airwallex Singapore\'s growth in 2024 is not a story of numbers and headcount&mdash;it\'s a story of shifting business needs, evolving digital landscapes, and the business itself as a catalyst for empowering SMEs for the future. As Fintech gains ground and old systems lag behind, Airwallex is leading the charge into a new financial world, offering the tools modern companies need to thrive.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-04-11', '23:19:44', 'airwallex-singapores-growth-in-2024-fuels-sme-digital-expansion', 'article/visionaries-network-airwallex-singapore-growth-2024-1.webp', 'Airwallex Singapore&rsquo;s Growth in 2024 Fuels SME Digital Expansion', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-airwallex-singapore-growth-2024-1.webp', 4, 2025, 'Airwallex, Singapore, SME growth, digital expansion, fintech, 2024, startups, payments, visionaries network, transaction volume, business banking, revenue growth, workforce, global payments, digital tools', 'Airwallex&#039;s rapid growth in Singapore during 2024 is accelerating digital expansion and financial access for SMEs and startups across the region.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(114, NULL, 'How 6G Will Revolutionize Connectivity by 2025', 'How 6G Technology Will Transform Connectivity by 2025', 'Voice', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We are at the start of yet another gigantic technological shift. The focus is moving away from 5G and to 6G technology, which is of paramount importance today. By 2025, we will see the first clear signals of what 6G can do. If we get ready, this new network will transform the way we are connected, create, and flourish in the&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/westown-smart-city-south-africa-set-to-transform-kwazulu-natal\">digital realm</a></span>.<br><br>Let us be realistic: 6G is more than a wireless communications revolution. It is an evolutionary change in the way that we think of connectivity, innovation, and worldwide collaboration. It will make us rethink the function of networks within our world&mdash;not only as technologies but as the intangible force driving an intelligent, leaner, and more interconnected world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Beyond Speed: The True Power of 6G</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Yes, 6G networks will be extremely fast&mdash;extremely fast. We are discussing potential speeds of 1 terabit per second and very low latency. But only focusing on speed would be a mistake. The true power of 6G technology is its capability to perform things that today\'s networks cannot: real-time immersive experiences, holographic communication, self-driving systems, and machine-to-machine intelligence on a scale we have never experienced before.<br><br>With these abilities, 6G will not only improve our lives&mdash;it will revolutionize them. Picture smart cities that can function on their own, remote treatments that are indistinguishable from in-person care, and metaverse environments that allow for frictionless collaboration and shopping in fully immersive virtual worlds. These are not far-off dreams&mdash;they are on the horizon, and 6G upgrades will be the catalyst for making them a reality.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>The Future of Connectivity Must Be Inclusive&mdash;If Only We Act Now</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We can\'t repeat past mistakes in deploying networks. 5G was promising but widened the digital divide in most areas. With 6G, we can make it right. Everyone should have access to high-speed internet, anywhere, including rural and underserved areas. This needs to be a priority for 6G.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As we move towards 2025, we must insist that governments, technology leaders, and infrastructure providers put equitable access first. If next-generation networks are to make the world a better place, they need to reach every nook and cranny of it&mdash;not just the wealthiest or most populous.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Innovation Requires 6G</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Let\'s not overlook how important <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.techtarget.com/searchnetworking/definition/6G\">6G technology</a></span> will be for innovation. Digital twins, automation by AI, self-driving cars, and advanced robots are already testing the limits of what 5G can do. 6G will do away with those limits, providing creators and businesses with a space where their actions and thoughts are not limited by data speed and latency.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We need to see 2025 as a tipping point. Not because 6G will be entirely operational but because the beginning of its adoption and infrastructure building will start to put us on track for it. This is the point at which startups, developers, and businesses can begin to tinker with 6G applications that are greater than mere basic connections&mdash;moving towards completely new ways of generating value.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Privacy, Security, and Responsibility</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As we build these networks, we need to do it properly. 6G networks will generate and manage a vast amount of data. This raises serious issues regarding privacy, cybersecurity, and technology ethics. If we do not have proper rules, we may be building a system of spying in disguise as new technology.<br><br>Let\'s get real: we\'re more likely to create new technology than we are to argue about ethics and regulations. In 6G, we can\'t afford to let that occur. We require systems with security built in from the beginning, safeguarding user data at all levels and offering transparent AI integration. If 6G is to be the nervous system of our digital world, then trust must be its foundation.<br><br><strong>Why 2025 Matters</strong><br><br>Others will insist that it\'s too early to talk about 6G in 2025. But we at Visionaries Network don\'t agree. By the year 2025, prime nations such as South Korea, China, America, and Europe will be greatly engaged in researching, testing, and beginning the deployment of 6G. Those who will do best are those who are planning and executing now&mdash;not sitting and waiting.<br><br>As a world community, we must view 6G technology as something that we all own and are responsible for. It\'s not merely about developing the next big thing; it\'s about developing the digital world that we will all live in for many years to come.<br><strong><br>A Call to Action</strong><br><br>We are at a special point in time. The decisions we make in the next two years will decide if 6G helps humanity or harms it. Let\'s make educated decisions.<br><br>We need to invest in STEM education, support research on 6G, and facilitate inclusive infrastructure development. We need to create vision-driven, accountable public-private partnerships. And we need to make sure that 6G does more than connect devices&mdash;it needs to connect people, ideas, and opportunities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Final Thoughts </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The journey towards 6G technology is not without challenges. Yet, if we come together&mdash;across industries, governments, and societies&mdash;we can make the future about how connection drives us forward, rather than what tears us apart. Let us not wait for the future to come. Let us create it today.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-11', '23:14:25', 'how-6g-technology-will-transform-connectivity-by-2025', 'article/visionaries-network-6g-technology-connectivity.webp', 'How 6G Technology Will Transform Connectivity by 2025', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-6g-technology-connectivity.webp', 4, 2025, '6G technology, connectivity, 2025, future networks, ultra-fast internet, smart cities, IoT, AI, latency, wireless innovation, telecom, 6G applications, visionaries network, tech trends, mobile networks', 'Explore how 6G technology is set to transform global connectivity by 2025 with faster speeds, lower latency, and smarter networks.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
