(143, NULL, 'Aurobac Unveils Precision AMR Solution | 2025', 'Franco-German Aurobac Therapeutics AMR solution Unveiled', 'biotechnology and pharmaceuticals', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Franco-German partnership&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://aurobac-tx.com/\">Aurobac Therapeutics</a></span> is formed to offer a long-sought solution to combat antimicrobial resistance. The Aurobac Therapeutics AMR solution will provide state-of-the-art diagnostics and precision treatments to eliminate lethal superbugs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Formed by German pharma giants <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.boehringer-ingelheim.com/\">Boehringer Ingelheim</a></span> and <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.evotec.com/\">Evotec</a></span> and French diagnostics giant <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.biomerieux.com/corp/en.html\">bioM&eacute;rieux</a></span>, the new firm will concentrate on the creation of fast, effective treatments based on high-level pathogen detection.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The French Lyon-based firm is the future of infection control based on intelligent science rather than the conventional trial-and-error therapy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Pooling Strengths to Counteract Superbugs</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Every founding business is key in driving this record-breaking partnership:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong>Evotec</strong> provides innovative research capacity, with a 200-person team focused on antimicrobial discovery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong>Boehringer Ingelheim</strong>, the venture sponsor, is providing &euro;30 million and has extensive experience in drug development and clinical trials.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong>bioM&eacute;rieux</strong>, donating &euro;5 million, is a leader in diagnostic innovation, with three-quarters of its R&amp;D spend going into AMR.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This synergy enables Aurobac to do more than simply produce yet another antibiotic. Rather, the Aurobac Therapeutics AMR solution is engineered to provide an end-to-end pipeline&mdash;from real-time diagnosis to precision therapies&mdash;tailored to the individual resistance profile of each infection.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>The Urgent Need for Action</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Antimicrobial-resistant infections now kill more than one million people each year, the World Health Organization states. That number would increase to 10 million each year by 2050, becoming the world\'s leading cause of death, even overtaking cancer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Infections that were previously easily treatable can become fatal, ushering in a dreaded post-antibiotic era. The rise of multidrug-resistant (MDR) microbes threatens to topple modern medicine, affecting surgery, chemotherapy, and even childbirth.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As Michel Pairet of Boehringer warns, AMR is \"potentially deadlier than cancer.\" Never has the call for a solution been more urgent&mdash;and that\'s why the Aurobac Therapeutics AMR solution is so vital.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why Antibiotic Innovation Needs a New Model</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Though there is a demand for novel antibiotics, there is no incentive to produce them. All new medicines are held back to be used in a crisis, so profitability and sales are low. This has led to a massive exodus of companies from antimicrobial R&amp;D.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To counter this model, the industry has introduced cooperative funding models:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->The AMR Action Fund, a funder of pioneering biotechs like Venatorx <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/alembic-pharmaceuticals-wins-usfda-approval-for-pantoprazole-injection\">Pharmaceuticals.</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->The UK\'s Netflix model subscription system, where one pays a set annual fee for access to antibiotics irrespective of use.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">These technologies aim to make antibiotic discovery more viable, and Aurobac\'s entry shows that the big pharma is once again ready to join in.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Aurobac Precision Medicine Vision</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In contrast to conventional methods, Aurobac Therapeutics is based on targeted antimicrobial therapy. The focus is not to manufacture antibiotics in bulk but highly targeted drugs, used judiciously, informed by quick diagnostic tests.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This enables patients to get the right treatment at the right time, minimizing resistance and maximizing outcomes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Final Thoughts: Aurobac Therapeutics AMR Solution Holds the Key</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Aurobac Therapeutics is not a collaboration&mdash;it\'s a new standard for saving lives in the era of rising resistance. With the coming together of diagnostics, drug discovery, and global collaborations, Aurobac Therapeutics\' solution to AMR can be the benchmark for combating infectious diseases tomorrow.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Watch out for Aurobac&mdash;it may just shift the paradigm.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-23', '01:18:16', 'franco-german-aurobac-therapeutics-amr-solution-unveiled', 'article/visionaries-network-franco-german-aurobac-therapeutics-amr-solution-unveiled.webp', 'Franco-German Aurobac Therapeutics AMR solution Unveiled', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-franco-german-aurobac-therapeutics-amr-solution-unveiled.webp', 4, 2025, 'Aurobac, visionaries network, antimicrobial resistance, precision medicine, Boehringer Ingelheim, Evotec, bioM&eacute;rieux, sepsis, diagnostics, bacterial infections, HABP, VABP, joint venture, healthcare innovation, antibiotic resistance', 'Franco-German Aurobac Therapeutics unveils a precision AMR solution, combining diagnostics and targeted therapies to combat severe bacterial infections in hospitals.', 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(144, '', 'GenAI Research Slows Amid Industry Disputes', 'GenAI Research Delayed Over Industry Battle Slows Progress', 'Voice', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As generative AI moves from research technology to a powerful commercial force, one unsettling reality has become the hallmark of the landscape: GenAI research is delayed because of industry rivalry. What was once an open, robust research ecosystem is now fragmenting into rival factions, each holding its intellectual property close. The implications of this shift aren\'t academic&mdash;they\'re global, and they affect everything from small startups to nations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Generative AI (GenAI) was built on the basis of transparency. The most capable models and best approaches were, at some point or another, freely shared with researchers in academia, nonprofits, and industry. Openness fueled innovation, and the area improved rapidly in language generation, image generation, and deep architectures. But in a matter of only a few years, things have changed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Secrecy now reigns in the field. Organizations like <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://openai.com/\">OpenAI</a></span>, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://deepmind.google/\">Google DeepMind</a></span>, Meta, and Anthropic are more concerned today with guarding their datasets and algorithms. Walled APIs, restricted licensing, proprietary models, and vague or non-existent research papers are the norm. Collaboration has been replaced by competition, and the prospect of losing a market advantage has led one-time collaborative organizations to shut down.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This dynamic is central to the problem&mdash;GenAI Research Delayed Over Industry Battle. It\'s not a short-term pause or a modest deceleration. It\'s a paradigm shift in how <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/ai-hair-care-for-black-women-is-getting-personal-with-technology\">AI</a></span> progress is created and disseminated. And this one, if left uncorrected, could extinguish the field\'s potential for years to come.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The rationale for such a retreat from transparency is reasonable from a business point of view. Big generative models are expensive to train. They require big datasets, compute, and engineering talent&mdash;expenses that all too easily sum to hundreds of millions. Companies in a tech-competitive economy are treating their models as trade secrets. The business logic for doing so: the less you know, the more the product must appear to be worth.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But while this might safeguard short-term profits, it damages the long-term well-being of the whole field. Innovation is seldom a solo endeavor. It depends on standing on the shoulders of giants, swapping techniques, comparing outcomes, and honing ideas together. When these activities are disrupted, the rate of discovery grinds to a halt.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Worse still, this research bottleneck renders the playing field unequal. Individual research groups, universities, and sole developers simply don\'t have any avenue to acquire the tools or the talent to compete equally with the walled gardens of Big Tech. And the more complex and resource-hungry models become, the wider the \"AI haves\" vs \"AI have-nots\" divide.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The public, too, has much to lose in this bargain. GenAI has incredible potential to benefit society, whether it is initiating customized learning, simulating public health impacts, or streamlining complex scientific research. But some of these socially useful uses are not short-term profit-generating, and thus are not available to corporate aspiration.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If a few firms control the course of GenAI, countless humanitarian and academic projects will remain unexplored. This moment demands reconsideration.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are ways forward. Public investment in open AI infrastructure can level the playing field. Grants to help academic labs acquire access to high-powered computing and large datasets can help them get back into the conversation. Open-source initiatives, like those of Hugging Face, EleutherAI, and Stability AI, must be backed by grants and incentives. These groups have shown that community-driven development can produce state-of-the-art models without the secrecy and exclusivity of corporate research labs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition, governments should ensure that foundational AI capabilities become a public good. Transparency mandates on foundation models, particularly on those affecting public services or security, may be much-needed control. The moment is now to think about whether the development of such powerful tools should actually only be in the private sector.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It\'s time, too, for the sector itself to rethink. There is space for competitive victory and commercial victory without severing the lifelines of collective advancement. Technology firms can look to hybrid models&mdash;where research is made available early stage, and monetization is downstream. The model already exists in sectors such as pharmaceuticals and aerospace, where competition and cooperation exist within a balanced system.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the end, the future of GenAI will be determined by the choices we make today. If the current leaders in the field continue to look at research as a battlefield instead of a shared cause, the delays will continue to pile up. And as much as some may triumph in the short term, society as a whole will suffer in the long term.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Innovation happens when ideas are allowed to flow freely, compete with one another, and change. That culture needs to be regained. GenAI Research Delayed Over Industry Battle is not a tech bug&mdash;it\'s a warning. It\'s a matter of whether we will hear it before it\'s too late.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-04-24', '10:59:33', 'genai-research-delayed-over-industry-battle-slows-progress', 'article/visionaries-network-gen-ai.webp', 'GenAI Research Delayed Over Industry Battle Slows Progress', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-gen-ai.webp', 4, 2025, 'GenAI, generative AI, AI research, industry conflict, AI development, research delays, tech disputes, innovation slowdown, AI companies, AI ethics, artificial intelligence, visionaries network, tech news, AI progress, AI collaboration', 'Progress in generative AI research is slowing as industry battles over direction, ethics, and control create major delays and tensions.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(145, '', 'OmniOn Launches 12V High Power Rectifier', 'OmniOn Launches High Power 12V Rectifier for Data Centers', 'iot-and-robotics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/ai-startup-investments-in-india-2025-break-records\">AI</a></span> workloads surge and <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/mtn-powers-the-future-of-smart-city-south-africa-with-iot-tech\">IoT</a></span> networks expand, modern data centers face a growing challenge: how to meet skyrocketing energy demands without compromising space, efficiency, or reliability. One such company to the rescue is <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.omnionpower.com/\">OmniOn Power</a></span>, which has just unveiled its new HPR-series power supplies &mdash; a powerful response to this next-gen infrastructure need.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Leading the charge are the HPR2812TEX12 and HPR2812DCX12, two advanced power supplies that deliver up to 2.8kW of highly efficient output in one of the most compact footprints available. These models are built specifically for 12V distributed architecture systems, the gold standard in high-performance computing environments.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For those looking for the ultimate high power 12V rectifier for data centers, this launch marks a serious upgrade path.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Next-Level Performance in a Compact Package</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The HPR2812TEX12 is a high-efficiency AC/DC rectifier with a 90-264V AC input and 12.3VDC output, boasting 80 PLUS&reg; Titanium efficiency levels above 96%. Meanwhile, the HPR2812DCX12 is a DC/DC converter supporting 36-72VDC input, also outputting 12.3V with a power density of 69W/in&sup3; and an efficiency exceeding 94%.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Together, they offer unprecedented flexibility and performance for data centers that need to scale without expanding rack space. Measuring just 1.57&rdquo; in height, 7.68&rdquo; deep, and 3.39&rdquo; wide, both units are compact enough to integrate easily into existing systems &mdash; making this duo a clear choice for engineers upgrading infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">And with mean time between failures (MTBF) greater than 1.5 million hours at 40&deg;C, these power supplies bring enterprise-grade reliability where it&rsquo;s needed most.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>One Series, Many Applications</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Engineered for compatibility, the HPR-series rectifier and converter are output, size, and connector compatible, giving data center architects maximum design flexibility. The two models support back-to-front airflow, critical for optimal thermal management in dense server environments, and come equipped with advanced overvoltage and overcurrent protection, plus PMBus&reg; communication for smart monitoring and control.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">These features make them ideal for everything from cloud computing infrastructure and optical line terminals to disaggregated memory banks, aggregation routers, and AI-ready server farms.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">And if you\'re searching for a scalable, efficient solution that can meet rising energy needs, OmniOn&rsquo;s latest offering may just be the best high-power 12V rectifier for data centers currently available.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Powering the Future of Cloud and AI</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">What sets OmniOn&rsquo;s new HPR-series apart isn&rsquo;t just power &mdash; it&rsquo;s the total package. These rectifiers and converters bring together cutting-edge power density, superior thermal performance, and exceptional longevity. For IT leaders and system designers navigating the power-hungry terrain of AI training clusters, data lakes, and edge computing &mdash; these tools are built for the job.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The HPR-series offers a smooth upgrade path from lower-output or legacy power systems, helping organizations prepare for more intensive workloads and complex computing tasks. It&rsquo;s future-proofing &mdash; but made practical.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With efficiency, power, and smart design all in one, the HPR2812TEX12 and HPR2812DCX12 models are positioned to become the go-to choice for anyone needing a high-power 12V rectifier for data centers &mdash; and fast.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Teamvisiona', '2025-04-24', '11:14:41', 'omnion-launches-high-power-12v-rectifier-for-data-centers', 'article/visionaries-network-omni-launches-high-power-data-center.webp', 'OmniOn Launches High Power 12V Rectifier for Data Centers', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-omni-launches-high-power-data-center.webp', 4, 2025, 'OmniOn, 12V rectifier, data center power, high power, power solutions, energy efficiency, rectifier technology, data center infrastructure, visionaries network, tech hardware, electrical systems, energy tech, power management, critical infrastructure, IT power', 'OmniOn introduces a high-power 12V rectifier designed for data centers, enhancing energy efficiency and supporting advanced power infrastructure needs.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(146, '', 'CBG Energy Hits $1B with NexGen India Deal', 'CBG Energy Investment in India Hits $1B with NexGen-Capital Deal', 'Environment Power and Clean Energy', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a first-of-its-kind for India\'s&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/pure-unveils-purepower-a-game-changer-in-indias-renewable-energy-landscape\">renewable energy</a></span> sector, Noida-based clean energy leader <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://nexgenenergia.com/\">NexGen Energia</a></span> Ltd has concluded a record $1 billion CBG energy investment in India from Kuwait-based investment holding company Capital Edge. The equity investment will drive Compressed Bio-Gas (CBG) infrastructure development in India to enable India\'s journey towards energy self-sufficiency and sustainability.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This investment is a milestone for NexGen Energia, one of India\'s leading developers of CBG plants. It also indicates growing global confidence in India\'s <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../magazine/profile/palmetto-makes-it-affordable-for-homeowners\">clean energy</a></span> potential and makes the nation a global capital center for climate-led capital.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Green Fuel Taking the Lead</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">NexGen Energia has been at the forefront of building CBG plants that utilize organic and farm waste to generate clean, high-calorie fuel for decades. With the backing of Capital Edge, the company is now poised to grow its operations nationally more aggressively than ever.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;This capital infusion is a landmark in our journey,\" said NexGen Energia Director of Sales Nishant Tiwari. \"It will fuel our vision of a cleaner India through the large-scale production of CBG. We\'re thrilled at the environmental and social contribution this will make across the nation.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">NexGen Energia aims to install 1,000 Compressed Bio-Gas units by 2026, which will not only be India\'s green fuel economy driver but will also generate mass employment as well as catalyze sustainable development for rural India.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why CBG Energy Investment in India Is a Game Changer</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The growing interest in CBG energy investment in India is due to its growing popularity in contributing to climate goals as well as providing energy resilience. CBG, a pure biogas, has a chemical similarity to natural gas and is increasingly being utilized as a clean-burning fuel for automobiles.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">India generates a vast quantity of agricultural waste annually, much of which is untapped. Using this biomass, the cultivation of CBG solves a variety of problems&mdash;disposal of waste, energy diversification, and rural revenues.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;Every CBG plant is a local driver of change&mdash;creating jobs, empowering farmers, and reducing harm to the environment,\" <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/k-ch-se-panda-1172a5199/\">NexGen Energia CEO Kishor Panda</a></span> said. \"With this support, we can move increasingly quickly towards developing a circular, sustainable energy economy.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This is in addition to the Indian government\'s SATAT initiative that promotes the development of 5,000 CBG plants by 2030. NexGen Energia\'s commitment of 1,000 plants is a giant leap towards the realization of this goal.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Strategic Alliance for Sustainable Development</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Capital Edge, the Kuwaiti investor, has an unblemished record of supporting innovative projects in Asia and the Middle East. With long-term structured equity financing experience, they offer the very investment model that NexGen Energia needs to enter scale without sacrificing sustainability.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Capital Edge representative explained, \"This is not an investment for cash, it\'s for strategy. We\'re investing in a company that can transform how India generates energy&mdash;and that\'s squarely in our mission as impact investors.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The CBG energy investment in India will not only fuel the production of clean fuel but also generate an estimated 50,000 jobs directly and indirectly. From the establishment of the supply chains to the running of the plants, the multiplier effects will be enormous.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Looking Ahead</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">First installations of the plants have already started in states with high potential, such as Maharashtra, Uttar Pradesh, and Karnataka. NexGen Energia targets to obtain several dozen installations over the next 18&ndash;24 months and complete the rollout by 2026.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With India\'s development in the direction of clean energy, strategic alliances like this between NexGen Energia and Capital Edge will become indispensable. They symbolize the fusion of capital assets, global vision, and joint accountability toward the earth. With this $1 billion India CBG energy investment, the stage is set for a revolutionary new era&mdash;a new era where innovation, sustainability, and economic opportunity come together to shape the future of energy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'Ethan Walker', '2025-04-24', '22:25:15', 'cbg-energy-hits-1b-with-nexgen-india-deal', 'article/visionaries-network-cbg-energy-investment-in-india.webp', 'CBG Energy Investment in India Hits $1B with NexGen-Capital Deal', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-cbg-energy-investment-in-india.webp', 4, 2025, 'CBG Energy, NexGen Capital, India investment, energy deal, renewable energy, clean tech, $1B deal, green energy, infrastructure, sustainability, energy finance, power sector, investment news, visionaries network, Indian market', 'CBG Energy&rsquo;s investment in India surpasses $1B through a major deal with NexGen Capital, boosting clean energy and infrastructure growth.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(147, '', 'Sky Medical Joins BMC | Medical Devices Manufacturer News', 'Medical Devices Manufacturer Sky Medical Joins BMC', 'healthcare and medical devices', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the first for India\'s neuro and orthopaedic rehabilitation, UK&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/nvidia-and-ge-healthcare-partner-advance-intelligent-automation-medical-imaging\">medical devices</a></span> manufacturer <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.skymedtech.com/\">Sky Medical Technology</a></span> &mdash; parent to Firstkind &mdash; has announced that the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) Hospital has added its game-changing geko&trade; device to standard physiotherapy treatment protocols. This achievement positions Sky Medical Technology as a global leader, extending its reach way beyond Western healthcare systems.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>BMC Hospital Launches geko Device: Rollout for Stroke and Orthopaedic Rehabilitation</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://bmchospital.in/\">BMC Hospital</a></span>, India\'s largest public network of health care facilities, initiated the use of the <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/firstkind-limited/\">geko device</a></span> in all its physiotherapy programs to assist stroke and orthopedic surgery patients. The device has also been effective in the prevention of deep vein thrombosis (DVT) in medically ill and bedridden patients &mdash; an ideal target in acute care and long-term hospitalization settings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>How the Geko Device Works: A Revolutionary Wearable Rehabilitation</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The geko device, one of the products of this new medical devices manufacturer, is a wearable, self-adhesive, and light neuromuscular electro-stimulator. It is worn just below the knee and delivers mild electric pulses to the common peroneal nerve. It mimics natural muscle movement in the foot and calf and enhances blood flow to levels similar to 60% of walking. It is life-saving for bedridden or otherwise immobile patients.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Quicker Recovery, Home Use, and Reduced Costs: A Triple Benefit for BMC</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Dr. Haridas Rathod, Chief Medical Officer, BMC, also praised the device\'s efficiency, saying, \"Fundamentally, at the heart of physiotherapy is the need to optimize a patient\'s functional capacity, to promote independence, and simply to add quality of life. The geko device does all three.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">He illustrated how the device facilitates therapy to start sooner after stroke and surgery, and also enables rehabilitation to continue in the home environment. \"Its simplicity allows patients to take charge and self-rehabilitate,\" he continued, adding also that it minimizes the demand for intensive one-to-one therapist intervention, which means cost savings for the BMC hospital group.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Indian distributor Curamatix celebrates a \"Milestone Moment\"</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Curamatix Healthcare, the Indian distributor of the geko device, called the integration a \"milestone moment.\" Directors <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ramen-mukherjee-10b8b440/\">Ramen Mukherjee</a></span> and <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/subhodeep-mukherjee-7a4887310/\">Subhodeep Mukherjee</a></span> said, \"The successful integration of the device into BMC Hospital\'s physiotherapy programmes is a major milestone that demonstrates the versatility and efficacy of the device in assisting stroke and orthopaedic rehabilitation.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sky Medical Technology\'s Global Expansion Finds Footing in Asia</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The product is not limited to cities in India. Curamatix is planning to distribute the product to other states in India, and it can potentially distribute the geko device to rural hospitals where post-operative care and physiotherapy are unavailable. Through the ability to have patients recover at home, the geko device can potentially bridge the gap in access to good care for millions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/bernard-ross-617b9610/\">Sky Medical Technology CEO and Founder Bernard Ross</a></span> had this to say as well: \"By complementing other treatments to perfection, the geko device not only minimizes recovery time, but also empowers patients to take control of their own rehabilitation.\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>India Becomes a Growth Market for Intelligent Medical Devices </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This further solidifies the increasing global reputation of Sky Medical Technology as a global medical devices manufacturer producing user-focused, cost-effective, and efficient solutions to difficult healthcare issues.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As hospitals across the globe continue to look for methods to deliver improved outcomes on limited budgets, technologies such as geko demonstrate a vision for a future in which intelligent, wearable technology drives human healing &mdash; and Sky Medical Technology is at the forefront.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As India becomes a hotbed of medical innovation adoption, such cooperation can perhaps be the precursor to an even larger movement: international cooperation between regional healthcare infrastructures and medical device manufacturer coming together to provide high-impact, scalable solutions. In the near term, however, Sky Medical Technology and the geko device are making a good first impression&mdash;one gentle pulse at a time.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-25', '11:57:58', 'medical-devices-manufacturer-sky-medical-joins-bmc', 'article/visionaries-netwrok-skymedical-technology-bmc-hospital.webp', 'Medical Devices Manufacturer Sky Medical Joins BMC', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-netwrok-skymedical-technology-bmc-hospital.webp', 4, 2025, 'Sky Medical, BMC, medical devices, healthcare technology, medical innovation, device manufacturer, merger news, medical equipment, health tech, medical partnerships, BMC collaboration, medical industry, visionaries network, patient care, medical solutions', 'Medical devices manufacturer Sky Medical has officially joined BMC, expanding innovation and collaboration in healthcare technology and patient care.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);
