(148, '', 'Why Superpower&rsquo;s Longevity App Is Booming in 2025', 'Why Superpower&rsquo;s Affordable Longevity App Is Booming', 'Startups', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At 24, Australian businessman&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/maxmarchione/\">Max Marchione</a></span> is Silicon Valley\'s latest tech and health phenomenon. His company, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://superpower.com/\">Superpower</a></span>, is already making waves for offering a future-oriented but affordable longevity app to health-conscious professionals who desire to live longer, healthier lives. The firm has been worth over $300 million in just two years and just closed a $47 million round.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Marchione, a Sydneysider, relocated to San Francisco to start Superpower with the intent to ride two big waves: the imploding U.S. <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/u-s--healthcare-system-is-failing-but-personalized-care-offers-hope\">healthcare</a></span> system and the growing demand for personalized, tech-enabled wellness solutions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">And it\'s working.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What Is Superpower?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Superpower is a yearly subscription longevity app that costs $499. In return, subscribers receive two yearly blood tests tested for dozens of biomarkers. According to the test results, the users receive personalized health recommendations&mdash;like supplements and preventive therapy&mdash;and fast access to healthcare providers via the app.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>\"Superpower is about delivering expert, preventive healthcare to more people,\"</em> Marchione said. <em>\"When I first tested my biological age, it was 35. After completing our own program, it\'s 20.4 now. I feel better, more energetic, and more focused than I ever have before.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">His transformation is not just an ad slogan&mdash;it is backed by data and an increasingly strong technology platform for real-time health monitoring and tailored wellness planning.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Celebrity and Venture Capital Support</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Investors are fully on board with this new affordable longevity app. Series A funding was provided by Forerunner Ventures, which have made it a known practice to invest in Oura rings, and also involved other top names such as Day One Ventures, Long Journey Ventures, and Winklevoss Capital. Celebrity names such as actress Vanessa Hudgens, DJ Steve Aoki, and Logan Paul are included in the list of investors as well.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kirstengreen/\">Forerunner co-founder Kirsten Green</a></span> is currently on the board of Superpower and believes the company has the potential to disrupt healthcare.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"There\'s a huge gap between what people do know about their bodies and what they might know,\" Green said. <em>\"Superpower bridges that gap.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The app currently boasts a 150,000-person waiting list and has been well-liked by Silicon Valley\'s biohacking set. Its business model features collectible trading cards that are tied to investors\' health data.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Marchione\'s journey began in Sydney, where he attended St Aloysius College, one of the city\'s elite schools. He started investing in technology at 17 and gave up a top-tier law degree to focus on his entrepreneurial ambitions on a full-time basis.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">After co-founding Superpower in 2023 with American co-founders <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/unkrich5/\">Kevin Unkrich</a></span> and Jacob Peters, the three took up residence in an apartment-office hybrid in San Francisco, separated by nothing more than a spiral staircase.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>&ldquo;There is no work-life balance&mdash;it\'s just life,\"</em> Marchione said. <em>\"And I feel privileged to be spending it doing something that does make a difference.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">His move was not an accident. <em>\"The healthcare shortage is larger in the U.S., people are typically less healthy, and the market is larger,\"</em> he said. <em>\"It\'s the perfect place to start a healthtech business.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Resolving a Personal Issue</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Marchione was inspired by his own ailments. He had chronic sinusitis, insomnia, and migraines during his teenage years&mdash;afflictions that were not diagnosed for years.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;I kept getting misdiagnosed again and again until I found what I call a \'10x doctor\'&mdash;a physician who listened to my symptoms in totality,\" he said. <em>\"That made me understand how much the system is broken and how valuable individualized health data is.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">That epiphany was the template for Superpower. Marchione wants to democratize the kind of luxury healthcare that\'s normally reserved for billionaires such as Jeff Bezos or Peter Thiel&mdash;both of whom have publicly invested in life-extension technology.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Constructing the Health of the Future</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The recently finished $47 million round will go towards expanding Superpower\'s engineering team, expanding its <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/how-to-start-data-analyst-career-a-simple-guide-for-beginners\">data analytics</a></span> platform further, and hiring more medical professionals. Superpower currently has 80 employees, one-third of whom are based in Australia.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While fears that Superpower will widen the healthcare gap exist, Marchione insists that affordability is at the mission\'s center. The affordable longevity app is already being made available to the workers of small businesses, and discussions with health insurers are underway to prolong coverage.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Co-founder Kevin Unkrich summarized it most aptly: <em>\"Living with your co-founders is extreme. But building a world-changing company takes extreme focus, discipline, and trust. We\'re not just counting steps&mdash;we\'re redefining health.\"</em><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-25', '23:31:54', 'why-superpowers-affordable-longevity-app-is-booming', 'article/visionaries-network-superpower-app.webp', 'Why Superpower&rsquo;s Longevity App Is Booming in 2025', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-superpower-app.webp', 4, 2025, 'Superpower app, longevity app, health tech, affordable wellness, anti-aging, wellness app, biohacking, health optimization, visionaries network, fitness tracking, personalized health, wellness trends, Superpower longevity, healthy aging, life extension', 'Discover why Superpower&rsquo;s affordable longevity app is booming&mdash;revolutionizing health, wellness, and anti-aging for a growing user base.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(149, NULL, 'Simplifyber Raises $12M for Bio-Based Fashion Innovation', 'Bio-Based Fashion Manufacturing Startup Simplifyber Raises $12M', 'lifestyle and fashion', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.simplifyber.com/\">Simplifyber</a></span>, a bio-based fashion manufacturing startup, has raised a $12 million Series A, led by Suzano Ventures. The funding will fuel the company\'s growth by expanding its materials science and mechanical engineering expertise, its manufacturing capacity, and driving new collaborations across industries.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Simplifyber: Revolutionizing How Soft Goods Are Produced</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Founded in 2021, Simplifyber is revolutionizing <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/hottest-summer-outfit-ideas-2025-to-shop-now\">fashion</a></span> production with a patented method that bypasses traditional processes like spinning and weaving. At the heart of its technology is Fybron, a new, biodegradable liquid derived from natural fibers. Fybron can be injected into 3D molds, enabling direct production of soft goods like clothing and footwear&mdash;cutting waste and energy consumption.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This bio-based fashion manufacturing startup seeks to substitute fossil-based, man-made fabrics with a sustainable and scalable alternative that is well-positioned to take advantage of an industry under pressure to minimize its environmental impact.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why This Matters: Scalability and Sustainability</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The $12 million infusion is not about throwing money&mdash;it\'s about a strategic move toward cost competitiveness with traditional manufacturing. The money will enable Simplifyber to establish pilot-scale production facilities, making the transition from concept to large-scale deployment easier.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With its solutions grounded in circular economy and sustainable material emphasis, Simplifyber now is poised to grow into other sectors&mdash;automotive interior, home furnishings, and high-performance footwear.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;We\'ve had keen interest from investors and brand partners, and we\'re thrilled to have Suzano Ventures as a strategic investor,\" <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/maria-intscher-owrang-3278a07/\">Simplifyber CEO and co-founder Maria Intscher-Owrang</a></span> said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Maria said, \"Since we started our company, Suzano has been a prime supplier of fibre to us. This partnership will give us exposure to world-class expertise and support, which will help us expand into new markets and drive our growth.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Suzano Invests in the Disruption Suzano Ventures, which is an investment vehicle of the world\'s largest hardwood pulp producer, believes Simplifyber has enormous potential. <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paulapuzzi-corporateventure-innovation-marketing-newbusiness-executive/\">Suzano\'s corporate venture capital senior manager Paula Puzzi,</a></span> pointed out why Simplifyber was among several hundred startups screened based on bio-based materials.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;We think Simplifyber is well placed to shake up soft goods supply chains in clothing, furniture, and even automotive,\" Puzzi said. \"This investment supports our mission of replacing fossil-based materials with bio-based, sustainable materials.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>From Fashion Week to the Factory Floor</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Simplifyber is not just a concept on paper&mdash;it\'s been creating buzz in the real world. In September 2024, the firm partnered with fashion label Ganni to launch a shoe upper made from cellulose-based Fybron during Paris Fashion Week. The partnership proved that their revolutionary production process can hold its own against high fashion while reducing environmental harm.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The firm\'s growing momentum follows a $4.2 million seed round in 2022. Other Series A investors are At One Ventures, Techstars, One Small Planet, Plug and Play Sustainability Fund, Collateral Good, Overlay Capital, and other similarly motivated climate investors.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Bio-Based Fashion Revolution in the Making </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As the fashion world starts to head towards greener pastures, this bio-based fashion manufacturing startup is all set to usher in the revolution. With its patented process, sustainable materials, and sustainability-driven philosophy, Simplifyber is changing the way products are created&mdash;right from the runways to everyday essentials.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If their pace is maintained, Simplifyber could be the template for the next wave of fashion-tech companies attempting to save the planet with innovation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-25', '11:56:29', 'bio-based-fashion-manufacturing-startup-simplifyber-raises-12m', 'article/visionaries-network-bio-based-fashion-manufacturing-startup1.webp', 'Bio-Based Fashion Manufacturing Startup', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-bio-based-fashion-manufacturing-startup1.webp', 4, 2025, 'Simplifyber, bio-based fashion, sustainable manufacturing, cellulose garments, 3D printing, fashion innovation, eco-friendly textiles, biodegradable clothing, fashion startup, funding news, sustainable fashion, additive manufacturing, textile industry, eco-conscious apparel, investment in fashion', 'Simplifyber secures $12M to revolutionize fashion with biodegradable, 3D-printed cellulose garments, aiming to transform sustainable apparel manufacturing.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(150, NULL, 'Silver Reef Casino Uses AI to Boost Small Casino Success', 'Silver Reef Casino Leverages AI Analytics for Small Casinos', 'casino tech and innovation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Silver Reef Casino Resort is stepping up its tech game by choosing Gaming Analytics to fuel its data-driven business. In its quest to be at the forefront of implementing next-gen AI analytics for small <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/wheel-of-fortune-video-poker-launches-in-vegas\">casinos</a></span>, the Ferndale-based resort is now leveraging real-time, artificial intelligence-based solutions to make quicker, wiser business decisions&mdash;all without the expense of an in-house analytics team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This collaboration is a rising trend for regional and tribal casinos to implement scalable, cloud-based analytics in order to compete in an increasingly dynamic industry.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;As a de facto analytics department for a casino, Gaming Analytics is a go-to resource,\" said <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/dale-robertson-52a2a644/\">Dale Robertson, General Manager of Silver Reef Casino Resort</a></span>. \"Being able to see patron activity in real-time and adjust marketing strategy on the fly has had a quantifiable effect. GA\'s platform is indispensable.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Real-Time Optimization of the Casino Floor</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With more than 1,000 slot machines, table games, a few dining venues, and a luxury hotel and spa, Silver Reef Casino Resort is a full-service entertainment resort of the Pacific Northwest. It is owned and operated by the Lummi Nation and is a local favorite as well as a tourist destination.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Silver Reef is now taking advantage of Gaming Analytics\' A.I. platform to revolutionize the management of those amenities. From the parking lot to the dining room and bars, the resort can monitor trends, guest behavior, and operational performance in real time&mdash;albeit all within one easy-to-navigate dashboard.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Real-time access to slot analytics is a game-changer,\" said <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/wayne-moenoa-1014a679/\">Wayne Moenoa, Director of Slots at Silver Reef</a></span>. \"We no longer have to wait for after-the-fact reports. GA gives us the power to make quick, smart decisions that drive maximum revenue and improve the guest experience.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Slot play is a key source of revenue for casinos of all sizes. GA\'s technology allows Silver Reef to identify poorly performing machines, floor plan for maximum efficiency, and adjust incentive plans&mdash;all from real-time information, without the lag of manual reporting.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Rolling Out A.I. Analytics Across the Resort</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While most casinos use analytics for gaming alone, Silver Reef is taking it a step further. The resort plans to utilize Gaming Analytics\' software to maximize other departments like marketing, hotel operations, and retail planning.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;We view this as a basis for further end-to-end digital transformation,\" Robertson said. \"Having real-time information at our fingertips, along with GA\'s backing, enables us to make improved decisions across the property.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This forward-thinking strategy is one aspect of a broader movement in the gaming sector: the growth of AI analytics for small casinos and regional resorts that desire the capabilities of big data without the expense and complexity.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What is Gaming Analytics?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Established in 2017, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://gaminganalytics.ai/\">Gaming Analytics</a></span> is an A.I.-based platform that provides real-time analytics, predictive modeling, and slot optimization to casino operators. Purpose-built to make complicated data work easy, GA gives properties of all sizes&mdash;particularly those with no large IT staff&mdash;the ability to optimize operations, maximize marketing ROI, and enhance the guest experience.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;We are excited to have Silver Reef become part of the GA network,\" says <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kiranbrahmandam/\">Kiran Brahmandam, Founder and CEO of Gaming Analytics</a></span>. \"Their organization understands the value of having real-time intelligence, and we are excited to assist their operating goals.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By breaking down the barriers to advanced analytics, Gaming Analytics is allowing tribal, freestanding, and regional casinos to access data insights that were once the domain of mega-resorts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>At the Forefront of Data-Driven Gaming </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The partnership between <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/live-streaming-technology-in-online-casinos-transforms-gaming\">Gaming</a></span> Analytics and Silver Reef Casino Resort is not software&mdash;it\'s strategy. As casinos nationwide struggle to compete and keep up, offerings such as GA are demonstrating that AI analytics for smaller casinos is no longer an extravagance&mdash;it\'s a necessity. From slot layout optimization to customer engagement optimization, the future of casino operations is real-time data-driven and A.I.-powered.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-25', '00:26:49', 'silver-reef-casino-leverages-ai-analytics-for-small-casinos', 'article/visionaries-network-silver-reef-casino-resort.webp', 'Silver Reef Casino Leverages AI Analytics for Small Casinos', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-silver-reef-casino-resort.webp', 4, 2025, 'Silver Reef Casino, AI analytics, small casinos, casino technology, gaming innovation, data analysis, AI tools, casino trends, customer insights, gaming revenue, casino growth, AI-driven strategy, casino AI, data-driven casinos, gaming analytics', 'Silver Reef Casino adopts AI analytics to help small casinos enhance customer insights, boost revenue, and stay competitive in the gaming industry.', 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(151, NULL, 'Essar Energy Transition Supports HyNet for Clean Future', 'Essar Energy Transition Backs HyNet for Low-Carbon Future', 'Environment Power and Clean Energy', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.essar.com/\">Essar Energy Transition</a></span> has congratulated Eni and the UK government for finalizing the financial deal for the Liverpool Bay carbon capture and storage (CCS) project. It is a key milestone for the HyNet Industrial Cluster and a major step closer to the UK\'s clean energy ambitions.<br><br>The Liverpool Bay CCS is part of the carbon handling system of HyNet. It enables permanent and secure storage of COâ‚‚ emissions. As construction is at hand, there are plenty of investment opportunities for low-carbon technologies in this project. The project also aids in the curtailment of carbon emissions within North West England and North Wales.<br><br><strong>HPP1 Hydrogen Plant for Low-Carbon Development</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the most notable projects associated with the new CCS equipment is Essar Energy Transition\'s Hydrogen Production Plant 1 (HPP1). It will be the UK\'s first large low-carbon hydrogen factory. The factory will produce 350 megawatts (MW) of hydrogen and will capture around 600,000 tonnes of COâ‚‚ annually. That is the equivalent of removing 125,000 cars from the road.<br><br>&ldquo;This is a major milestone not just for the HyNet group but also for the UK\'s energy transition to cleaner energy,\" said <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tony-fountain-a959a554/\">Tony Fountain, Managing Partner of Essar Energy Transition</a></span>. \"The HyNet COâ‚‚ pipeline will play an important role in helping industries transition in the North West and shows how our Stanlow Manufacturing Complex is a hub for energy transition.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Stanlow Manufacturing Complex: Leading the Change</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Stanlow Manufacturing Complex is situated at the heart of the HyNet cluster and is being redeveloped to be a future energy hub. Its core element is the EET Fuels refinery, and Stanlow is already a major part of the UK energy infrastructure. It will be among the top places for the low-carbon industry in Europe in the near term.<br><br>The plant is intended to lower carbon emissions by capturing as much as 2 million tonnes of COâ‚‚ annually and assisting in the production of low-carbon products and fuels. These are:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Bringing electricity to important industrial work</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Adding carbon capture and storage (CCS) plants</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Construction of Hydrogen Production Plant 2 (HPP2)</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Production of Sustainable Aviation Fuel (SAF)</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Securing Employment and Stimulating Economic Growth</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition to lowering emissions, the projects are expected to protect and create jobs, promote local economic growth, and deliver long-term UK fuel security.<br><br>&ldquo;This provides huge opportunities for future North West business development,\" Fountain added. \"It confirms Stanlow\'s path to being one of Europe\'s leading decarbonised refineries.\"<br><br><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/joe-seifert-735610a4/\">Joe Seifert, EET Hydrogen\'s Chief Executive</a></span>, said: <em>\"Today\'s announcement gives us high confidence as we move ahead to build our flagship project.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Hydrogen Infrastructure for the Future</strong><br><br>Hydrogen is central to the UK\'s net-zero strategy. HPP1 will supply clean hydrogen to industry, transport, and power networks in the area. Carbon capture makes these operations low in carbon from start to finish.<br><br>As this plant expands, Stanlow will be a prime launch point for a broader hydrogen economy, with a template being repeatable for future UK energy groups. A Roadmap for UK <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/pure-unveils-purepower-a-game-changer-in-indias-renewable-energy-landscape\">Clean Energy</a></span> Leadership Essar Energy Transition\'s plan for a low-carbon energy future positions the company&mdash;and the Stanlow facility&mdash;at the vanguard of the UK\'s decarbonisation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As work on HyNet proceeds, it shows what is possible where public-private partnership is married to technological innovation to build a cleaner, more secure energy future for generations to come.<br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-26', '00:39:19', 'essar-energy-transition-backs-hynet-for-low-carbon-future', 'article/visionaries-network-essar-clean-energy.webp', 'Essar Energy Transition Backs HyNet for Low-Carbon Future', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-essar-clean-energy.webp', 4, 2025, 'Essar Energy, HyNet, low-carbon, energy transition, hydrogen, clean energy, carbon capture, visionaries network, sustainability, green future, net-zero, industrial decarbonization, climate action, energy innovation, renewable solutions', 'Essar Energy Transition partners with HyNet to drive a low-carbon future through hydrogen and carbon capture technologies in the UK.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(152, NULL, 'eBay &amp; Klarna Partner to Offer Flexible Payments in US', 'eBay Klarna Partnership 2025 Brings Flexible Payments to the US', 'banking and fintech', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.ebay.com/\">eBay</a></span>, the largest online marketplace in the world that connects millions of buyers and sellers, has now formally extended its strategic partnership with <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.klarna.com/international/\">Klarna</a></span> to provide a flexible payment option for shoppers in the United States. This significant move allows US consumers to utilize Klarna\'s flexible \"Pay in 4\" and longer-term credit products directly on the eBay platform.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The eBay Klarna partnership 2025 follows a successful launch in six European nations&mdash;the UK, France, Italy, Austria, the Netherlands, and Spain&mdash;last December 2024. The payment options in these markets performed particularly well in high-value segments like electronics, collectibles, and fashion.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Millions of American eBay consumers can take advantage in the same manner. Klarna\'s \"Pay in 4\" divides purchases into four interest-free payments, and its financing options provide longer terms on higher-priced items.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Strategic Expansion via Flexible Payments</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This alliance underpins the general market growth strategy of eBay by <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/tapcheck-raises-225m-to-expand-on-demand-pay-platform\">powering the Payments</a></span> and Financial Services business. The goal is to further streamline the checkout experience and make it more modern, and create additional revenue streams apart from seller fees.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/avrittimittal/\">Avritti Khandurie Mittal, EVP and GM for Global Payments and Financial Services at eBay</a></span>, says:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;With more than 2.3 billion listings, eBay is where shoppers go to buy with purpose&mdash;whether it\'s a retro gadget, a hard-to-find car part, or a vintage purse. We\'re looking forward to bringing our international strategic partnership with Klarna to the US.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The eBay Klarna partnership 2025 will enhance the buying power of consumers by providing more payment choices, particularly convenient in the current economy, as consumers are becoming increasingly thrifty.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Circular Commerce: Klarna\'s Resell Tool Goes Live on eBay</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the most innovative features of the alliance is Klarna\'s resale function, which is now available to US consumers through eBay. The function allows consumers to resell products they have already purchased with Klarna&mdash;with product details and images pre-populated.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Since launching in December 2024, the resell option has already prompted over 500,000 new listings on eBay, signaling heightened consumer demand for the circular economy and sustainable take-up. This aligns with eBay\'s mission of keeping products in use for longer and delivering a quick and simple resale experience to its users.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Klarna US Market Play</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For Klarna, the acquisition further solidifies its footprint in the highly competitive US buy now, pay later (BNPL) space, where <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/smartbiz-becomes-first-fintech-bank-approved-under-trump\">fintech</a></span> giants such as Affirm, Afterpay, and PayPal also vie for domination.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/david-sykes01/\">David Sykes, Klarna\'s Chief Commercial Officer</a></span>, said:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"eBay is one of the most dynamic marketplaces in the world, offering everything from the mundane to the unusual and unique. With this growth, we\'re giving US consumers the power to buy what they want in more personalized, flexible terms.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Through gaining direct access to eBay\'s vast American consumer base, Klarna is able to promote massive user acquisition for its AI-driven payments app, as well as enhance its merchant relationships and overall US presence.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>The Future of Shopping: Flexibility and Sustainability</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The eBay Klarna partnership 2025 is not merely introducing a new payment option&mdash;it\'s about shaping the future of shopping. With growing interest in flexible payments and sustainability, this partnership is for the new-age consumer who wants convenience along with sustainable consumption.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For eBay, it\'s a savvy play as it looks to become more than a resale behemoth, but also a fintech-powered marketplace. For Klarna, it\'s a bold play deeper into integration with one of the internet\'s most recognizable brands. As the eBay Klarna partnership 2025 goes completely live in the US, it will revolutionize the way Americans buy&mdash;and the way they sell&mdash;on one of the world\'s most powerful e-commerce platforms.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-26', '00:52:51', 'ebay-klarna-partnership-2025-brings-flexible-payments-to-the-us', 'article/visionaries-network-ebay-klarna-partnership.webp', 'eBay Klarna Partnership 2025 Brings Flexible Payments to the US', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-ebay-klarna-partnership.webp', 4, 2025, 'eBay, Klarna, flexible payments, 2025 partnership, buy now pay later, online shopping, visionaries network, e-commerce, payment solutions, Klarna US, eBay checkout, digital payments, fintech, eBay Klarna 2025, shopping flexibility', 'eBay teams up with Klarna in 2025 to bring flexible &quot;buy now, pay later&quot; payment options to US shoppers, enhancing online shopping convenience.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(153, '', 'M&amp;S Cyber Attack Halts Online Orders in UK and Ireland', 'Marks &amp; Spencer Cyber Attack Online Orders Paused in UK, Ireland', 'lifestyle and fashion', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.marksandspencer.com/?msockid=2aad64c6e205683d3ed37785e3f26953\">Marks &amp; Spencer</a></span> (MKS.L) suspended online trading temporarily in the UK and Ireland after a last-week cyber-attack. The action, announced on Friday, reduced the British <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../retail-and-ecommerce\">retailer\'s</a></span> shares by 5%.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Popular for its clothing, homeware, and food, Marks &amp; Spencer said the move was a \"proactive management\" response to the incident. The firm said its employees, with the support of leading cyber experts, work around the clock to rebuild its internet services in a secure way.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a post on <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://x.com/x\">X</a></span> (formerly Twitter), Marks &amp; Spencer apologized for the disruption it has caused to customers. It also promised that its physical stores remain open for shopping, as some international websites are also suspending orders.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Description of the Incident</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Marks &amp; Spencer first revealed the cyber-attack last week, stating that it would lead to some short-term changes to store operations. Customers subsequently experienced contactless payment issues and click-and-collect delays.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Marks &amp; Spencer cyber attack online orders has raised alarm, especially given that nearly a third of the company\'s clothing and home business is conducted online. The prolonged downtime will potentially be a threat to revenue if online shopping is not reinstated in the near future.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The National Crime Agency stated that it had knowledge of the incident and was working with the National Cyber Security Centre to help Marks &amp; Spencer with an investigation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Marks &amp; Spencer\'s Response</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As part of its recovery process, Marks &amp; Spencer has also gone the precautionary route of suspending all online and app orders. This is to safeguard customers\' details and avoid any further risks as the company recovers its digital systems.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>\"We have a talented team &mdash; supported by leading cyber experts &mdash; working tirelessly to get online and app shopping back to full service,\" </em>Marks &amp; Spencer announced in its official statement.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although the Marks &amp; Spencer cyber attack online orders procedure is infuriating for consumers, the shops of the company are open for business as usual. This means customers are still capable of obtaining food, fashion, homeware, and beauty products from stores while digital infrastructure is repaired.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Watershed Moment for Retail Cybersecurity</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">UK high street favorite Marks &amp; Spencer recorded around &pound;13 billion in revenues last year in all its business divisions. With increasingly more and more transactions being made online, there has never been a greater need for proper cybersecurity measures.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Marks &amp; Spencer cyber attack online orders incident highlights the weaknesses that even big retailers must contend with today. While the scope of the attack is not yet out for public scrutiny, that the company acted swiftly by suspending services is a commendable indication of its care for protecting customers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At the same time, Marks &amp; Spencer is encouraging consumers to continue shopping in store and assuring that it will let everyone know when online and app shopping is back to full service.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-26', '23:52:41', 'ms-cyber-attack-halts-online-orders-in-uk-and-ireland', 'article/vsionaries-network-marks-and-spencer-cyber-attack-online-order-pause.webp', 'Marks &amp; Spencer Cyber Attack Online Orders Paused in UK, Ireland', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/vsionaries-network-marks-and-spencer-cyber-attack-online-order-pause.webp', 4, 2025, 'Marks &amp; Spencer, M&amp;S, cyber attack, online orders, UK, Ireland, data breach, cybersecurity, M&amp;S website, retail cyber attack, shopping disruption, ecommerce, M&amp;S hack, online shopping pause, Visionaries network', 'Marks &amp; Spencer faces a cyber attack, forcing a pause in online orders across the UK and Ireland as security teams work to restore services.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(154, '', 'Meta Smart Glasses 2025: Features &amp; Launch Details', 'Meta Smart Glasses October 2025: New Features and Launch Details', 'wearable technology', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Meta will make a huge leap in wearable tech. Following the hullabaloo that the&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.ray-ban.com/usa/ray-ban-meta-ai-glasses?cid=PM-FGS_010122-US-SmartShoppingRayBanStoriesRBM&amp;promo=eaccess&amp;cid=PM-SBI_080622-5.US-RayBanStories-EN-B-NA-PMAX-NA-Prs-NA-Ecom-NA__&amp;gclid=081e51750afa1db0a1b4397a7da30ade&amp;gclsrc=3p.ds&amp;msclkid=081e51750afa1db0a1b4397a7da30ade&amp;utm_source=bing&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_campaign=5.US-RayBanStories-EN-B-NA-PMAX-NA-Prs-NA-Ecom-NA&amp;utm_term=www.ray-ban.com&amp;utm_content=Always%20On\">Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses</a></span> in India brought about, the tech behemoth is now sprinting towards introducing an entirely new, top-of-the-line model. Based on a Bloomberg report, Meta smart glasses October 2025 release date has been announced, and the new model is going to bring electrifying new features.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The future Meta glasses will allegedly come with a small internal display screen. The new functionality will enable users to display images and use basic apps straight from the glasses without the need to constantly connect the glasses to a smartphone. If all goes as planned, the new smart glasses will launch at more than $1,000, which will make them a high-end product compared to previous versions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Meta Smart Glasses October 2025 Release: Ambitious Timelines and Scheduling Issues</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Meta seems to be extremely dedicated to the October 2025 deadline. Managers are reported to have instructed teams to work faster, even over weekends, in order for the project to be finished within the strict deadline. Although there is less chance the project is going to be delayed, the company is doing all it can to keep on track. With the Meta smart glasses October 2025 deadline, Meta is keen to be a good role model in the <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/google-and-samsung-to-launch-xr-glasses-in-2026-with-smart-features\">wearable technology</a></span> race.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The new release will likely be a paradigm shift in the wearables space. So far, the majority of smart glasses have not been able to offer great design, practical features, and affordable prices. Meta\'s new glasses, if successful, could be a new benchmark.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Apple\'s Secret Smart Glasses \"N50\" and Camera AirPods: Competition Intensifies</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the meantime, Apple is not idle. <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/apple-watch-upgrade-set-to-transform-wearables-by-2027\">Apple</a></span>, the tech giant, is quietly working on its own line of smart glasses codenamed \"N50.\" Apple smart glasses N50, while still in their infancy, will be capable of scanning their surroundings and offering them useful information &mdash; a step toward augmented reality, but not entirely entering into it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition, Apple is working on another new product: camera AirPods. Camera AirPods would be for people who don\'t want to wear glasses all day but still want some of the same environmental sensing features.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While Meta is building a first-mover advantage in the market for smart glasses, industry observers think that the actual competition between Meta and Apple will start in the second half of this decade. Both firms will likely launch fully immersive AR glasses by then, and smart glasses will be as ubiquitous as smartphones are today.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Meta vs Apple: Who Wins the War of Smart Glasses?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It\'s rare to see Apple, the owner of wearables like the Apple Watch, ceding early center stage to another technology behemoth. Meta\'s rapid response with the Meta smart glasses October 2025 project could pay dividends in the short term. Apple\'s past, however, suggests that it likes to mature a technology before it launches a blockbuster.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For now, Meta\'s first priority is clear: get next-generation smart glasses ready for October 2025 and build solid ground in India and other countries with products like the Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses. If all goes well, the world might be seeing an entirely new way of app, photo, and internet interaction &mdash; all through a cool pair of glasses.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-04-28', '22:58:48', 'meta-smart-glasses-october-2025-new-features-and-launch-details', 'article/visionaries-network-meta-launch-smart-glasses-2025.webp', 'Meta Smart Glasses October 2025: New Features and Launch Details', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-meta-launch-smart-glasses-2025.webp', 4, 2025, 'Meta Smart Glasses, 2025 launch, AR glasses, wearable tech, Meta glasses features, smart eyewear,visionaries network, hands-free tech, Meta innovations, tech launch, smart devices, Meta updates, next-gen glasses, connected eyewear, wearable AI', 'Meta unveils its 2025 Smart Glasses with cutting-edge features, AR capabilities, and hands-free tech designed to elevate daily life and digital interaction.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);
