(199, NULL, 'LEGO, Boston Library Grant Boosts 150K Kids&#039; Learning', 'LEGO Boston Public Library Grant Supports 150K Kids&rsquo; Learning', 'edtech and learning', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.lego.com/en-in\">LEGO</a></span> is making a significant difference in Boston&mdash;just weeks after opening its new U.S. headquarters in Boston, the global toy giant introduced the LEGO Boston Public Library grant, a $1 million initiative to bring interactive, play-based learning to more than 150,000 children in the Greater Boston community.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The two-year program, funded by the <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://learningthroughplay.com/about-us/the-lego-foundation\">LEGO Community Fund</a></span>, will help support dozens of new projects at the Boston Public Library (BPL). Why? To allow children of all backgrounds to \"learn through play\" and strengthen their connection with their communities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Library leaders project the program will lead to 21,000 new library card accounts and over 600,000 book checkouts&mdash;a literacy and youth outreach coup.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The grant for innovation will unlock what is possible&mdash;more creative, more playful, and more civic experiences for young people in all Boston neighborhoods,\" stated <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/dleonard/\">Boston Public Library President David Leonard.</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What the LEGO Boston Public Library Grant Includes</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The LEGO Boston Public Library grant will fund a variety of children\'s programs from 0 through 13 years old:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->LEGO Clubs for upper-level children at 11 BPL locations will feature STEM, civic, and storytelling exercises led by trained LEGO employee volunteers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->20 author and music events will feature creative storytelling and invite writers and artists to be open.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->A LEGO summer design competition will ask kids to design a big mural to be displayed at BPL\'s iconic Copley Square branch.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->For children under the age of 9, the library will offer 12,000 parent literacy kits of books, multilingual materials, and DUPLO blocks to learn toddlers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->The library will also resume its popular \"1,000 Books Before Kindergarten\" program, now enhanced with LEGO\'s signature hands-on play elements.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->These programs will extend beyond library walls, with literacy kits sent to hospitals and city-wide community centers&mdash;giving equal access to all families.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>LEGO Moves Headquarters to Boston </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The announcement follows LEGO\'s official relocation of its U.S. headquarters from Connecticut to Boston, closing a 50-year chapter and opening a new one in the center of a city of international renown for learning and innovation. The relocation is expected to be finalized by the end of 2026, but the company has already made its presence known.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">During the ribbon-cutting ceremony, LEGO Group CEO Niels Christiansen called Boston his favorite American city.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Boston is at the center of it all, from sports and literature to innovation and, most crucially, learning,\" Christiansen said. \"This is the perfect place to broaden out our mission to inspire the builders of tomorrow.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Boston Mayor Michelle Wu also rolled out the red carpet for LEGO to the city, referring to Boston as a \"community of builders\" and lauding the new public-private sector partnership.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Building the Future, One Brick at a Time</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The LEGO Boston Public Library grant is a new wave of corporate-community collaborations that go beyond brand to deliver real value. In this case, LEGO is planting roots in its newest hometown not as a job creator, but as a force for kids\' development and public education.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By combining the educational mission of the Boston Public Library with the playful, creativity-oriented aesthetic of LEGO, this grant offers a template for how private enterprise can help reimagine the public services of the future.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Whether it\'s a LEGO Club project, a literacy kit packed with books, or a community-created mural, the LEGO Boston Public Library grant will be making an investment in long-term returns on Boston children&mdash;one brick, one book, and one imagination at a time.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-20', '00:01:04', 'lego-boston-public-library-grant-supports-150k-kids-learning', 'article/visionaries-network-lego-boston-public-library-grant-support (1).webp', 'LEGO, Boston Library Grant Boosts 150K Kids&#039; Learning', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-lego-boston-public-library-grant-support (1).webp', 5, 2025, 'LEGO, Boston Public Library, visionaries, kids game, learning, STEM, visionaries network, programs, support,  kids education, kids development, outreach', 'LEGO partners with Boston Public Library through a grant to support learning programs benefiting 150,000 kids across the community.', 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(200, NULL, 'Metaplanet Bitcoin Holdings Top $800M in 2025', 'Metaplanet Bitcoin Holdings Surge Past $800M in 2025', 'blockchain and cryptocurrency', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a shocking turnaround,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://metaplanet.jp/en\">Metaplanet</a></span> has moved from being a relatively unknown Japanese tech firm to a world leader in the global cryptocurrency arena. The firm is now sitting on a staggering 7,800 BTC, worth over $807 million at the current price, making it one of the world\'s top ten listed firms with the largest holdings of Bitcoin.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This expansion is no coincidence. It is a bold, strategic bet on digital holdings, implying that Metaplanet Bitcoin holdings are not only a hedge&mdash;but a core financial tool. The company\'s aggressive maneuvers can change institutional investors in Asia\'s approach to crypto.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Strategy Built on Bitcoin</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Metaplanet\'s rocket-like path in the cryptocurrency universe is in a highly focused strategy of Bitcoin purchases. During May 2025 alone, the firm made two headline-grabbing purchases&mdash;first purchasing 1,241 Bitcoins and then another 1,004 Bitcoins. These purchases worth more than 15.2 billion yen, were made at an average price of 15.13 million yen per Bitcoin.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The goal? To overtake Galaxy Digital, which has 8,101 BTC in its vault, and become a member of the exclusive club of the top nine largest publicly disclosed Bitcoin holders. Should the pace keep up, that milestone could be reached sooner than later.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Smart Tracking, High Performance</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It\'s not simply a matter of investing in Bitcoin&mdash;Metaplanet is converting those holdings into concrete dividends. During Q4 2024, the company\'s Bitcoin holdings returned a staggering 309.8%. Q1 2025 added another 95.6%, and the second quarter is already at 47.8%. These returns indicate an extremely calculated investment model supported by excellent timing and strategic foresight.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With in-house performance indicators like BTC Gain and BTC &yen; Gain, Metaplanet has close monitoring of its <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/bitcoin-price-after-trump-news-boosts-crypto-market-sentiment\">Bitcoin</a></span> positions. The company\'s proprietary approach has immediate adjustments and risk management in advance of market changes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Creative Financing Without Traditional Debt</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To capitalize on its successive purchases, Metaplanet is embracing a warrant-based financing strategy&mdash;a technique that bypasses traditional debt without compromising value for shareholders. By issuing successive structured warrants, the company gains access to capital without putting a substantial dent in shares.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This funding model provides room for maneuver in uncertain markets and guarantees that the firm can respond fast when Bitcoin falls or rises. It\'s a hybrid model that is appropriate for the dynamic character of crypto trading.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Asia\'s Crypto Attitude Shift</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Japan has traditionally been conservative in the realm of cryptocurrency. But Metaplanet Bitcoin holdings have set the pace, proving that Japanese companies can be as innovative&mdash;and as bold&mdash;as their Western counterparts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In fact, Metaplanet now holds more Bitcoin than El Salvador, the world\'s first country to legalize Bitcoin as legal tender. With its aim of one day holding 1% of the world\'s store of Bitcoin, the firm is creating new space in the region and disrupting traditional thinking of what is possible in Asian crypto markets.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>The Road Ahead </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While Metaplanet\'s achievement is staggering, the crypto world is known to be volatile. Whether or not it can sustain the momentum and its sky-high returns remains to be seen.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But one thing is for sure: Metaplanet Bitcoin holdings are now part of the company\'s brand and strategy. By opening up more possibilities for what Japanese companies can accomplish in crypto, Metaplanet is becoming a model for local investment&mdash;and a power to be met with in the global digital asset space. Competitors and investors are taking notice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-21', '00:15:22', 'metaplanet-bitcoin-holdings-surge-past-800m-in-2025', 'article/visionaries-network-metaplanet-bitcoin-holdings-surge-past-8m.webp', 'Metaplanet Bitcoin Holdings Surge Past $800M in 2025', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-metaplanet-bitcoin-holdings-surge-past-8m.webp', 5, 2025, 'Metaplanet, Bitcoin, crypto, investment, visionaries, visionaries network, digital assets, blockchain, finance, portfolio, cryptocurrency, market, growth, strategy', 'Metaplanet&rsquo;s Bitcoin holdings surge past $800 million in 2025, highlighting its aggressive crypto investment strategy and market confidence.', 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(201, NULL, 'Standard Chartered PE Team Expands Globally', 'Standard Chartered Private Equity Team Expands Globally', 'banking and fintech', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.sc.com/us/\">Standard Chartered</a></span> has formed a new specialist team in private equity firms, hedge funds, and sovereign wealth funds. The move is a strategic build-out of its investment banking franchise.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The new Standard Chartered private equity team will be within the bank\'s financial institution coverage group and will have around 25 bankers to start with. The team, led from New York, will also maintain offices in London and Dubai.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Leadership and Organization of the New Unit</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the interim, until the permanent global head of financial sponsors assumes the role, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/molly-duffy-burns-48600b112/\">Molly Duffy, co-head of financial institution</a></span> coverage, will lead the group. She shares responsibility for running the division with Jerry Zhang. The coming of the permanent head is around the corner, but the interim leadership is symptomatic of the team\'s importance to the bank\'s broader business goals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Strategic Reorientation Amidst International Banking Stress</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Standard Chartered\'s new initiative is a major attempt at growth in business with financial sponsors. Already, these customers account for 51% of the bank\'s total investment banking fee income. With a greater return than the average, they are a high-growth opportunity. Standard Chartered private equity team will spearhead the growth, targeting companies that will deliver long-term value.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Simultaneously, its rival HSBC has been downsizing its U.S. and European M&amp;A and capital markets businesses. StanChart is defying the trend by investing more in the West and maintaining its high profile in Asia, Africa, and the Middle East.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Focus on High-Return Institutional Clients</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As Sunil Kaushal, the co-head of StanChart\'s corporate and investment banking, puts it, the bank is doubling up on asset managers, insurers, banks, and private equity clients. The Standard Chartered private equity team will form the center of the strategy so that the bank can participate in big cross-border deals and have more substantial relationships with high-value <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/05/willis-launches-fintech-insurance-solutions-with-fintech-plus\">financial</a></span> sponsors.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Investor Strategy Presentation Points to New Direction</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The announcement is made in conjunction with a presentation to investors within the framework of a broader drive for transparency. The presentation gave a glimpse into what StanChart will do to shift its investment banking business into higher-margin return and stable growth areas.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-22', '00:08:13', 'standard-chartered-private-equity-team-expands-globally', 'article/visionaries-network-standard-chartered-private-equity.webp', 'Standard Chartered Private Equity Team Expands Globally', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-standard-chartered-private-equity.webp', 5, 2025, 'Standard Chartered, private equity, global expansion, investment team, finance, mergers, acquisitions, visionaries network, visionaries', 'Standard Chartered&#039;s Private Equity team announces global expansion, strengthening investment capabilities across key international markets.', 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(202, NULL, 'Volvo EX90 Gets First Android 15 Update', 'Volvo Android 15 Update Arrives First in EX90 Electric SUV', 'it and software', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a move to transform the smart car market,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.volvocars.com/in/cars/electric-cars/?msockid=2aad64c6e205683d3ed37785e3f26953\">Volvo Cars</a></span> and Alphabet\'s Google have announced a major development to their collaboration: Volvo is now the primary development partner for Android Automotive.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The more integrated collaboration will see Volvo become the first-ever car manufacturer to introduce the latest Android 15 update to its vehicles, enabling its owners to enjoy the best software updates years before other car manufacturers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The new Volvo EX90 electric SUV, which debuted at Google I/O 2025, is the first production car to natively boot on Android 15. That\'s right &mdash; when everybody else is still on Android 12 or 13, Volvo Android 15 update is already available in the wild to be rolled out.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&ldquo;We will be in a position to respond fast in bringing new capabilities, new features, and new experiences to our customers,\" <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alwinbakkenes/\">Volvo global software engineering head Alwin Bakkenes</a></span> told Reuters in an interview. \"This actually gives us an early advantage in creating great customer experiences.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why It Matters</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Overall, the auto industry has lagged two full Android updates behind smartphones. That is, drivers have not been able to access the same smart features in their cars that they adore on their phones. This partnership aims to bridge that gap&mdash;and fast.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Through its role as a lead development partner, Volvo has a front-row seat to Google software innovation. More importantly, Google engineers will now validate new Android features in Volvo vehicles for real-time feedback and performance insights in actual driving scenarios.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"They will take the car, see how their product performs in real-world conditions&mdash;much sooner and much quicker,\" Bakkenes said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Gemini AI Takes to the Highway</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Another major overhaul was announced at the Google I/O conference: Google\'s Gemini AI model will be integrated into Volvo cars soon. For the drivers, it will mean no more messing with touchscreens or scrolling through long lists of contacts to enter destinations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Rather, you can say things such as:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Hey Gemini, locate my dentist appointment in my mail and take me there,\" or &ldquo;Create a shopping list for those ingredients from that dinner recipe my sister shared with me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Volvo\'s purpose, says Bakkenes, is a \"human-centric experience\" &mdash; one where technology enhances your experience without taking away from it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Android 15 Takes the Road First with Volvo</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Volvo Android 15 update will be offered in the EX90 SUV later this year, with other models to follow. That would put Volvo owners in the position of potentially having two years more advanced software than the competition &mdash; a huge advantage in the connected car market.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While other firms will only be able to release Android 15 in 2027, Volvo drivers will already be enjoying it by the end of 2025.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This is not about listening to music or using maps. Android 15 will improve everything from voice control to personalized infotainment systems, making driving smarter and safer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Final Thoughts </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This move makes Volvo a clear technology pioneer in the automotive industry. By being in a position to access Google\'s sophisticated <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/laser-technologies-unveils-nesting-software-for-cutting\">software</a></span> &mdash; and <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/05/meta-ai-app-premium-tier-launches-new-revenue-stream\">artificial intelligence</a></span> &mdash; before anyone else, the Swedish car maker is setting the standard for what drivers can expect from cars these days.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If you are looking to buy a technology-facilitated electric car, look out for the EX90, and the word in your head should be: Volvo Android 15 update.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-22', '00:18:09', 'volvo-android-15-update-arrives-first-in-ex90-electric-suv', 'article/visionaries-volvo-android-15-udate-arrives-first-in-ex90-electric-ev.webp', 'Volvo Android 15 Update Arrives First in EX90 Electric SUV', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-volvo-android-15-udate-arrives-first-in-ex90-electric-ev.webp', 5, 2025, 'Volvo, Android 15, EX90, electric SUV, software update, infotainment, EV, car tech, visionaries network, visionaries, automobile news, latest news', 'Volvo rolls out the Android 15 update first in its EX90 electric SUV, enhancing infotainment and tech features for a smarter driving experience.', 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(203, '', 'Nerivio REN: FDA-Approved Wearable for Migraine Relief', 'FDA-Approved Nerivio REN Wearable Device Treats Migraines', 'wearable technology', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Millions of Americans suffer from migraine headaches&mdash;more than a bad headache, migraines are disabling, delivering throbbing pain, nausea, and blinding sensitivity to light and sound.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For decades, treatment has ranged from over-the-counter painkillers to prescription drugs and even Botox injections. But now, a revolutionary, drug-free remedy is revolutionizing the treatment of migraines&mdash;especially among young people.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The FDA-approved <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.nerivio.com/\">Nerivio REN wearable device</a></span>, previously only available to adults, is now approved for patients 12 and up. This drug-free device provides patients with hope who are unable to tolerate or do not respond to drugs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Instead of working chemically, the FDA-approved Nerivio REN wearable device harnesses Remote Electrical Neuromodulation (REN) to engage the body\'s own pain relief mechanism. It is worn on the upper arm and delivers soft electrical impulses that stimulate nerve fibers. This causes a response in the brain that leads to the release of natural painkillers such as serotonin and endorphins.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For Downingtown, Pennsylvania, working mom Alison Kerber, this technology was a game-changer. \"Dealing with chronic pain on a daily basis was really challenging, and I was consistently benched,\" she said. Traditional medications not only failed to keep her migraines in check&mdash;they caused severe side effects. Desperate for relief, she employed the FDA-approved Nerivio REN <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/how-an-ecg-smartwatch-is-revolutionizing-heart-health-among-young-adults\">wearable device</a></span>, and the effect was almost immediate.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It doesn\'t harm and it doesn\'t use drugs,\" Kerber explained. \"I use my phone to operate the device. I\'m able to adjust the stimulus up or down until it\'s just right. It\'s regained control of my life.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/heidi-kling-newnam-29b48111a/\">Dr. Heidi Kling-Newnam, a nurse practitioner at Penn Medicine</a></span> who sees migraine patients, commented that the technology behind the device is elegant and potent. \"By simulating the sensation of pain&mdash;without actually causing injury&mdash;it causes the brain to release its own natural painkillers,\" she said. \"And because it\'s noninvasive and drug-free, the risk of serious side effects is extremely, extremely low.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Nerivio has 45 minutes of wear per session and may be worn at the beginning of an attack of a migraine or every other day as a prophylactic measure. It is therefore perfect for those with both episodic and chronic migraines. The new FDA approval for use in children makes it now available to teenagers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although some insurance companies are catching up on coverage, the out-of-pocket cost is roughly $90 per month. For Kerber, every cent is worth it. \"Being pain-free is worth every cent,\" she said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Medical professionals are excited about what that holds for the future of migraine therapy. While the device won\'t be effective for everyone, it has demonstrated enormous potential, particularly for people who are looking for something other than medication. And with no severe side effects that have been reported, it\'s becoming increasingly popular with patients and physicians alike.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As more people become informed, the FDA-approved Nerivio REN wearable device can be a major part of the battle against migraines. To those families seeking safe, effective, and drug-free answers, it could be the answer they\'ve been waiting for. If you or a loved one are plagued by migraines&mdash;especially if meds haven\'t helped&mdash;the Nerivio wearable is worth investigating. With FDA approval and growing medical community backing, this small device may be a life-altering game-changer for your life.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-22', '23:42:53', 'fda-approved-nerivio-ren-wearable-device-treats-migraines', 'article/Visionaries-network-fda-approved-nerivio-wearable-device-treats.webp', 'FDA-Approved Nerivio REN Wearable Device Treats Migraines', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/Visionaries-network-fda-approved-nerivio-wearable-device-treats.webp', 5, 2025, 'nerivio, migraine relief, wearable device, FDA approved, REN, headache, treatment, drug-free, neuromodulation, migraine therapy, pain management, visionaries network, bioelectronic, non-invasive, medical device', 'Discover Nerivio REN, the FDA-approved wearable device offering safe, drug-free migraine relief through advanced neuromodulation technology.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(204, NULL, 'Dockers Sold to Authentic for $311M in Levi&rsquo;s Overhaul', 'Dockers Brand Sold to Authentic for $311M in Levi&rsquo;s Shakeup', 'brand management digital marketing and business', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a dramatic change of direction in its strategy,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.levistrauss.com/\">Levi Strauss</a></span> has sold the Dockers brand to <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://corporate.authentic.com/press-releases/authentic-brands-group-dockers-acquisition\">Authentic Brands Group</a></span> for $311 million. The transaction, announced Tuesday, lets Levi\'s double down on its core denim business and direct-to-consumer growth strategy while providing Authentic with a widely known casualwear brand to place alongside its growing roster.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Under the agreement, Authentic will acquire Dockers intellectual property, but Centric Brands will oversee day-to-day operations, including manufacturing and distribution. The arrangement is similar to Authentic\'s standard model, which is based on licensing and building brands in global markets.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Levi\'s has been considering selling Dockers since October 2024 in an effort to make its business more rational and to cut out internal brand competition. The Dockers brand, launched in 1986 as a fashionable alternative to jeans, had been a hit in the 1990s and early 2000s. But with changing <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/bio-based-fashion-manufacturing-startup-simplifyber-raises-12m\">fashion</a></span> and the resurgence of denim, khakis have been out of style in the United States.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/michellegass/\">Levi Strauss CEO Michelle Gass</a></span> underscored that the move is in line with the company\'s long-term goals. \"The Dockers transaction further aligns our portfolio to our strategic priorities&mdash;focusing on our direct-to-consumer-first approach, expanding our international footprint, and investing in women\'s and denim lifestyle offerings,\" Gass said.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why did Levi\'s decide to sell</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">During the most recent quarter to March 2, Dockers contributed $67 million of revenue to Levi\'s. While not trivial, the brand was no longer a significant growth driver. Executives cited brand duplication too&mdash;both Levi\'s and Dockers were offering similar tops and bottoms, making it hard to differentiate brands.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition to this, Dockers was also hurting Levi\'s bottom line. By selling it to Authentic, Levi\'s can release capital and focus on more profitable segments, such as its core denim and growing athleisure brand, Beyond Yoga.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Noteworthy is the fact that the agreement also includes a performance aspect: Levi\'s can receive up to $391 million in future payments based on the performance of the Dockers brand in the hands of Authentic.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sees Global Expansion on The Horizon</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although khakis have gone out of style in the United States, Dockers remains popular outside the country. Authentic Brands plans to leverage an international network of licensing partners to restore and grow the Dockers brand globally. With more than 1,700 licensing partners, the company is already negotiating with proprietors in Europe, Asia, Latin America, and the Middle East.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Few brands have a category as fully in their ownership as Dockers does, yet with as much potential left in front of them,\" Authentic Brands Group President Matt Maddox stated. \"Its casualwear heritage will help it, but the real upside is repositioning the brand to a next generation.\".</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Authentic\'s portfolio features successful revamps of other popular brands such as Reebok, Forever 21, and Nautica. The firm is an expert at buying and licensing legacy brands that retain consumer relevance but require strategic repositioning.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Dockers Brand Sold&mdash;What It Means for Retail</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Dockers brand sold is reflecting a larger pattern within the fashion industry: narrowing portfolios to concentrate on high-margin core assets and to enable brand management companies to inject new life into heritage brands.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Levi\'s, for example, is honing its concentration on direct-to-consumer sales and product innovation. Authentic, however, views Dockers as a growth driver in international casualwear.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This is not just a simple sale&mdash;it\'s a sign of how large apparel companies are refocusing. With the Dockers brand sold, both Levi\'s and Authentic are betting on their strengths: Levi\'s on heritage denim and customer relationship, and Authentic on global reach and brand revitalizing expertise.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For fashion observers and retail investors alike, the Dockers deal will be worth observing because it will be a harbinger of a new trend in how established brands become relevant again in a fast-accelerating global economy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><br><br><br><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-22', '23:25:59', 'dockers-brand-sold-to-authentic-for-311m-in-levis-shakeup', 'article/visionaries-network-dockers-brand-sold-authentic-levis-shakeup.webp', 'Dockers Brand Sold to Authentic for $311M in Levi&rsquo;s Shakeup', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-dockers-brand-sold-authentic-levis-shakeup.webp', 5, 2025, 'Dockers, Authentic Brands, Levi&rsquo;s, brand sale, $311M deal, fashion news, apparel, visionaries network, brand shakeup, retail news, Levi Strauss, business deal, clothing, Dockers sale, fashion industry', 'Levi&rsquo;s sells Dockers to Authentic Brands for $311 million in a strategic shift to streamline its business.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(205, '', 'BYD Surpasses Tesla in Europe EV Sales &ndash; April 2025', 'BYD Beats Tesla in Europe April 2025 as EV Leader Shifts', 'ai vr and automation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a surprise switch for the European electric vehicle (EV) market,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.bydglobal.com/en/index.html\">BYD</a></span> beats Tesla in Europe April 2025, new figures from automotive market research firm JATO Dynamics say. Chinese automaker BYD (002594.SZ) had 7,231 <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/jeff-bezos-bets-on-affordable-electric-pickup-truck-maker\">battery-electric vehicles</a></span> (BEVs) registered in European markets in April, edging past Tesla (TSLA.O), which had 7,165.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It is BYD\'s first time beating Tesla in Europe, a region long dominated by Elon Musk\'s EV brand. It is a first for not just BYD, but all Chinese automakers seeking to establish themselves in one of the world\'s most competitive car markets. \"This is a turning point for Europe\'s auto market,\" <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/felipe-munoz-carindustryanalysis/\">JATO Dynamics global analyst Felipe Munoz</a></span> said. \"Tesla has ruled the European BEV market for years, while BYD only officially began selling cars outside Norway and the Netherlands towards the end of 2022.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>BYD\'s meteoric rise</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the main reasons BYD beats Tesla in Europe April 2025 is the business\'s aggressive expansion plan and wide range of electric and plug-in hybrid vehicles. Although April sales only account for BEVs, overall market share of BYD is growing strongly. One recent case of the firm\'s strategy is the BYD Dolphin Surf, introduced at a recent Berlin event: affordable, desirable, and well-equipped EVs for the European market.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although the European Union charges electric vehicles made in China, their sales keep rising. Sales of Chinese electric vehicles grew 59% year-on-year in April compared to the same time last year, while sales of their European, Japanese, South Korean, and American counterparts grew 26%. The figures reflect the strength of Chinese manufacturers in the face of regulatory hurdles.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Aside from this, European BEV registrations in the region increased 28% in April 2024, showing sustained consumer appetite for electric mobility. Chinese automobile manufacturers, particularly BYD, are capitalizing on the same by offering value-for-money options compared to traditional Western manufacturers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tesla\'s Fading Momentum</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Conversely, Tesla\'s European operations have been defined by a string of issues. The company posted a 13% drop in worldwide deliveries in Q1 2025, and the expectation here is for another year of reduced production. Although Elon Musk asserted that Tesla has recovered elsewhere in the world, the sales landscape in Europe does not match.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Tesla troubles have several causes. The older model lineup of the company is falling behind newer models from rivals. In addition, production deficiencies from factory retooling to make the new Model Y have compromised supply. Potential customers are waiting for more affordable versions of the Model Y, which has led short-term sales to plummet.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Elon Musk\'s politics have also set off protests and boycotts in Europe and the U.S., hurting Tesla\'s brand reputation in its most lucrative markets. In a consumer-facing business, these kinds of reputation blows can hurt sales in quantifiable ways.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Paradigm Shift in the Global EV Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">BYD beats Tesla in Europe April 2025 is more than a headline on the front page&mdash;it\'s a harbinger of a larger revolution in the global automobile industry. Chinese electric vehicle makers are no longer niche players; they\'re increasingly serious competitors with an increasingly significant presence in overseas markets.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With its sights fixed on long-term dominance, BYD is poised to become a global giant. Its success in Europe may be the start of a bigger phenomenon where Chinese automakers increasingly lead the way in driving innovation, design, and affordability in the EV space. Since competition is increasing, current players like Tesla must adapt quickly or fall even further behind&mdash;not just in Europe, but everywhere.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-23', '00:09:49', 'byd-beats-tesla-in-europe-april-2025-as-ev-leader-shifts', 'article/visionaries-network-byd-beats-tesla.webp', 'BYD Beats Tesla in Europe April 2025 as EV Leader Shifts', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-byd-beats-tesla.webp', 5, 2025, 'BYD, Tesla, EV sales, Europe, April 2025, electric vehicles, visionaries network, auto industry, clean energy, BYD vs Tesla, EV growth, European market, car sales, green tech, EV trends', 'BYD overtakes Tesla in European EV sales for April 2025, signaling a major shift in the electric vehicle market leadership.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(206, NULL, 'U.S. to End Penny Production by 2026, Treasury Confirms', 'Treasury Confirms End of Penny Production USA by 2026', 'banking and fintech', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The penny, which has been a staple of US currency since 1793, is finally at the end of its own long, winding road.&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://home.treasury.gov/\">The US Treasury Department</a></span> formally announced the end of penny production USA in 2026. The announcement brings to an end over two centuries of the one-cent coin clinking in the country\'s cash registers, charity jars, and piggy banks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The move came after a directive by President Donald Trump to Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent earlier this year to halt minting the coins, calling them \"wasteful.\"<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/bitcoin-price-after-trump-news-boosts-crypto-market-sentiment\"> Trump</a></span>, in his letter, cited the rising expense and limited uses of pennies in the present cashless economy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It now takes 3.69 cents to produce a penny, nearly four times its face value, Treasury estimates. A decade ago, it took around 1.3 cents. It is the expense of keeping pennies in circulation that has led to annual losses, with the Treasury estimating a saving of $56 million in the first year when production is halted.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Coin No Longer Worth Its Price</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Although beloved by some for sentimental reasons, the penny has long been a target of reform. Not only do detractors argue the coin is antiquated, they also contend that it is costly to the environment, constructed of zinc and copper&mdash;materials that are energy-intensive to extract and manufacture.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Even Elon Musk, the billionaire, weighed in on the issue, using his unofficial Department of Government Efficiency (Doge) Twitter account on X to pinpoint the problem of penny inefficiency. His go-viral January post sparked widespread public debate about the problem.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Treasury confirmed that the last order of penny blanks has already been placed and that from this point, the United States Mint will only be producing pennies until they use them up.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What Will Change? </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The end of penny production USA will compel companies to adjust by rounding prices to the nearest nickel. Although some consumers are concerned with minor price hikes resulting from rounding, economists say the impact will be negligible.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Other countries that have followed suit&mdash;like Canada, which got rid of its penny in 2012&mdash;have had easy transitions with little impact on inflation. The United Kingdom itself has also not been manufacturing new 1p and 2p coins in recent years due to declining cash use.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Even with the shift in logistics, the majority of economists see the transition as a step toward economic efficiency. \"It\'s symbolic, but it\'s necessary,\" says <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/05/willis-launches-fintech-insurance-solutions-with-fintech-plus\">financial</a></span> analyst Morgan Steele. \"We\'re phasing out a coin that\'s done its job in the economy now.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>End of an Era</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The penny\'s exit marks the end of an era in American life. To some, it\'s not merely a coin&mdash;it\'s a symbol of culture. From the Lincoln penny minted in 1909 to the common expression \"a penny for your thoughts,\" the lowly copper coin has a strong presence in American hearts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But as it goes digital and cash disappears, even the most sentimental rituals have to change. The end of penny production USA is not only a policy change&mdash;it\'s an indication of how money, business, and everyday life continue to change.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Collectors are already getting on the bandwagon. Demand for 2025 pennies&mdash;the final year of full minting&mdash;will increase as individuals desire a physical reminder of American history. So, if you do have a penny, maybe don\'t spend it. It will be worth more than lost forever.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-05-24', '00:24:13', 'treasury-confirms-end-of-penny-production-usa-by-2026', 'article/visionaries-network-tresury-confirms-enfd-of-penny-production.webp', 'Treasury Confirms End of Penny Production USA by 2026', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-tresury-confirms-enfd-of-penny-production.webp', 5, 2025, 'penny production, U.S. Treasury, coin phase-out, end of penny, U.S. currency, coin news, U.S. economy, visionaries network, coin value, currency update, federal reserve', 'The U.S. Treasury confirms penny production will cease by 2026, marking the end of an era in American coinage and currency cost-cutting efforts.', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);
