(247, NULL, 'Tesla Launches Robotaxi Service in Austin | Limited Access Rollout', 'Tesla Robotaxi Service Launches in Austin with Limited Access', 'ai vr and automation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">After all those years of promotional buildup, teasers, and technological challenges,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.tesla.com/\">Tesla</a></span> Robotaxi service is finally up and running&mdash;starting out in Austin, Texas. The pilot, launched this week with modest fanfare, is a significant milestone toward Elon Musk\'s dream of a world without drivers. The first riders? Social media personalities and online content creators, specially selected to clog the internet with first impressions and going-viral content.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Tesla Robotaxi service is operating in limited mode. Through a small fleet of specially outfitted Model Y vehicles, the rides are geofenced to a specific region of Austin, and invite-only riders can take them now. The vehicles are equipped with Tesla\'s new Full Self-Driving (FSD) software and camera-based autonomy&mdash;still, however, a human safety net. A Tesla safety monitor is on board every vehicle for this pilot mode.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Despite its celebrity status, Tesla is entering a field already populated. Alphabet\'s Waymo already has a fleet of fully autonomous taxis plying the streets since 2018, most recently in Phoenix, Arizona. The only catch? Waymo employs radar and lidar sensors, while Tesla has chosen to be \"vision-only,\" using cameras and neural networks. Some safety experts have panned the move, especially given Tesla\'s accident history and the U.S. auto safety agency\'s current probes into its autonomous claims.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But Musk is hopeful. In a congratulatory tweet on X (formerly Twitter), he teased:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Massive congrats to the @Tesla_AI chip design &amp; software teams on a tremendous @Robotaxi launch!!! Ten years of hard work coming to fruition. Both chip and AI software teams were built from the ground up at Tesla.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One thing that caught people\'s attention? The fixed price point&mdash;$4.20. Whether it\'s a sarcastic comment or a publicity stunt, Musk never disappoints.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What is a Robotaxi?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Tesla Robotaxi service is Musk\'s grander vision: a future with self-driving <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../magazine/profile/ev-electra-wins-a-spot-in-the-top-business-leaders-awards-2025\">electric taxis</a></span> reducing traffic, pollution, and accidents. All Robotaxis are based on the Model Y platform and come with Tesla\'s Autopilot and Full Self-Driving (FSD) software bundle to navigate roads.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While Waymo or Cruise uses costly lidar systems like everybody else\'s autonomous vehicles, Tesla\'s uses only cameras and AI processing. Although this has been controversial, especially under tough circumstances like rain, fog, or dark alleys, this has kept Tesla\'s prices much lower.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Federal authorities are observing closely. In fact, the U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) is requesting more details regarding how Tesla\'s autonomous systems react in real-world environments, particularly after previous crashes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>How Does the Tesla Robotaxi Work?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are just 10&ndash;20 Tesla Robotaxis in Austin. Operation is 6 AM to midnight, excluding highways, airports, and weather-impacted zones. You must have an invitation as an eligible user to have access to the system.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">When Robotaxi goes public, riders will simply need to download a specific app. Taking a ride will be similar to Uber or Lyft&mdash;put in a destination, receive an estimated fare and wait time, and monitor your ride in real-time. When the vehicle pulls up, users simply match the license plate number, enter the vehicle, and click \"Start\" through the app to start.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Aboard, passengers can customize the ride by tweaking climate control, seat position, and even music&mdash;all via app or touchscreen. Riders can call for help or make the vehicle pull over or stop in case help is needed. After the ride, passengers exit, close the doors, and offer their feedback&mdash;all through the app interface.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-24', '00:41:42', 'tesla-robotaxi-service-launches-in-austin-with-limited-access', 'article/visionaries-network-tesla-robotaxi-services-launches-in-austin.webp', 'Tesla Robotaxi Service Launches in Austin with Limited Access', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-tesla-robotaxi-services-launches-in-austin.webp', 6, 2025, 'Tesla Robotaxi, Austin Robotaxi launch, Tesla autonomous service, visionaries network, self-driving taxi Austin, Tesla Robotaxi limited access, autonomous vehicle service, Tesla news 2025', 'Tesla has officially launched its Robotaxi service in Austin, Texas, with limited access for select users. Discover how this innovative autonomous ride-hailing pilot is shaping the future of urban transport.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(248, NULL, 'Death Stranding 2 PC Port Expected in 2026 | Key Reasons Explained', 'Death Stranding 2 PC Port Likely in 2026, Here&rsquo;s Why', 'Entertainment and Recreation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Last but not least, after all the rumor-mongering over the years,&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.kojimaproductions.jp/en/death-stranding-2\">Death Stranding 2</a></span> is on the cards. Hideo Kojima\'s ambitious follow-up takes up where Sam Bridges left off in the 2019 Death Stranding. While the game itself is only releasing on PlayStation 5, however, lots of PC gamers are left wondering: Will Death Stranding 2 be ported to PC?</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While no official confirmation has been issued, all signs point to yes. Kojima Productions has a history of releasing its signature titles on PC after a short exclusivity period on PlayStation. Not only does this increase the game\'s consumer base, but this also taps into a massive PC gaming market.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Looking Back: The First Port</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To estimate the possibility of a Death Stranding 2 PC port, we should consider what happened to the first title. Launched in November 2019 as a PS4 exclusive game, Death Stranding saw the light of day on PC in July 2020&mdash;eight months later.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The PC version was also well-received, with improved graphics, improved frame rates, and bonus material, like fantastic crossovers with other games. It also brought the game to an entirely new generation of individuals, many of whom had never experienced the innovative, genre-defying gameplay.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This successful porting venture has provided a solid foundation for the sequel.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Will Death Stranding 2 come to PC?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">So far, no official statement of a Death Stranding 2 PC release by Kojima Productions or Sony has been made. That being said, given industry practice and past precedent, it\'s probably a certainty. PlayStation does negotiate timed exclusivity in major titles, but they always seem to come to PC.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Both the fans and critics have the view that the same pattern will be repeated for Death Stranding 2. The game will be PS5 exclusive for some months&mdash;six to eight months&mdash;before appearing on PC platforms.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Predicted Release Date for PC </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">If Death Stranding 2 maintains the same timeline as the original, then a PC launch would be imminent in the first half of 2026. The February or March 2026 launch window would give PlayStation enough time to savor the exclusive sales while also giving Kojima Productions enough time to refine the game for PC players.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While this date is speculative, most insiders believe that development on the PC version is already happening in parallel with the PS5 version.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>How the PC Port Makes Sense</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are some solid reasons to release a Death Stranding 2 PC port:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Market demand:</strong> PC gaming has never been more popular. To be outside this market would be folly.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Proven success:</strong> The initial PC port was a critical and commercial success, demonstrating that there\'s a hungry audience.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Partnerships secured:</strong> Kojima Productions had previously secured a partnership with 505 Games for the initial PC release, so a second partnership is highly probable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition, PC ports typically include bonus content, improved graphics, and mod support&mdash;elements that only help to make the PC port more attractive to hardcore gamers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Final Thoughts </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While the Death Stranding 2 PC version has not been officially announced yet, all the signs are pointing in that direction. History, customer demand, and dev intent all suggest it is a matter of when, not if, Sam Bridges walks onto PC screens once again.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/live-streaming-technology-in-online-casinos-transforms-gaming\">Gamers</a></span> who wish to play on PC will have to wait until sometime early in 2026. For now, your best bet is to watch for updates from Kojima Productions.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-24', '00:52:45', 'death-stranding-2-pc-port-likely-in-2026-heres-why', 'article/visionaries-network-death-stranding-2pc-port-likely-in-2026.webp', 'Death Stranding 2 PC Port Likely in 2026, Here&rsquo;s Why', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-death-stranding-2pc-port-likely-in-2026.webp', 6, 2025, 'Death Stranding 2 PC, Death Stranding 2 release date, visionaries network, Kojima Productions, DS2 PC 2026, Death Stranding sequel, Death Stranding 2 news, PC gaming 2026', 'Death Stranding 2 may arrive on PC in 2026, following the timeline of the original release. Learn why the port is likely delayed and what it means for fans and PC gamers.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(249, NULL, 'Hims Stock Plunges 20% After Wegovy Deal Falls Through', 'Hims stock plunges over 20% after Wegovy deal collapses', 'banking and fintech', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://investors.hims.com/news/default.aspx\">Hims &amp; Hers Health Inc.</a></span> saw its stock take a dive this week after Novo Nordisk abruptly ended its weight-loss pill partnership. The move prompted a surprise selloff in Hims\' shares of the online health firm, with Hims stock plunges over 20% on Monday &mdash; its largest decline in over two years.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The fallout is due to increasing controversy from the sale of compounded versions of semaglutide, the active pharmaceutical ingredient in Novo\'s incredibly successful obesity drug Wegovy. While Hims has insisted that it never actually sold compounded semaglutide directly, the increasing scrutiny regarding telehealth platforms supposedly selling unapproved versions led Novo Nordisk to end the partnership.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Novo Walks Away Over Compounded Drug Issues</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Novo Nordisk, the maker of both Ozempic and Wegovy, has been particularly vocal in its criticism of compounded semaglutide &mdash; <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/alembic-pharmaceuticals-wins-usfda-approval-for-pantoprazole-injection\">pharmacy</a></span>-produced copies by pharmacies when name-brand products are in short supply. Compounded products are not FDA-approved and their safety and effectiveness are uncertain.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While Hims had partnered with Novo to sell Wegovy on its online prescription platform, the increasing legal gray area in the sale of weight-loss pills might have been too perilous for the drug giant. Analysts speculate that Novo shifted to protect its brand image, avoiding any online platform associated with unscrupulous or non-FDA-approved drug sales.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a release, Novo Nordisk said the move was part of its global effort to enable responsible patient access to its medicines. Hims, however, claimed that it does not sell or distribute compounded drugs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Hims stock plunges over 20%: A Blow to Investor Sentiment</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Wall Street responded hastily to this split. Hims stock plunges over 20%, sending shockwaves through the health tech and investor communities. The investors had been relying on the company\'s for-profit entry into the GLP-1 weight-loss drug market as a source of future capital. The loss of Novo\'s support now threatens those plans.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This sudden drop is reflective of broader doubt about Hims\' growth strategy. While the company has done well in categories like men\'s wellness, skin health, and mental health treatments, weight-loss medications were meant to be a game-changer &mdash; possibly catapulting Hims to a new level of high-margin pharma products.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Experts now argue over whether the firm jumped so quickly into the highly regulated sector without adequate oversight or strategic protection.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What\'s Next for Hims &amp; Hers?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Despite the glitch, the management at Hims insists that the company remains robust. In a public statement following the <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/05/costco-stock-forecast-2025-what-investors-should-expect\">stock</a></span> drop, the company reaffirmed that it will continue pursuing partnerships that are aligned with regulations and standards of patient safety. It also referenced its expanding product line and user base as signs of robustness.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But the week\'s most significant story has been Hims stock plunges over 20%, showing how quickly public opinion can shift. It\'s an age in which health care and technology become more and more entwined, and trust, compliance, and transparency are essential. The market for weight-loss drugs may be lucrative, but it\'s also full of legal risk that can make or break a partnership &mdash; and a stock price.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Going forward, Hims must restore investor and consumer confidence. That will mean clearly stating its stances on compounded medications, complying with all FDA guidelines, and perhaps reforming how it approaches high-risk pharma classes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The loss of the Wegovy deal is a short-term loss, but how Hims acts over the next several weeks will be whether it can bounce back &mdash; or whether this 20% drop is the start of a more extended downturn.</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-25', '00:25:27', 'hims-stock-plunges-over-20-after-wegovy-deal-collapses', 'article/visionariesnetwork-hims-stock-plunges-over-twenty-percent.webp', 'Hims stock plunges over 20% after Wegovy deal collapses', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionariesnetwork-hims-stock-plunges-over-twenty-percent.webp', 6, 2025, 'Hims stock, Wegovy deal, Hims &amp; Hers Health, stock market news, visionaries network, HIMS share price, Wegovy collapse, biotech stocks, healthcare stocks, HIMS news', 'Hims &amp; Hers Health Inc. shares dropped over 20% after its anticipated deal involving weight-loss drug Wegovy collapsed, raising investor concerns about future growth prospects.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(250, NULL, 'Bezos Venice Wedding Protest Sparks Global Attention', 'Bezos Venice Wedding Protest Draws Global Attention', 'agriculture and rural development', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Amazon CEO&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/money/Jeff-Bezos\">Jeff Bezos</a></span> will marry fianc&eacute;e Lauren Sanchez this week in one of the most celebrity-studded weddings of the year. Bezos\' and Sanchez\' three-day wedding will be held between June 26 and June 28 on Italy\'s island of San Giorgio off Venice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As much as the wedding has made international headlines over its A-list guest list, it has also unleashed a frenzy of local outrage, leading to what has become the Bezos Venice wedding protest.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>San Giorgio Island Transformed into Exclusive Venue</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The newlywed couple has allegedly rented the whole island for their VIP party, with over 200 A-listers in attendance. Guests will be on Bezos\' $500 million yacht, Koru, during the partying, making a spectacle that has further infuriated many Venetians. They say the wedding is a symbol of the growing divide between the super-rich and ordinary people&mdash;and they\'re protesting in the streets to have their say.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Activists Trigger a Public Uproar</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">On June 23, protesters from organizations like Greenpeace and \"Everyone Hates Elon\" made their point clear and loud. They rolled out a giant placard in St Mark\'s Square addressed to Bezos and demanding that billionaires be taxed. Their protest is part of a larger movement that is unfolding in the city, the Bezos Venice wedding protest, condemning not only the single person, but a system that permits gargantuan wealth to dominate public life.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>\"No Space for Bezos\": The Local Resistance</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Another outspoken group, \"No Space for Bezos,\" has started protesting against what they describe as the \"privatization of Venice.\" They think that the billionaire is turning the old town into his personal party zone. Protester Alice Bazzoli told local media, \"He is going to use the whole city like a private ballroom, as a private event space, as if the citizens are not there.\" Protesters have also criticized <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/amazon-retail-chief-stresses-balance-between-cost-cutting-and-innovation\">Amazon</a></span> for destroying small businesses and exploiting workers, stoking a highly charged atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>More than a Wedding: A Fight for Equality </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the demonstrators explained to Reuters, \"The issue is not the wedding. The issue is the system. We believe that it is not possible for one billionaire to lease a city to play with.\" There were others who mentioned the tax rate of Bezos, which was said to be as low as 1.1%, and questioned how someone so affluent could give back so little to society.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>City Officials Defend the Glamorous Affair</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Despite the criticism, local politicians are embracing the celebrity wedding. Venice Mayor Luigi Brugnaro and Veneto Governor Luca Zaia both jumped to defend the wedding, describing it as an economic bonanza for the city. Zaia estimated the wedding to add between &euro;20 to &euro;30 million to the regional economy, a boost in revenue for hotels, caterers, and gondola companies.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A City Grappling with Fame and Frustration</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">But these promises have not been enough to quiet the Bezos Venice wedding protest. The locals remain concerned that such high-end events make it appear acceptable for Venice to be a high-end playground for the wealthy, not a living city with real people, culture, and struggles.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>More Than A Wedding &mdash; A Symbolic Divide </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The growing protest movement is an indication of Venice\'s constant fight against commercialization, overtourism, and cultural erosion. While some see Bezos\' wedding as a lavish love party, others see it as a bitter reminder of elitism and inequality.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As wedding dates approach, it is clear that Venice will not only be hosting an amazing wedding but also a significant public discourse on money, space, and power.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-25', '00:31:06', 'bezos-venice-wedding-protest-draws-global-attention', 'article/visionaries-network-bezos-venice-wedding-protest-draws.webp', 'Bezos Venice Wedding Protest Sparks Global Attention', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-bezos-venice-wedding-protest-draws.webp', 6, 2025, 'Jeff Bezos wedding, Venice protest, Bezos wedding protest, climate protest Venice, Bezos news, billionaire wedding, environmental protest, Bezos Venice, Jeff Bezos 2025', 'Jeff Bezos&rsquo; lavish wedding in Venice faced environmental protests that drew global media coverage, spotlighting concerns over climate impact and billionaire extravagance.', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(251, NULL, 'Philadelphia and Newark Power Outage Today After Storms &ndash; Thousands In the Dark', 'Philadelphia and Newark Power Outage Today After Storms', 'brand management digital marketing and business', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Philadelphia and Newark power outage today has left thousands of individuals in the dark after a string of severe storms swept the region Thursday night.&nbsp;<span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.peco.com/\">PECO Energy Company (PECO)</a></span>, the dominant electric utility company in southeastern Pennsylvania, reported widespread outages in multiple counties in the two states.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and Newark, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/03/northwind-midstream-expands-gas-treatment-and-energy-reliability-in-new-mexico\">Delaware</a></span>, residents are reporting power outages after driving through the area of high wind and heavy rain, according to PECO\'s official outage map. The utility company posted a message on its site warning the public about downed lines and advising people not to approach or touch any electrical wires.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Extreme high winds and rain have moved through our service area. Avoid touching or handling electrical wires and presume all wires on the ground are live and dangerous,\" the alert warned.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>The Top Most Affected Counties by the Outage</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Up to this point today, based on PECO data, five Pennsylvania counties have weathered the worst of the destruction:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Delaware County &ndash; 72,155 outages</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Bucks County &ndash; 71,893 outages</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Montgomery County &ndash; 70,422 outages</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Chester County &ndash; 40,786 outages</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Philadelphia County &ndash; 20,791 outages</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For York County, nearly 218 outages were reported as well. Newark, Delaware, also experienced considerable service disruptions, although numbers have yet to be updated.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Storm Spreads Blazes and Narrow Escapes</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Philadelphia and Newark power outage today is part of a series of weather-related mishaps on Thursday. In Blue Bell, Pennsylvania, a tree had fallen on a car carrying a family of individuals. Luckily, there were no reported injuries.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Meanwhile, a suspected weather-related house fire occurred in Westtown Township in Chester County at Westbourne Road. Officials confirmed that there were no injuries and that the house was likely vacant at the time. The fire is under investigation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tornado Warnings and Severe Alerts Issued</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Earlier today, a tornado warning was issued by the National Weather Service at about 5:00 p.m. for New Castle, Delaware, and Chester counties. The warning lasted for about 30 minutes as heavy rains and gusts ravaged the region, leading to damaged infrastructure, uprooted trees, and blocked drainage.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PECO had anticipated the storm\'s impact, sending a pre-emptive advisory</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>\"Severe thunderstorms will deliver hazardous rain and gusty winds to PECO service areas by 9 p.m. Be on the lookout for potential power lines and fallen trees.\"</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>PECO Urges Caution and Patience</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Due to the massive number of outages, PECO alerted customers to a possible delay in notifications. The utility advised people to report the outages through the PECO mobile app or by telephone at 1-800-841-4141.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"We notice the disruption and are moving as quickly and safely as possible to restore service to all affected customers,\" a PECO spokesperson stated.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Authorities have not yet given a precise time limit for that return, but have ensured that workers are prioritizing the most essential areas to deal with first.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What\'s Next?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Residents should stay indoors if possible and avoid driving in areas where downed power lines or floodwater can be dangerous. Emergency response personnel track weather closely and assist with cleanup and safety operations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To receive the latest information about the Philadelphia and Newark power outage today, customers can visit PECO\'s outage center or view local news websites.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-25', '23:49:14', 'philadelphia-and-newark-power-outage-today-after-storms', 'article/visionaries-network-philadelphia-newark-power-outage.webp', 'Philadelphia and Newark Power Outage Today After Storms', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-philadelphia-newark-power-outage.webp', 6, 2025, 'Philadelphia power outage, Newark power outage, storm damage, Delaware County, Gloucester County, PSE&amp;G outages, PECO outages, severe thunderstorms, visionaries network, power restoration', 'Severe thunderstorms swept through the Philadelphia and Newark regions, knocking down trees and utility lines. Thousands of homes lost power&mdash;PECO, PSE&amp;G, Delmarva, and Atlantic City Electric report widespread outages. Crews are working urgently to restore electricity as residents deal with', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(252, '', 'McDonald&rsquo;s to Drop Krispy Kreme Doughnuts &ndash; Final Day Julyâ€¯2,â€¯2025', 'McDonald&rsquo;s Krispy Kreme Doughnut Removal Starts July 2', 'brand management digital marketing and business', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beginning July 2, 2025, McDonald\'s Krispy Kreme doughnut phase-out will begin in 2,400 United States restaurants. The union of the two food giants is finally coming to an end, and lovers of the sweet treat will no longer be able to spot them on McDonald\'s menus.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The withdrawn products are:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Original Glazed Doughnut</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Chocolate Iced with Sprinkles Doughnut</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Chocolate Iced Kreme Filled Doughnut</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">These had previously been sold separately or in batches of six, together with <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.mcdonalds.com/us/en-us.html\">McDonald\'s</a></span> other treats like Oreo McFlurry and Hot Fudge Sundae.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Sweet Partnership That Soured</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The McDonald&rsquo;s <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.krispykreme.com/\">Krispy Kreme doughnut</a></span> removal marks the end of a relationship that started in late 2023. The doughnut trial initially introduced at 160 McDonald\'s <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/05/robot-burger-restaurant-in-california-serves-meals-in-27-seconds\">restaurants</a></span> in Kentucky was a hit and created buzz. In response to positive reviews, the companies launched the offer in October 2024 at Chicago-area restaurants.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/05/sateliot-australia-5g-satellite-iot-set-for-15m-expansion\">Expansion</a></span> initiatives were already in progress to go national by the end of 2026. But plans are on hold for a while.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a statement on June 24, <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/josh-charlesworth-6151645/\">Krispy Kreme CEO Josh Charlesworth</a></span> said:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Both our companies functioned very tightly together, having common support for execution, marketing, and training, with a great consumer experience. Ultimately, efforts to align our costs with unit demand were not successful, and the partnership was no longer viable for us.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why McDonald\'s Krispy Kreme Doughnut Removal Happened</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">While pilot tests were successful and even better than expected in the initial stages, the same did not happen when the scale increased. Demand at a larger scale failed to live up to expectations, and the costs remained too high to be justifiable, according to an Associated Press report.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">McDonald\'s has seemingly experienced supply chain and logistics problems with keeping a consistent supply of Krispy Kreme doughnuts. In the meantime, Krispy Kreme was unable to keep operational costs in line with the amount of sales they gained.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Therefore, McDonald\'s Krispy Kreme doughnut removal was the most sensible next move for both companies.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>What\'s Next for Both Brands</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Krispy Kreme is now set to return to expanding its own branded distribution system. The company has been expanding its retail store and convenience store base and is likely to double down on that.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Meanwhile, McDonald\'s is going back to basics and will revamp its breakfast. Although demand for breakfast items remains strong among consumers, the chain feels more secure in tweaking such classics as Egg McMuffins and hash browns than experimenting with new dessert partnerships.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Customer Reaction to Krispy Kreme Withdrawal</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">On Twitter, the reaction was mixed. Some loyal customers were irritated at the disappearance of a convenient pickup point for their favorite doughnuts, but others were not.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>One of Twitter (formerly X) users penned:</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Never gonna make it long. Krispy Kremes are too delicate for fast food schedules.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>Another joined:</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Sad to lose them, but Krispy Kreme is something to put in a box on your breakfast table &mdash; not a bag in a drive-thru.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>McDonald\'s Krispy Kreme Doughnut Removal&mdash;A Final Thought</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Though short-lived, the McDonald\'s-Krispy Kreme experiment was a daring attempt to combine two of America\'s favorite brands. But the McDonald\'s Krispy Kreme doughnut removal signals that all marriages are not meant to be forever.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beginning July 2, shoppers will have to visit Krispy Kreme stores or retailers for their doughnut fix. Meanwhile, McDonald\'s will continue to simplify its core menu as the golden arches say goodbye to glazed rings&mdash;forever.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-27', '00:26:52', 'mcdonalds-to-drop-krispy-kreme-doughnuts-final-day-july22025', 'article/visionaries-network-mcdonald-krispy-kreme-doughnut.webp', 'McDonald&rsquo;s Krispy Kreme Doughnut Removal Starts July 2', 'https://thesiliconreview.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-mcdonald-krispy-kreme-doughnut.webp', 6, 2025, 'McDonald&rsquo;s Krispy Kreme removal, McDoughnuts end, Krispy Kreme partnership ending, visionaries network, McDonald&rsquo;s doughnuts news, fastâ€‘food menu change', 'Discover why McDonald&rsquo;s is ending its Krispy Kreme doughnut partnership on Julyâ€¯2,â€¯2025. After launching the treat in over 2,400 US locations, the collaboration proved unsustainable for Krispy Kreme, prompting both brands to refocus on their core businesses', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(253, NULL, 'Google Launches Geminiâ€¯CLI: AI-Powered Coding from the Command Line', 'Google launches Gemini CLI for easier AI-powered coding', 'ai vr and automation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/google-cloud-next-2025-unveils-smarter-ai-tools-and-chips\">Google</a></span> has introduced a new <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"../../2025/04/ai-powered-stroke-rehabilitation-technology-enhances-patient-safety\">AI-powered tool</a></span> called Gemini CLI, an open-source coding companion used to revolutionize how developers interact with their systems. With this new command-line interface, developers can now write, debug, and manage code using natural language instead of technical syntax &mdash; all from the terminal.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Its global launch is seen as Google\'s ambitious foray into the aggressive market of AI code assistant competitors like OpenAI\'s Codex and Anthropic\'s Claude Code. However, what makes Gemini CLI stand out is that it emphasizes transparency and accessibility.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Coding With Conversations</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Before, terminal work was always a set of specific commands and programming code. <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://gemini.google/about/?hl=en-IN\">Gemini CLI</a></span> eliminates that by simply allowing users to tell it what they wish to do in plain English. From creating site templates to debugging or automating, the tool accepts natural language inputs and converts them into code.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Instead of learning particular commands by heart, programmers can now just talk to their terminal like they talk to their coworker,\" explained Google Senior Staff Software Engineer Taylor Mullen. \"It\'s about making coding easier and faster.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Open Source for Everybody</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the most unique aspects of Gemini CLI is that it is open-source. Developers can get at the code, customize it to fit particular requirements, or help make it better. This is a departure from how Google did things before, trending towards the open community rather than having powerful AI tools trapped in corporate silos.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By going open source, Google hopes to make available not only veteran developers but also students, solo developers, and tech hobbyists who might otherwise not have been able to access the like.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Founded on Gemini AI\'s Power</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The feature is one of a broader family of Gemini products Google has been releasing throughout the past year. The company unveiled Gemma, its set of open large language models, earlier in 2024, followed by Gemini AI integration into Google Docs, among other applications.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With Gemini CLI, that same intelligence now comes to the command line. It brings activities like code explanations, documentation generation, and project management, and even content generation like blog drafts or video scripts &mdash; all from the developer\'s command terminal of choice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Individual Google account owners are offered free access to the Gemini Code Assist level tier, up to 1,000 requests per day. Additional limits are offered for a fee, for professional developers and enterprise teams.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Designed for Creators and Developers Both</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Even though its main function is designed for software developers, Gemini CLI is general in nature. Freelancers, artists, and bloggers may use its features. It can be employed to draft technical guides, build landing pages, and automate routine digital tasks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"AI tools such as this will be included in every creative process in the near future,\" <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ryanjsalva/\">Google\'s Senior Director of Product Ryan J. Salva</a></span> stated. \"Whether you are coding, writing, or designing, having a tool like Gemini CLI alongside you can enable you to accomplish more in a shorter amount of time.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A Glimpse of the Future</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Google\'s Gemini CLI release is an indicator of the tech giant\'s commitment to making AI more accessible and inclusive. While other software requires steep learning curves, this assistant simplifies things for more individuals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By bringing the best of conversational AI to the command line, Gemini CLI is a vision of the future where coding is more problem-solving and creativity. and less memorization.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As developers begin to experiment with this tool, it becomes clear that natural language interfaces are the way forward. And with its open-source origins and strong AI backing, Gemini CLI could well become the go-to for today\'s developers in the near future.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'visionariesnetwork Team', '2025-06-27', '00:35:49', 'google-launches-gemini-cli-for-easier-ai-powered-coding', 'article/visionaries-network-google-launches-gemini-cli.webp', 'Google Launches Geminiâ€¯CLI: AI-Powered Coding from the Command Line', 'http://www.visionariesnetwork.com/thumb/article/visionaries-network-google-launches-gemini-cli.webp', 6, 2025, 'Google Gemini CLI, Gemini Code Assist, AI coding tool, Gemini 2.5 Pro, openâ€‘source CLI, developer AI assistant, commandâ€‘line AI, visionaries network', 'Google has introduced Geminiâ€¯CLI, an open-source command-line interface powered by the Geminiâ€¯2.5â€¯Pro AI model. Available free to developers with a Gemini Code Assist license, it supports tasks like code generation, debugging, content creation, and even image/video generation&mdash;all directl', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);
