(116, 12, '<p><strong>Zappi: Revolutionizing Consumer Insights with Connected, Continuous Research</strong></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In today&rsquo;s fast-paced market environment, brands face immense pressure to innovate quickly and launch campaigns that resonate with diverse audiences. Yet traditional market research&mdash;often slow, siloed, and rigid&mdash;struggles to keep pace. We introduce you to Zappi: a world-class, AI-driven consumer insights platform designed to embed consumer feedback into every phase of brand, product, and advertisement development.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>A New Approach to Market Research</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At its core, Zappi harnesses agile, automated research tools that clients report deliver insights in as little as 12 hours, with full dashboards ready within 48&ndash;72 hours. Far from one-off studies, the platform builds a persistent, connected dataset&mdash;what Zappi describes as a &ldquo;learning loop&rdquo;&mdash;where each test informs the next. Rather than treating insights as isolated projects, teams can aggregate learnings over time, making continuous improvements and avoiding repeated mistakes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Fast, Reliable, Repeatable</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Zappi combines automated sample quality, repeatable survey templates, and comprehensive benchmarking to deliver speed and consistency:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Trusted Sample</strong>: ISO- and ESOMAR-compliant panels, supported by AI-powered fraud detection.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Repeatable Designs</strong>: A consistent 80/20 mix of standardized and customizable questions enables cross-study comparability and database building.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Global Norms &amp; Benchmarks</strong>: Users can test ideas against internal or industry-wide norms to understand real-world performance potential.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">These capabilities give clients data they can trust&mdash;backed by internal quality scores and compliance with international research standards.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Driven by AI &amp; Actionable Reporting</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Zappi&rsquo;s platform isn&rsquo;t just fast&mdash;it&rsquo;s smart. AI-generated reporting, prompt-engineered narratives, smart auto-coding of themes, and real-time charting make insights immediately accessible. Users receive instant visualizations, deep-dive verbatim, and diagnostic guidance&mdash;no waiting, no heavy analytics lift.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Solving Real Business Problems</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Zappi&rsquo;s agile model supports multiple phases of brand work:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Innovation</strong>: Early-stage concept testing, iterative refinement, and pre-launch validation keep consumers involved from spark to shelf.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Advertising</strong>: From concept to pre-test to final spot, clients like PepsiCo report up to 30% improvements in ad effectiveness by continually optimizing creative elements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This flexible suite empowers insights teams to go beyond tactical, one-off studies&mdash;helping them scale consumer insight across product innovation and creative production pipelines.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Proven Success &amp; High Profile Clients</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Trusted by global brands&mdash;Mars, PepsiCo, McDonald&rsquo;s, Wendy&rsquo;s, Vodafone, Reckitt, SoFi, Clorox&mdash;Zappi has repeatedly demonstrated ROI and efficiency gains. PepsiCo shared that their creative effectiveness increased by nearly 30%, translating to hundreds of millions in business value. McDonald&rsquo;s sees clear benefits in revisiting past research to inspire smarter product ideas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>An Organization Built for Impact</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beyond its technological offering, Zappi has built a strong ethical and cultural foundation:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>B Corp Certification</strong>: Reflects commitments to environmental sustainability and social responsibility</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Inclusion &amp; Accessibility</strong>: Signatory of the MRS Inclusion Pledge and Disability Confident Committed.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Net-Zero Ambitions</strong>: Transparency in carbon emissions, tree planting, and environmental impact.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The company has also received internal culture awards&mdash;Best Place to Work by Fast Company, Comparably, Quirks, and Great Place to Work.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Recognition &amp; Momentum</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Zappi has been honored as the &ldquo;Best Marketing Insights Platform&rdquo; at the MarTech Breakthrough Awards (2023 &amp; 2024) and recognized by Business Insider as one of the hottest MarTech companies. PitchBook notes over $171â€¯million raised via private equity, underscoring strong investor confidence.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong>Aaron Kechley, Chief Executive Officer</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\">Aaron Kechley is the CEO of Zappi, where he is focused on driving the company\'s growth strategy, expanding its global presence, and enhancing its platform to deliver transformative consumer insights solutions. At Zappi, Aaron&rsquo;s leadership supports the company&rsquo;s vision of building a connected insights ecosystem while empowering brands with data and insights that enable consumer-centricity at scale.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\">With over 25 years of experience, Aaron has led high-growth technology companies across industries, from start-ups to enterprises exceeding $1B in revenue. Prior to joining Zappi, Aaron was President at Inmar Intelligence, where he launched and scaled their Retail Media platform to over $165M. He also played a pivotal role at DataXu, where he spearheaded the transition from managed service to self-service in AI-driven media optimization, contributing to the company&rsquo;s acquisition by Roku in 2019.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\">Aaron has applied data at every stage of the customer journey, from leveraging pre-launch insights that help brands create work consumers love, to driving targeted programmatic media buying through demand-side platforms. His expertise spans product development, marketing, and customer success, with a deep focus on harnessing the power of data to solve complex business challenges.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\">Aaron holds an MBA from the MIT Sloan School of Management. When he&rsquo;s not spearheading hypergrowth for Zappi, Aaron enjoys staying active through hiking and outdoor activities, and spending time with his family. He\'s also passionate about exploring new technologies and how they intersect with marketing to drive business growthâ€‹.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'VisionariesNetwork Team', 'zappi-revolutionizing-consumer-insights-with-connected-continuous-research', '2025-06-17', 'us/visionaries-network-aaron-kechley-ceo.webp', 7, 'profile', 'Zappi transforms how brands gather consumer insights through connected, continuous research. Make faster, smarter decisions with agile, AI-powered data.', 'consumer insights, continuous research, market research, Zappi, agile insights, visionariesnetwork, AI-driven research, brand intelligence, customer data', 'Zappi &ndash; Continuous Consumer Insights for Smarter Decisions', NULL, 1, 'no', 'https://www.zappi.io/web/', ' linkedin.com/company/zappi ', 'Zappi', '2013', 'Boston, Massachusetts '),
(117, 12, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><strong>Agmatix: Harnessing Data to Revolutionize Sustainable Agriculture</strong></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Agmatix stands at the forefront of digital agriculture, delivering unified, AI-driven solutions that transform agronomic data into actionable insights. From field data collection and trial management to crop nutrition modeling and sustainable practice tracking, Agmatix empowers agronomists, agribusinesses, and research bodies to enhance efficiency, support regenerative farming methods, and drive informed decision-making across the agricultural value chain.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Company Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Agmatix, headquartered in Creve Coeur, Missouri, with global offices in Israel, the Netherlands, and Brazil, specializes in software development for agriculture.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Established in 2021 and backed by ICL Group, Agmatix offers a SaaS-based platform tailored to agronomic field trials, big data analytics, crop nutrient optimization, carbon footprint evaluation, and regenerative agriculture frameworks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The firm\'s guiding principle&mdash;&ldquo;Growing Data for Impact&rdquo;&mdash;signifies its mission: consolidating data management, predictive modeling, and sustainability practices for consistent, scalable agricultural outcomes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Core Solutions</strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Field Data Collection &amp; Analysis</strong>: Streamlines agronomic trial planning, monitoring, and results analysis&mdash;accelerating data integrity and test-to-decision cycles.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Predictive Modeling &amp; Insights</strong>: Leverages AI/ML models combined with remote sensing to generate predictive crop outcomes and nutritional recommendations&mdash;positioned as a Data-as-a-Service offering.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Crop Nutrition Management</strong>: Offers field-level decision support to optimize nutrient application as part of sustainable workflows.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Sustainable &amp; Regenerative Agriculture</strong>: Introduces RegenIQ, a scalable framework for regenerative agriculture that combines remote and on-ground data collection to track environmental impact and guide farm-level adaptation.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>AXIOM Technology</strong><br>Advanced AI and generative AI backbone that powers the platform&rsquo;s analytics and predictive capabilities, with support from AWS and NVIDIA partnerships.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Agmatix for Students</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The company offers complimentary one-year platform licenses for university agronomy students, enabling them to enhance their research, field trials, and analytical skills&mdash;earning digital credentials and hands-on data management experience.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Leadership &amp; Team</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Agmatix boasts a multidisciplinary leadership team blending agronomy professionals with technological experts. Among its key figures, President &amp; CEO Ron Baruchi champions a mission to bridge global agribusinesses and local practitioners through harmonized data-driven solutions. The company also maintains a scientific committee guiding R&amp;D initiatives.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Recognition &amp; Impact</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l2 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Named the 2025 Dataâ€‘Driven Agriculture Solutions Company of the Year, highlighting its commitment to integrating science-backed AI in agriculture.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l2 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Its RegenIQ platform has gained attention in regenerative agriculture circles for providing measurable, scalable decisionâ€‘support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Case Studies &amp; Industry Collaborations</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l3 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Deepak Fertilisers (India)</strong>: Achieved a 70% reduction in trial data analysis time&mdash;from 6 months to under a month&mdash;by adopting Agmatix&rsquo;s Trial Management platform across 1,500+ annual trials. The system enhanced data accuracy by integrating timestamps, geolocation, and photos into mobile uploads.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l3 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Stine Seed</strong>: Implemented localized insights to refine product development and support sales through data-driven analytics.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l3 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Wageningen University &amp; IFA</strong>: Collaborated to collect global crop nutrient data, emphasizing Agmatix&rsquo;s scientific and sustainability contributions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sustainability &amp; Regenerative Practices</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Through RegenIQ, Agmatix supports an outcomes-based approach to regenerative agriculture&mdash;prioritizing impactful practices by aligning with environmental standards, enabling \'whatâ€‘if\' scenario analysis, and scaling from pilot farms to multi-regional operations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why It Matters</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Efficiency &amp; Data Quality</strong>: Centralized management of field data reduces manual errors and speeds analytics.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Faster Time-to-Market</strong>: Streamlined workflows accelerate the development and registration of agricultural products.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>AI-Driven Insights</strong>: Self-guided analytics enable researchers to extract key trends and model crop behaviors effectively.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Scalable &amp; Compliant</strong>: Platform adheres to regulatory standards, serving small demo plots to broad multi-site studies.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>Education &amp; Innovation</strong>: Investment in student licenses nurtures future leaders in agritech.<br><br></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong>Ron Baruchi, President &amp; CEO, Agmatix </strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\">Ron Baruchi is a seasoned executive with more than two decades of proven leadership across technology, operations, and strategic development. His expertise spans corporate strategy, product management, innovation, operational excellence, and the application of advanced data analytics and AI/ML. Driven by a passion for systems thinking and data-led problem solving, Ron is dedicated to tackling some of agriculture&rsquo;s most complex challenges&mdash;such as boosting crop yields, enhancing crop quality, and minimizing environmental impact&mdash;through cutting-edge, sustainable AgTech solutions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; tab-stops: 159.0pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><br>&ldquo;With our tailored approach, we&rsquo;re advancing sustainability and transforming the future of agriculture, one data-driven solution at a time.&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; tab-stops: 159.0pt;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>', 'VisionariesNetwork Team', 'agmatix-harnessing-data-to-revolutionize-sustainable-agriculture', '2025-06-17', 'us/visionaries-network-ron-barucchi-ceo-agmatix.webp', 8, 'profile', 'Agmatix uses advanced data analytics to drive sustainable agriculture. Turn agronomic data into actionable insights for better crop performance and resilience.', 'sustainable agriculture, agri data analytics, visionaries network, Agmatix, precision farming, crop data solutions, agtech, smart agriculture, farming innovation', 'Agmatix &ndash; Data-Driven Solutions for Sustainable Agriculture', NULL, 1, 'no', 'https://www.agmatix.com/ ', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/agmatix/ ', 'Agmatix', ' 2021 ', 'Creve Coeur, Missouri'),
(118, 12, '<p><strong>T3 Consultants: Transforming Risk, ESG, and AI into Opportunity</strong></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a world where regulatory pressure, ESG scrutiny, and AI governance are redefining how businesses operate, T3 Consultants emerges as a beacon of strategic clarity and transformation. Based in London and female-led, T3 is not your typical consultancy. It brings together a powerhouse team of senior professionals with decades of experience across finance, technology, academia, and public policy. Their mission is bold yet clear: to help businesses turn complex compliance demands into a competitive advantage through a unique blend of insight, strategy, and implementation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At the heart of T3&rsquo;s value proposition is its senior-led, outcome-based delivery model. While many consultancies rely heavily on junior analysts, T3 ensures that every engagement is handled by top-tier professionals&mdash;former COOs, CROs, directors, and regulatory architects who have worked at some of the world&rsquo;s leading institutions. This model not only ensures deep subject-matter expertise but also guarantees that clients receive fast, actionable, and practical results tailored to their business realities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">T3&rsquo;s work is guided by three core principles: Think, Transform, and Thrive. &ldquo;Think&rdquo; is about applying strategic, policy-aligned intelligence to each client\'s unique challenges. &ldquo;Transform&rdquo; focuses on designing and embedding tailored solutions. And &ldquo;Thrive&rdquo; reflects their goal to help clients not just survive disruption, but lead with confidence and resilience in increasingly volatile markets.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The firm offers a focused suite of services across four interconnected domains: Risk &amp; Regulation, Responsible AI, Sustainability &amp; Climate Change, and Change Management. Each area is led by experts who have directly shaped international policy or led enterprise-wide transformations in these domains.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In <strong>Risk &amp; Regulation</strong>, T3 provides a 360&deg; view across financial and non-financial risks, including operational resilience, governance, compliance, and regulatory engagement. They help organizations align with UK, EU, and global regulatory frameworks such as Basel, FCA/PRA, and EMIR. The goal is not just to meet the letter of the law, but to use regulatory alignment as a way to strengthen strategic direction and stakeholder trust.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">T3 is also a global leader in <strong>Responsible AI</strong>. Their team includes former Google executives who implemented Responsible AI programs at scale, as well as contributors to the EU AI Act, OECD AI Principles, and NIST AI Risk Management Framework. T3 works with clients to develop AI governance strategies, risk management systems, training, and implementation support that ensures compliance and accountability&mdash;especially as AI regulations evolve rapidly across regions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the <strong>Sustainability and Climate</strong> practice, T3 supports businesses in navigating the complex landscape of ESG reporting, green claims, and regulatory disclosures. Their services include alignment with ISSB, CSRD, SFDR, GRI, and EU taxonomy, as well as climate risk assessments and ESG strategy development. In an era where greenwashing risks are high&mdash;over 40% of green claims in Europe were found to be misleading&mdash;T3 helps organizations build credibility and structure around their sustainability messaging and data.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Their <strong>Change Management</strong> offering complements these services by ensuring that transformations&mdash;whether regulatory, technological, or strategic&mdash;are sustainable and embedded. Using proven frameworks, they manage stakeholder alignment, risk mitigation, governance structures, and culture change. Whether it&rsquo;s navigating an AI adoption journey or implementing new ESG disclosures across business units, T3 ensures organizations are equipped for both immediate transition and long-term success.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">T3&rsquo;s impact is not just theoretical. Their leadership and teams have worked with over 25 banks and financial services firms in the past year alone. They have trained over 20 governments in risk management, won four major awards in the risk and AI space, and have had a 100% contribution rate to the development of new international standards. They&rsquo;ve also helped clients avoid reputational and regulatory fallout by auditing and correcting misleading ESG claims and implementing Responsible AI frameworks that passed internal and regulatory scrutiny.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Among T3&rsquo;s key differentiators is their collaborative model. The firm maintains a robust network of partnerships with technology vendors, research organizations, think tanks, and advocacy groups. This allows them to provide clients with not only best-in-class advisory, but also access to innovative tools, data platforms, and implementation support. Their work is scalable, practical, and always tailored to the client\'s maturity, sector, and ambition.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">T3 serves a wide array of sectors including banking, fintech, asset management, commodities, tech, aerospace, telecom, life sciences, and manufacturing. Each engagement is adapted to the regulatory environment and operational complexity of the sector, ensuring relevance and depth. Clients value T3 not just for their technical skills but for their ability to deliver fast, clear, and confident outcomes in high-stakes contexts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Recognition for T3&rsquo;s impact continues to grow. Co-founder Jen Gennai was recently shortlisted for &ldquo;AI Leader of the Year&rdquo; and included in the &ldquo;Top 33 Women Shaping Responsible AI.&rdquo; T3 was also featured as a finalist for the &ldquo;AI for Good&rdquo; award and highlighted by British-American Business in their Transatlantic Growth Tracker. These accolades underscore the firm&rsquo;s growing influence on both sides of the Atlantic.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At its core, T3 Consultants is more than a risk and regulation firm. It&rsquo;s a strategic ally for forward-thinking businesses who want to navigate complexity with clarity, embed transformation with integrity, and lead markets with purpose. For organizations that see regulation not as a burden but as a chance to lead, T3 is the trusted partner that ensures you don&rsquo;t just adapt&mdash;you thrive.<br><br><strong>Lana H.</strong>, <strong>Partner &ndash; Risk &amp; RegTech</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\">Lana H. helps organizations tackle last-minute compliance challenges while developing forward-looking regulatory strategies. At T3 Consultants, she plays a key role in bridging the gap between urgent regulatory demands&mdash;such as FCA oversight, operational resilience, the AI Act, and ESG mandates&mdash;and long-term business sustainability. Her focus is on turning compliance into a strategic advantage for clients.</p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong>&ldquo;We translate complex ESG regulations (EU Taxonomy, CSRD, SFDR, CSDDD) into actionable strategies.&rdquo;<br></strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'VisionariesNetwork Team', 't3-consultants-transforming-risk-esg-and-ai-into-opportunity', '2025-06-17', 'us/visionaries-network-t3-consultants-lana-h.webp', 9, 'profile', 'T3 Consultants help businesses navigate risk, ESG, and AI challengesâ€”turning them into growth opportunities with expert insights and data-driven strategies.', 'risk management, ESG strategy, AI consulting, T3 Consultants, sustainable business, enterprise risk, visionaries network, data-driven consulting, corporate governance', 'T3 Consultants &ndash; Turning Risk, ESG, and AI into Strategic Advantage', NULL, 1, 'no', 'https://t3-consultants.com/ ', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/t3-consultants/ ', 'T3 Consultants', ' 2023', 'Headquarters  London, GB');

